{"title_page": "Kenneth Copeland", "text_new": "{{short description|American Televangelist}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Kenneth Copeland\n| residence          = [[Fort Worth, Texas]], U.S.\n| other_names        = \n| image              = File:Kenneth Copeland 2011.jpg\n| caption            = Kenneth Copeland in 2011\n| birth_name         = Kenneth Max Copeland\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1936|12|06}}\n| birth_place        = [[Lubbock, Texas]], U.S.\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| known              = \n| occupation         = {{hlist|Author|speaker|pastor|televangelist}}\n| net_worth          = {{nowrap| [[US$]]300 million<ref name=\"Beliefnet profile\">{{cite web|title= Richest Pastor in America|url=https://www.ibtimes.com/kenneth-copeland-net-worth-evangelist-richest-pastor-world-2951331p=2|website=IBTimes|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}</ref> }} (April 2020)\n| salary             = \n| term               = \n| nationality        = [[United States|American]]\n| predecessor        = \n| years active       = 1967-present\n| successor          = \n| influences         = [[Kenneth Hagan|Kenneth Hagan]]\n| boards             = \n| movement           = [[Word of Faith]]\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Ivy Bodiford|1955|1958}}<br /> {{marriage|Cynthia Davis |1958|1961}}<br /> {{marriage|Gloria Neece|1963}}\n| partner            = \n| children           = 3\n| parents            = \n| relations          = \n| website            = {{URL|http://www.kcm.org}}\n| footnotes          = \n| party              = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n| height             = \n| weight             = \n}}\n\n'''Kenneth Max Copeland''' (born December 6, 1936) is an American [[Televangelism|televangelist]] and fraudster, and author associated with the [[Charismatic Movement]]. He runs the [[#Kenneth Copeland Ministries|Kenneth Copeland Ministries]] based in [[Tarrant County]], [[Texas]].\n\nHe has been identified as preaching the [[Prosperity theology|prosperity gospel]]. As part of his evangelism, he calls for donations to his church, with the suggestion that parishioners will get a \"hundredfold\" return on their investment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vox.com/identities/2017/9/1/15951874/prosperity-gospel-explained-why-joel-osteen-believes-prayer-can-make-you-rich-trump|title=The prosperity gospel, explained: Why Joel Osteen believes that prayer can make you rich|last=Burton|first=Tara Isabella|date=2017-09-01|website=Vox|language=en|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref> He has stirred controversy over his use of donations to finance mansions, private jets, an [[Kenneth Copeland Airport|airport]] and other lavish purchases.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Goodstein|first=Laurie|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/16/us/16gospel.html|title=Believers Invest in the Gospel of Getting Rich|date=2009-08-15|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-03-12|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/religion/2019/06/04/wealthy-televangelist-explains-his-fleet-private-jets-its-biblical-thing/|title=A wealthy televangelist explains his fleet of private jets: \u2018It\u2019s a biblical thing\u2019|date=2019|work=The Washington Post|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nDuring [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|the pandemic of COVID-19]] in 2020, Copeland gained national attention for his comments and actions in response to the outbreak. He repeatedly claimed that the pandemic had ended or would soon end, that he could heal followers of it, and that his followers should continue paying tithes if they lost their jobs in the economic crisis that the pandemic caused.<ref name=\"independent-corona\" /> He later made claims to have destroyed the virus and to have ended the still-ongoing pandemic.<ref name=\"independent-corona\" />\n\n==Personal life==\nKenneth Max Copeland was born in [[Lubbock, Texas|Lubbock]], [[Texas]], to Aubrey Wayne and Vinita Pearl (n\u00e9e Owens) Copeland.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ancestrylibrary.com/interactive/8781/TXBTH_1936_000208e?pid=2675215|title=Texas Birth Index, 1903-1997|website=www.ancestrylibrary.com|access-date=2018-04-18}}</ref> He was raised in [[West Texas]] near a [[United States Army Air Forces]] [[List of United States Army airfields|airfield]], which inspired him to become a [[aviator|pilot.]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.biographyministries.com/kenneth-copeland.html |title=Kenneth Copeland |publisher=biographyministries.com |year=2008 |accessdate=December 17, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081016102647/http://www.biographyministries.com/kenneth-copeland.html |archivedate=October 16, 2008 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://newsok.com/article/3275378|title=AP IMPACT: Relatives of televangelist prosper|last=Gorski|first=Eric|date=2008-07-27|work=NewsOK.com|access-date=2018-04-18}}</ref>\n\nCopeland married Ivy Bodiford in October 1955 and became the parents of Terri Copeland Pearsons;<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://erecord.co.lubbock.tx.us/recorder/eagleweb/viewDoc.jsp?node=DOCCM-120611|title=Lubbock County Marriage Certificate|website=erecord.co.lubbock.tx.us|access-date=2018-04-18}}</ref> they divorced in 1958. Kenneth married Gloria (n\u00e9e Neece) on April 13, 1963.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kennethcopelandblog.com/2010/08/01/kenneth-and-gloria-copeland-the-untold-story/|title=Kenneth and Gloria Copeland, The Untold Story|publisher=KennethCopelandBlog.com |date=August 1, 2010 |accessdate=March 7, 2016}}</ref> They are the parents of John Copeland and Kellie Copeland. Gloria co-hosts the ministry's flagship broadcast, \"The Believer's Voice of Victory,\" alongside her husband. Kellie preaches throughout the United States, as does Terri, who also preaches at Eagle Mountain International Church, which is pastored by her husband, George Pearsons.\n\nPrior to becoming a [[born again Christian]] in November 1962, Copeland was a recording artist on the [[Imperial Records]] label, having one ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' Top 40 hit (\"Pledge of Love\", which charted in the Top 40 on April 20, 1957, stayed on the charts for 15 weeks, and peaked at #17).<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books/about/The_Billboard_Book_of_Top_40_Hits.html?id=drgq4g0rmVsC|title=The Billboard Book of Top 40 Hits|last=Whitburn|first=Joel|date=2000|publisher=Billboard Books|year=|isbn=9780823076901|location=|pages=151}}</ref>\n\nFollowing his conversion, Copeland devoted his life to the gospel and ministry work.<ref>Kenneth Copeland, \"The Word in My life...\", Kenneth Copeland Ministries Catalog (Fort Worth: Kenneth Copeland Ministries, n.d.), 3.</ref> In the fall of 1967, he enrolled in [[Oral Roberts University]], where he soon became pilot and chauffeur to [[Oral Roberts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oru.edu/alumni/excell/spring06/feature1.html|title=ORU alumni|accessdate=April 16, 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090210080448/http://www.oru.edu/alumni/excell/spring06/feature1.html|archivedate=February 10, 2009|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nCopeland sat on the evangelical executive advisory board that Donald Trump assembled during his campaign for the presidency.<ref>{{cite news |last=Sharman |first=Jon |date=February 6, 2018 |title=Trump adviser urges followers to 'inoculate yourself with the word of God' against flu |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-politics/gloria-copeland-trump-adviser-flu-shot-jesus-god-christian-evangelical-healing-miracle-a8197801.html |work=The Independent |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> Appointment to the board did not require endorsement of his bid for presidency, <ref>{{cite news |last=Wing |first=Nick |date=June 21, 2016 |title=Donald Trump\u2019s New Evangelical Adviser Was Sure God Had Chosen Ted Cruz To Be President |url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/donald-trump-kenneth-copeland_n_5769880de4b065534f47fb24 |work=HuffPost |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> and Copeland clarified that he did not endorse Trump at the time.<ref>{{cite news |last=Shellnutt |first=Kate |last2=Eekhoff Zylstra |first2=Sarah  |date=June 22, 2016 |title=Who\u2019s Who of Trump\u2019s \u2018Tremendous\u2019 Faith Advisers |url=http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/2016/june-web-only/whos-who-of-trumps-tremendous-faith-advisors.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160707085329/http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/2016/june-web-only/whos-who-of-trumps-tremendous-faith-advisors.html |archivedate=July 7, 2016 |work=Christianity Today |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> Before the 2016 election, Copeland said that Christians that did not vote for Trump would be guilty of murder, referring to the abortion policy of Hillary Clinton.<ref>{{cite news |last=Pulliam Bailey  |first=Sarah |date=October 11, 2016 |title=Televangelist: Christians who don\u2019t vote are \u2018going to be guilty of murder\u2019 |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/acts-of-faith/wp/2016/10/11/televangelist-christians-who-dont-vote-are-going-to-be-guilty-of-murder/ |work=The Washington Post |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> In an interview after a state dinner at the White House that Copeland attended, he said that Trump was \"led by the Spirit of God\", and that his most important legacy as president would be the appointments of conservative judges.<ref>{{cite news |last=Strang |first=Steve |date=2018 |title=Kenneth Copeland on Trump's State Dinner: 'It Was Like a Really Anointed Church Service' |url=https://www.charismamag.com/blogs/the-strang-report/38641-kenneth-copeland-on-trump-s-state-dinner-it-was-like-a-really-anointed-church-service |work=Charisma Magazine |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\nCopeland has amassed significant wealth during his career, and has referred to himself as a \"very wealthy man\".<ref name=\"washingtonpost-private-jet\" /> News media have cited different numbers of his net worth, from $300 million<ref name=\"christianpost-very-wealthy-man\">{{cite news |last=Blair |first=Leonardo |date=May 28, 2019 |title=\u2018I'm a very wealthy man,\u2019 says Kenneth Copeland; he couldn\u2019t help but buy jet from Tyler Perry |url=https://www.christianpost.com/news/prosperity-preacher-kenneth-copeland-says-ministry-brought-122-million-people-jesus-christ.html |work=The Christian Post |access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref> to $760 million.<ref>{{cite news |last=Swaak |first=Taylor |date=February 21, 2018 |title=Billy Graham Net Worth: Evangelist Was One of the Richest Pastors in America |url=https://www.newsweek.com/billy-graham-net-worth-814750 |work=Newsweek |access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n==Kenneth Copeland Ministries==\nKenneth Copeland and his wife Gloria Copeland run Kenneth Copeland Ministries (KCM), based in [[Tarrant County]], [[Texas]]. The ministry's motto is \"[[Jesus is Lord]]\" from {{bibleverse-lb||Romans|10:9|KJV}}.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://kcm.org/about-us-0 |title=Kenneth Copeland Ministries - About Us |publisher=Kenneth Copeland Ministries |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606124545/http://kcm.org/about-us-0 |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live |access-date=June 26, 2019}}</ref> He has claimed in an interview that the ministry has \"brought over 122 million people to the Lord Jesus Christ\".<ref name=\"christianpost-very-wealthy-man\" />\n\n===Television and other programming===\nFor decades, Copeland's ministry has held three-to-six-day conventions across the United States. The number of longer set conventions has waned in recent years, although KCM still holds an annual Believer's Convention in his hometown of [[Fort Worth, Texas|Fort Worth]], Texas, during the week of July 4. Kenneth and Gloria Copeland, along with ministry friends including some family members, also preach at other conventions and conferences throughout the world.{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}} These events stream live on Copeland's website, kcm.org, as well as being shown on Christian television stations such as [[God TV]] and the [[Daystar Television Network]]. Portions of recorded conferences are shown Sundays. The Monday through Friday television broadcasts feature a Copeland family member, either alone or with another minister, discussing subjects from the [[Bible]].\nMost of these episodes are available on BVOV.tv.  In July 2015, KCM launched the Believer's Voice of Victory Network on channel 265 of [[Dish TV]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dish.com/business/downloads/dish-general-channel-lineup.pdf |title=dish general channel linup |publisher=dish |accessdate=29 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Facilities===\nKenneth Copeland Ministries is located at 14355 Morris Dido Road, Fort Worth, TX 76192 on 33 acres (13 ha), a property valued at $554,160 in 2008 by Tarrant Appraisal District. The site includes the Eagle Mountain International Church, television and radio production facilities, warehouse and distribution facilities, residences for the Copeland family, and [[Kenneth Copeland Airport]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/religion/2008-07-27-copeland-evangelist-finances_N.htm |title=Analysis: Copeland's religious empire benefits his family |publisher=USA Today |date=July 27, 2008 |accessdate=29 January 2014}}</ref> Approximately 500 people are employed by KCM. John Copeland is the ministry's chief operating officer.\n\nKCM also owns a 1998 [[Cessna Citation II|Cessna 550 Citation Bravo]], which it received from a donor in October 2007 and is used for [[domestic flight]]s, and a 2005 [[Cessna Citation X|Cessna 750 Citation X]], which it uses for [[international flight]]s. It also is [[Maintenance, repair, and operations|restoring]] a 1962 [[Beechcraft Model 18|Beech H-18 Twin]], which the ministry plans to use for [[Disaster response|disaster relief efforts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://flightaware.com/resources/airport/4T2|title=Kenneth Copeland Airport FBOs (Fort Worth, TX) [4T2] \u2708 FlightAware|publisher=|accessdate=April 16, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104010640/http://www.believersstandunited.com/faq/ |url=http://www.believersstandunited.com/faq/ |archivedate=2013-11-04 |title=FAQ: Why does Kenneth Copeland Ministries own private aircraft? What types of aircraft are they? Why don't Kenneth and Gloria fly on commercial airlines? |accessdate=May 14, 2013 |work=Believers Stand United}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2007, Copeland was accused of using his ministry's Citation X for personal vacations and friends.<ref name=\"Jetrecords\">{{cite news |title=Jet flight records spur Copeland ministry questions |url=http://www.wfaa.com/sharedcontent/dws/wfaa/latestnews/stories/wfaa070228_mo_churchjet.87be631.html |publisher=[[WFAA-TV]] |date=February 28, 2007 |accessdate=October 17, 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070907124947/http://www.wfaa.com/sharedcontent/dws/wfaa/latestnews/stories/wfaa070228_mo_churchjet.87be631.html |archivedate=September 7, 2007}}</ref> The Copelands' financial records are not publicly available, and a list of the board of directors is not accessible as these details are protected but known confidentially by the [[Internal Revenue Service]].<ref name=\"Jetrecords\" /> Responding to media questions, Copeland pointed to what he asserted was an accounting firm's declaration that all jet travel complies with federal tax laws.<ref name=\"Jetrecords\" /> In December 2008, KCM's Citation Bravo was denied tax exemption after KCM refused to submit a standardized [[Texas Comptroller of Public Accounts|Texas Comptroller]] form that some county appraisal districts use to make determinations, which would have required making public the salary of all ministry staff.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.star-telegram.com/804/story/1078037.html |title=Televangelist's $3.6 million jet not tax-exempt, county says |publisher=[[Fort Worth Star Telegram]] |date=December 5, 2008 |accessdate=December 17, 2008}} {{Dead link|date=September 2010|bot=H3llBot}} - dead link</ref><ref name=\"CLG 2010-03-11\">{{cite news |title=A Victory for Church Freedom |date=March 11, 2010 |url=http://churchlawgroup.com/blog/uncategorized/a-victory-for-church-freedom/ |work=Church Law Group |accessdate=May 14, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104224501/http://churchlawgroup.com/blog/uncategorized/a-victory-for-church-freedom/ |archive-date=November 4, 2013 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> KCM subsequently [[lawsuit|filed suit]] with the [[Tarrant Appraisal District]] in January 2009 and its petition to have the aircraft's tax-exempt status restored was granted in March 2010.<ref name=\"CLG 2010-03-11\" /><ref>{{cite news |first=Darren |last=Barbee |title=Appraisal district sued over tax exemption for private jet |date=February 25, 2009 |work=Fort Worth Star-Telegram |pages=B07 Metro }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=TAD, Copeland ministry settle suit over tax-exempt jet |date=March 10, 2010 |work=Fort Worth Star-Telegram }}</ref>\n\nKenneth Copeland Ministries has taken advantage of a [[Federal Aviation Administration]] program that keeps flights private from tracking websites, and the ministry owns five such aircraft whose flights are kept private, including the [[Cessna Citation X|Cessna 750 Citation X]] noted above and a [[North American T-28 Trojan]].<ref name=\"usatoday30.usatoday.com\">{{cite web|url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/washington/2010-04-08-blocked-flights-inside_N.htm|title=Televangelist, college boosters, Hooters on stealth fliers list - USATODAY.com|publisher=|accessdate=April 16, 2017}}</ref> [[United States Senator]] [[Chuck Grassley]] has questioned some of the flights taken by these aircraft, including layovers in [[Maui]], [[Fiji]], and [[Honolulu]].<ref name=\"usatoday30.usatoday.com\"/> The ministries say that the stopovers were for preaching or for allowing pilot rest.<ref name=\"usatoday30.usatoday.com\"/>\n\n==Controversies==\n\n===2006 Angel Flight 44 Controversy===\nAccording to ''[[The Christian Post]]'', Kenneth Copeland Ministries was criticized in 2010 for failing to fly disaster relief missions to [[Haiti]] after allegedly promising an aviation relief assistance program called '''Angel Flight 44'''.<ref name=\"christianpost.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.christianpost.com/news/televangelist-kenneth-copeland-blasted-for-unfulfilled-vows-43561/|title=Televangelist Kenneth Copeland Blasted for 'Unfulfilled Promises'|publisher=|accessdate=April 16, 2017}}</ref> The Angel Flight 44 ministry was announced by Kenneth Copeland Ministries in 2006 and the ministry attempted to raise money to fund it.<ref name=\"christianpost.com\"/> Richard Vermillion, co-author of a book on Angel Flight 44 commissioned by Kenneth Copeland Ministries, said that Copeland promised to form the aviation ministry but now believes it was never created.<ref name=\"christianpost.com\"/> A spokesperson for Kenneth Copeland Ministries, Stephen Swisher, told ''The Christian Post'', \"This was not a specific promise with a time line attached\", and said that the money was spent on airplane repairs, and that the airplane was \"not in airworthy condition\" and had \"structural issues\".<ref name=\"christianpost.com\"/>\n\n===2008 Mike Huckabee controversy===\nIn late November 2007, [[Mike Huckabee]], a [[Republican Party (United States) presidential primaries, 2008|2008 Republican presidential primary]] candidate, made six appearances on Copeland's daily television program ''[[Believer's Voice of Victory]]'', discussing \"Integrity of Character\".{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}} Huckabee, an ordained Baptist minister, was appearing on Copeland's daily broadcast to promote his book, ''Character IS the Issue: How People with Integrity Can Revolutionize America''. Through the years, Copeland has invited many church pastors and evangelists to appear on his daily program to discuss their respective books.  Subsequently, in January 2008, the Huckabee campaign paid for use of Kenneth Copeland Ministries' facilities for a fundraiser.<ref name=\"2008-01-29 ADG\">{{cite news |url=http://www2.arkansasonline.com/news/2008/jan/29/plate-passed-huckabee-ministry-site |title=Plate passed for Huckabee at ministry site |publisher=[[Arkansas Democrat-Gazette]] |date=January 29, 2008 |accessdate=2008-12-17}}</ref> The fundraising at the church was criticized by the [[Trinity Foundation (Dallas)|Trinity Foundation]].<ref name=\"2008-01-29 ADG\" />\n\nAs a result of the Huckabee appearances, Kenneth Copeland Ministries was one of six approached by the [[United States Senate inquiry into the tax-exempt status of religious organizations]]. The Copelands responded with a [[financial statement]] and created a website, ''Believers Stand United'', to help explain their perspective.{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}}<ref>The investigation found no evidence of the Copelands making personal profit from financial donations. {{cite web |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/40960871/ns/politics-capitol_hill/t/televangelists-escape-penalty-senate-inquiry/#.URiVeTsiGYV |title=Televangelists escape penalty in Senate inquiry |publisher=www.nbcnews.com |date=2011-07-01 |accessdate=2013-02-11 |author=Zoll, Rachel}}</ref>\n\n===2013 vaccination controversy===\nIn 2013, a [[Measles outbreaks in the 21st century#United States|measles outbreak]] (20 confirmed cases as of August 26) in [[Tarrant County]] was attributed in the press to [[Vaccine controversies|anti-vaccination]] sentiments expressed by members of the Copeland Ministries. The church denied making any such statements and urged members to get vaccinations, even offering free immunizations through the church itself.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.christianpost.com/news/texas-measles-outbreak-linked-to-church-led-by-kenneth-copelands-daughter-infection-spread-to-congregation-staff-day-care-103057/|title=Texas Measles Outbreak Linked to Church Led by Kenneth Copeland's Daughter; Infection Spreads to Congregation, Staff, Day Care|website=www.christianpost.com|access-date=2017-12-22}}</ref> Pastor Terri Copeland Pearsons, who is Kenneth Copeland's daughter, offered free vaccination clinics and advised those who did not attend one of the clinics to [[quarantine]] themselves at home for two weeks. In a statement on the church website, Pearsons said she was not against immunizations, but also raised concerns about them.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2013/09/01/217746942/texas-megachurch-at-center-of-measles-outbreak|title=Texas Megachurch At Center Of Measles Outbreak|work=NPR.org|access-date=2017-12-22}}</ref>\n\n<blockquote>\"Some people think I am against immunizations, but that is not true\", the statement said. \"Vaccinations help cut the mortality rate enormously. I believe it is wrong to be against vaccinations. The [[MMR vaccine controversy|concerns]] we have had are primarily with very young children who have family history of [[autism]] and with bundling too many immunizations at one time. There is no indication of the [[Controversies in autism|autism connection]] with vaccinations in older children. Furthermore, the new [[MMR vaccine|MMR vaccination]] is without [[thimerosal]] (mercury), which has also been [[Thiomersal controversy|a concern]] to many.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Health/texas-church-epicenter-measles-outbreak/story?id=20071644|title=Texas Church at Epicenter of Measles Outbreak|last=News|first=A. B. C.|date=2013-08-27|website=ABC News|access-date=2017-12-22}}</ref></blockquote>\n\n===2015 ''Last Week Tonight'' criticism===\nKenneth Copeland and his wife, Gloria Copeland, were featured in a 2015 episode of ''[[Last Week Tonight with John Oliver]]'' that gained media attention.<ref>{{cite web|title=Last Week Tonight with John Oliver: Televangelists (HBO)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7y1xJAVZxXg|website=YouTube|accessdate=18 August 2015|format=16 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Ohlheiser|first1=Abby|title=Comedian John Oliver takes on the prosperity gospel by becoming a televangelist|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/acts-of-faith/wp/2015/08/17/comedian-john-oliver-takes-on-the-prosperity-gospel-by-becoming-a-televangelist/|website=The Washington Post|accessdate=18 August 2015|date=17 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Locker|first1=Melissa|title=John Oliver Becomes a Televangelist and Finally Starts His Own Church|url=http://time.com/3999933/john-oliver-televangelist-church-alst-week-tonight/|website=Time Magazine|accessdate=18 August 2015|date=17 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Stern|first1=Marlow|title=John Oliver Exposes Shady Televangelists Fleecing Americans For Millions|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2015/08/17/john-oliver-exposes-shady-televangelists-fleecing-americans-for-millions.html|website=The Daily Beast|accessdate=18 August 2015|date=17 August 2015}}</ref> Comedian [[John Oliver (comedian)|John Oliver]] criticized the Copelands for using tax laws to live in a $6.3 million mansion as the [[parsonage]] allowance for their home is not subject to income taxes,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Burnett|first1=John|title=Can A Television Network Be A Church? The IRS Says Yes|url=https://www.npr.org/2014/04/01/282496855/can-a-television-network-be-a-church-the-irs-says-yes|website=NPR|accessdate=18 August 2015|format=1 April 2014}}</ref> for using church donations to buy a $20 million jet that was used for trips to a ski resort and a private game ranch,<ref>{{cite web|title=Senate audit critical of TV preacher Kenneth Copeland|url=http://www.wfaa.com/story/news/local/investigates/2014/08/10/13660222/|website=WFAA|accessdate=18 August 2015|location=Dallas, Texas|date=7 January 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151019235219/http://www.wfaa.com/story/news/local/investigates/2014/08/10/13660222/|archive-date=October 19, 2015|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and for promotion of healing through faith and skepticism of medicine, which Oliver highlighted with a video of Gloria Copeland saying that doctors give patients \"poison that will make you sicker\" and that the church is an alternative to medical treatment: \"Which do you want to do? Do you want to do that\", Copeland asked of the doctor's \"poison\" treatment, \"or do you want to sit here on a Saturday morning, hear the word of God, and let faith come into your heart and be healed?\"\n\n===Private jets===\nIn 2009, Copeland's $3.6 million jet was denied tax-exempt status, opening up a possible investigation into the church's expenses; Copeland failed to disclose the salaries of his directors. In 2008 the ministry stated it owned five airplanes, one of which is valued at $17.5 million.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tax-Exempt Status For Televangelist's Jet Denied|publisher=Americans United|url=https://au.org/church-state/january-2009-church-state/au-bulletin/tax-exempt-status-for-televangelist%E2%80%99s-jet-denied|access-date=December 25, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180120124428/https://au.org/church-state/january-2009-church-state/au-bulletin/tax-exempt-status-for-televangelist%E2%80%99s-jet-denied|archive-date=January 20, 2018|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nCopeland's ministry bought a multi-million [[Gulfstream V]] jet airplane,<ref name=CP-KC>{{cite web|title=Kenneth Copeland Acquires New Gulfstream V Jet, Seeks $19.5M for Upgrades and Maintenance|publisher=Christian Post|url=https://www.christianpost.com/news/kenneth-copeland-acquires-new-gulfstream-v-jet-seeks-19-5m-for-upgrades-and-maintenance-214408/}}</ref> and Copeland thanked his followers and Jesus for buying it when it was delivered at the Fort Worth airstrip, wearing a [[Flight jacket|pilot jacket]] and sunglasses.<ref name=D5286955>{{cite web|title='Jesus bought this': Delighted televangelist Kenneth Copeland giggles with glee as he unveils new $3million private jet paid for by donations from his followers|publisher=Daily Mail|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-5286955/Prosperity-Preacher-Kenneth-Copeland-giggles-GV.html}}</ref> The jet was bought from filmmaker and businessman [[Tyler Perry]].<ref name=D5286955/><ref name=CP-KC/> Now,{{when?|reason=This should be a \"As of\" fact. Saying \"Now\" introduces ambiguity.|date=April 2020}} the church is asking another $17<ref name=D5286955/> or $19.5 million for the building of a hangar, upgrading of the runway, and maintenance.<ref name=CP-KC/>\n\nIn 2015, Kenneth Copeland, in a broadcast alongside fellow televangelist [[Jesse Duplantis]], defended the use of private jets as a necessary part of their ministry, comparing flying in a commercial plane to getting \"in long tube with a bunch of demons\".<ref name=\"washingtonpost-private-jet\">{{cite news |last=Brice-Saddler |first=Michael |date=June 4, 2019 |title=A wealthy televangelist explains his fleet of private jets: \u2018It\u2019s a biblical thing\u2019 |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/religion/2019/06/04/wealthy-televangelist-explains-his-fleet-private-jets-its-biblical-thing/ |work=The Washingot Post |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Bote |first=Joshua |date=December 15, 2019 |title='None of your business': A televangelist defending his private jets goes viral |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2019/06/04/televangelist-kenneth-copeland-defends-private-jets-inside-edition/1337549001/ |work=USA Today |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Calicchio |first=Dom  |title=Televangelist Kenneth Copeland defends use of private jets in TV interview, denies calling people 'demons' |url=https://www.foxnews.com/us/televangelist-kenneth-copeland-defends-use-of-private-jets-in-tv-interview-denies-calling-people-demons |work=Fox News |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Brito |first=Christopher |date=June 4, 2019 |title=Televangelist defends lavish lifestyle and use of private jets, calls it a \"biblical thing\" |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/kenneth-copeland-televangelist-defends-lavish-lifestyle-and-use-of-private-jets-2019-06-04/ |work=CBS News |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\nCopeland's and other televangelists' use of private jets and other lavish houses and vehicles has been criticized.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kenneth Copeland Ministries Ups Being a Scumonaut by Bragging About New G5 Jet|publisher=Pulpit&Pen|url=http://pulpitandpen.org/2018/01/16/kenneth-copeland-ministries-ups-being-a-scumonaut-by-bragging-about-new-g5-jet/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Kenneth Copeland Loves His New $36 Million Jet|publisher=Patheos|url=http://www.patheos.com/blogs/warrenthrockmorton/2018/01/18/kenneth-copeland-36-million-jet/|access-date=December 25, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180324233307/http://www.patheos.com/blogs/warrenthrockmorton/2018/01/18/kenneth-copeland-36-million-jet/|archive-date=March 24, 2018|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Televagelist thanks Jesus for $36M private jet he uses to avoid demons|publisher=The Maven|url=https://www.themaven.net/beingliberal/room/televagelist-thanks-jesus-for-36m-private-jet-he-uses-to-avoid-demons-sldtGWfs-kq7Qisw941q5w}}</ref>\n\n=== COVID-19===\nDuring the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|pandemic of COVID-19]], Copeland repeatedly got attention for his comments and actions in response to the outbreak. On March 11, 2020, Copeland claimed to heal viewers of his TV show of the disease, asking them to touch the television set as he prayed for them.<ref>{{cite news |last=Lemon |first=Jason |date=March 12, 2020 |title=Conservative Pastor Claims He 'Healed' Viewers of Coronavirus Through Their TV Screens |url=https://www.newsweek.com/conservative-pastor-claims-he-healed-viewers-coronavirus-through-their-tv-screens-1492044 |work=Newsweek |access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\nAs many lost their jobs in the [[Coronavirus recession|economic crisis]] that the outbreak caused, Copeland told followers to continue paying tithes even if they lost their jobs.<ref>{{cite news |last=Gagn\u00e9 |first=Andr\u00e9 |date=March 29, 2020 |title=Coronavirus: Trump and religious right rely on faith, not science |url=https://theconversation.com/coronavirus-trump-and-religious-right-rely-on-faith-not-science-134508 |work=The Conversation |access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nIn a broadcast, Copeland called it a weak strain of the flu, and that fear of it was sin and putting faith in the devil. Copeland said that he did not agree with pastors that cancelled their services due to the coronavirus, saying \"I want you in my church. If we have to pass out thermometers. If we find one with a fever, let\u2019s get him healed right there. What if you do get it? Big deal!\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Blair |first=Leonardo |date=March 13, 2020 |title=Kenneth Copeland calls coronavirus \u2018very weak strain of flu,\u2019 says healthy people shouldn\u2019t fear |url=https://www.christianpost.com/news/kenneth-copeland-calls-coronavirus-very-weak-strain-of-flu-healthy-people-shouldnt-fear.html |work=The Christian Post |access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Wilson |first=Jason |date=April 4, 202 |title=The rightwing Christian preachers in deep denial over Covid-19's danger |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/apr/04/america-rightwing-christian-preachers-virus-hoax |work=The Guardian |access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nKenneth Copeland has repeatedly said during the pandemic that it has ended or will soon end.<ref name=\"independent-corona\">{{cite news |last=Woodward |first=Alex |date=April 6, 2020 |title=Coronavirus: Televangelist Kenneth Copeland \u2018blows wind of God\u2019 at Covid-19 to \u2018destroy\u2019 pandemic  |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/kenneth-copeland-blow-coronavirus-pray-sermon-trump-televangelist-a9448561.html |work=The Independent |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> He said at one point that God told him that it would soon be over as Christians' prayers have overwhelmed it, and that the pandemic was brought to America by \"displays of hate\" towards president Donald Trump by critics, which had intereferred with \"divine protection\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Sommer |first=Will |date=March 23, 2020 |title=Trump\u2019s Megachurch Allies Promise COVID-19 Snake Oil and \u2018Miracles\u2019 |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/trump-friendly-megachurch-pastors-push-bogus-coronavirus-cures |work=The Daily Beast |access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> On March 29, 2020, in a televised sermon, Copeland \"executed judgement\" on COVID-19. He claimed that it was \"finished\" and \"over\" and that the US was now \"healed and well again\".<ref name=\"independent-corona\" /> In another sermon shortly thereafter, Copeland claimed to destroy the virus with the \"wind of God\", saying \"I blow the wind of God on you. You are destroyed forever, and you\u2019ll never be back. Thank you, God. Let it happen. Cause it to happen.\"<ref name=\"independent-corona\" />\n\n==Selected KCM publications and recordings==\n*''Load Up Pocket Devotional: 31 Devotions to Revolutionize Your Future'' (Harrison House, July 2004) {{ISBN|1-57794-399-6}} {{ISBN|978-1577943990}}\n*''You Are Healed'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, July 1999) {{ISBN|0-88114-733-8}} {{ISBN|978-0881147339}}\n*''A Ceremony of Marriage'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, December 1996) {{ISBN|0-938458-15-9}} {{ISBN|978-0938458159}}\n*''Prayer: Your Foundation for Success'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, June 1999) {{ISBN|1-57794-155-1}} {{ISBN|978-1577941552}}\n*''Kenneth Copeland Reference Bible \u2013 Leather Bound'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, December 1996) {{ISBN|0-88114-296-4}} {{ISBN|978-0881142969}}\n*''Becoming Subject to the Authority of Jesus'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, 2001) {{ISBN|0-88114-972-1}} {{ISBN|978-0881149722}}\n*''How to Discipline Your Flesh'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, June 1999) {{ISBN|1-57562-116-9}} {{ISBN|978-1575621166}}\n*''From Faith to Faith: A Daily Guide to Victory'' (Harrison House, May 2000) {{ISBN|1-57794-225-6}} {{ISBN|978-1577942252}}\n*''Pursuit of His Presence: Daily Devotional'' (Harrison House, September 1998) {{ISBN|1-57794-137-3}} {{ISBN|978-1577941378}}\n*''The Wake-up Call'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, 2002) {{ISBN|1-57562-792-2}} {{ISBN|978-1575627922}}\n*''Classic Redemption'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, 2001) {{ISBN|0-938458-58-2}} {{ISBN|978-0938458586}}\n*''The Laws of Prosperity'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, December 1995) {{ISBN|0-88114-952-7}} {{ISBN|978-0881149524}}\n*''Prosperity: The Choice Is Yours'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, June 1992) {{ISBN|0-88114-728-1}} {{ISBN|978-0881147285}}\n*''Healing Promises'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, August 1994) {{ISBN|0-88114-949-7}} {{ISBN|978-0881149494}}\n*''Over the Edge: Youth Devotional'' (Harrison House, September 1998) {{ISBN|1-57794-138-1}} {{ISBN|978-1577941385}}\n*''Big Band Gospel'' (KCP Records, 2003)\n*''Racism in the Church. Kill the Root, Destroy the Tree'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, 2016) {{ISBN|978-1604633252}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Trinity Foundation (Dallas)]]\n*[[Neo-charismatic churches]]\n*[[Charismatic movement]]\n*[[Word of Faith]]\n*[[Prosperity Gospel]]\n*[[Tony Palmer (bishop)]]\n*[[Ulf Ekman]]\n\n==Notes and references==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.kcm.org/ Kenneth Copeland Ministries official site]\n*[http://emic.org Eagle Mountain International Church]\n*[http://bvov.tv Believer's Voice of Victory streaming site]\n*[http://believersstandunited.com Believers Stand United for Religious Freedom in America]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Copeland, Kenneth}}\n[[Category:1936 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American Pentecostal pastors]]\n[[Category:American television evangelists]]\n[[Category:American Charismatics]]\n[[Category:Imperial Records artists]]\n[[Category:Oral Roberts University people]]\n[[Category:People from Fort Worth, Texas]]\n[[Category:People from Lubbock, Texas]]\n[[Category:Pentecostal writers]]\n[[Category:Oral Roberts University alumni]]\n[[Category:American faith healers]]\n[[Category:Prosperity theologians]]\n[[Category:Pentecostals from Texas]]\n[[Category:Texas Republicans]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American Televangelist}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Kenneth Copeland\n| residence          = [[Fort Worth, Texas]], U.S.\n| other_names        = \n| image              = File:Kenneth Copeland 2011.jpg\n| caption            = Kenneth Copeland in 2011\n| birth_name         = Kenneth Max Copeland\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1936|12|06}}\n| birth_place        = [[Lubbock, Texas]], U.S.\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| known              = \n| occupation         = {{hlist|Author|speaker|pastor|televangelist}}\n| net_worth          = {{nowrap| [[US$]]300 million<ref name=\"Beliefnet profile\">{{cite web|title= Richest Pastor in America|url=https://www.ibtimes.com/kenneth-copeland-net-worth-evangelist-richest-pastor-world-2951331p=2|website=IBTimes|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}</ref> }} (April 2020)\n| salary             = \n| term               = \n| nationality        = [[United States|American]]\n| predecessor        = \n| years active       = 1967-present\n| successor          = \n| influences         = [[Kenneth Hagan|Kenneth Hagan]]\n| boards             = \n| movement           = [[Word of Faith]]\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Ivy Bodiford|1955|1958}}<br /> {{marriage|Cynthia Davis |1958|1961}}<br /> {{marriage|Gloria Neece|1963}}\n| partner            = \n| children           = 3\n| parents            = \n| relations          = \n| website            = {{URL|http://www.kcm.org}}\n| footnotes          = \n| party              = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n| height             = \n| weight             = \n}}\n\n'''Kenneth Max Copeland''' (born December 6, 1936) is an American [[Televangelism|televangelist]], and author associated with the [[Charismatic Movement]]. He runs the [[#Kenneth Copeland Ministries|Kenneth Copeland Ministries]] based in [[Tarrant County]], [[Texas]].\n\nHe has been identified as preaching the [[Prosperity theology|prosperity gospel]]. As part of his evangelism, he calls for donations to his church, with the suggestion that parishioners will get a \"hundredfold\" return on their investment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vox.com/identities/2017/9/1/15951874/prosperity-gospel-explained-why-joel-osteen-believes-prayer-can-make-you-rich-trump|title=The prosperity gospel, explained: Why Joel Osteen believes that prayer can make you rich|last=Burton|first=Tara Isabella|date=2017-09-01|website=Vox|language=en|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref> He has stirred controversy over his use of donations to finance mansions, private jets, an [[Kenneth Copeland Airport|airport]] and other lavish purchases.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Goodstein|first=Laurie|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/16/us/16gospel.html|title=Believers Invest in the Gospel of Getting Rich|date=2009-08-15|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-03-12|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/religion/2019/06/04/wealthy-televangelist-explains-his-fleet-private-jets-its-biblical-thing/|title=A wealthy televangelist explains his fleet of private jets: \u2018It\u2019s a biblical thing\u2019|date=2019|work=The Washington Post|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nDuring [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|the pandemic of COVID-19]] in 2020, Copeland gained national attention for his comments and actions in response to the outbreak. He repeatedly claimed that the pandemic had ended or would soon end, that he could heal followers of it, and that his followers should continue paying tithes if they lost their jobs in the economic crisis that the pandemic caused.<ref name=\"independent-corona\" /> He later made claims to have destroyed the virus and to have ended the still-ongoing pandemic.<ref name=\"independent-corona\" />\n\n==Personal life==\nKenneth Max Copeland was born in [[Lubbock, Texas|Lubbock]], [[Texas]], to Aubrey Wayne and Vinita Pearl (n\u00e9e Owens) Copeland.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ancestrylibrary.com/interactive/8781/TXBTH_1936_000208e?pid=2675215|title=Texas Birth Index, 1903-1997|website=www.ancestrylibrary.com|access-date=2018-04-18}}</ref> He was raised in [[West Texas]] near a [[United States Army Air Forces]] [[List of United States Army airfields|airfield]], which inspired him to become a [[aviator|pilot.]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.biographyministries.com/kenneth-copeland.html |title=Kenneth Copeland |publisher=biographyministries.com |year=2008 |accessdate=December 17, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081016102647/http://www.biographyministries.com/kenneth-copeland.html |archivedate=October 16, 2008 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://newsok.com/article/3275378|title=AP IMPACT: Relatives of televangelist prosper|last=Gorski|first=Eric|date=2008-07-27|work=NewsOK.com|access-date=2018-04-18}}</ref>\n\nCopeland married Ivy Bodiford in October 1955 and became the parents of Terri Copeland Pearsons;<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://erecord.co.lubbock.tx.us/recorder/eagleweb/viewDoc.jsp?node=DOCCM-120611|title=Lubbock County Marriage Certificate|website=erecord.co.lubbock.tx.us|access-date=2018-04-18}}</ref> they divorced in 1958. Kenneth married Gloria (n\u00e9e Neece) on April 13, 1963.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kennethcopelandblog.com/2010/08/01/kenneth-and-gloria-copeland-the-untold-story/|title=Kenneth and Gloria Copeland, The Untold Story|publisher=KennethCopelandBlog.com |date=August 1, 2010 |accessdate=March 7, 2016}}</ref> They are the parents of John Copeland and Kellie Copeland. Gloria co-hosts the ministry's flagship broadcast, \"The Believer's Voice of Victory,\" alongside her husband. Kellie preaches throughout the United States, as does Terri, who also preaches at Eagle Mountain International Church, which is pastored by her husband, George Pearsons.\n\nPrior to becoming a [[born again Christian]] in November 1962, Copeland was a recording artist on the [[Imperial Records]] label, having one ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' Top 40 hit (\"Pledge of Love\", which charted in the Top 40 on April 20, 1957, stayed on the charts for 15 weeks, and peaked at #17).<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books/about/The_Billboard_Book_of_Top_40_Hits.html?id=drgq4g0rmVsC|title=The Billboard Book of Top 40 Hits|last=Whitburn|first=Joel|date=2000|publisher=Billboard Books|year=|isbn=9780823076901|location=|pages=151}}</ref>\n\nFollowing his conversion, Copeland devoted his life to the gospel and ministry work.<ref>Kenneth Copeland, \"The Word in My life...\", Kenneth Copeland Ministries Catalog (Fort Worth: Kenneth Copeland Ministries, n.d.), 3.</ref> In the fall of 1967, he enrolled in [[Oral Roberts University]], where he soon became pilot and chauffeur to [[Oral Roberts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oru.edu/alumni/excell/spring06/feature1.html|title=ORU alumni|accessdate=April 16, 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090210080448/http://www.oru.edu/alumni/excell/spring06/feature1.html|archivedate=February 10, 2009|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nCopeland sat on the evangelical executive advisory board that Donald Trump assembled during his campaign for the presidency.<ref>{{cite news |last=Sharman |first=Jon |date=February 6, 2018 |title=Trump adviser urges followers to 'inoculate yourself with the word of God' against flu |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-politics/gloria-copeland-trump-adviser-flu-shot-jesus-god-christian-evangelical-healing-miracle-a8197801.html |work=The Independent |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> Appointment to the board did not require endorsement of his bid for presidency, <ref>{{cite news |last=Wing |first=Nick |date=June 21, 2016 |title=Donald Trump\u2019s New Evangelical Adviser Was Sure God Had Chosen Ted Cruz To Be President |url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/donald-trump-kenneth-copeland_n_5769880de4b065534f47fb24 |work=HuffPost |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> and Copeland clarified that he did not endorse Trump at the time.<ref>{{cite news |last=Shellnutt |first=Kate |last2=Eekhoff Zylstra |first2=Sarah  |date=June 22, 2016 |title=Who\u2019s Who of Trump\u2019s \u2018Tremendous\u2019 Faith Advisers |url=http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/2016/june-web-only/whos-who-of-trumps-tremendous-faith-advisors.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160707085329/http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/2016/june-web-only/whos-who-of-trumps-tremendous-faith-advisors.html |archivedate=July 7, 2016 |work=Christianity Today |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> Before the 2016 election, Copeland said that Christians that did not vote for Trump would be guilty of murder, referring to the abortion policy of Hillary Clinton.<ref>{{cite news |last=Pulliam Bailey  |first=Sarah |date=October 11, 2016 |title=Televangelist: Christians who don\u2019t vote are \u2018going to be guilty of murder\u2019 |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/acts-of-faith/wp/2016/10/11/televangelist-christians-who-dont-vote-are-going-to-be-guilty-of-murder/ |work=The Washington Post |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> In an interview after a state dinner at the White House that Copeland attended, he said that Trump was \"led by the Spirit of God\", and that his most important legacy as president would be the appointments of conservative judges.<ref>{{cite news |last=Strang |first=Steve |date=2018 |title=Kenneth Copeland on Trump's State Dinner: 'It Was Like a Really Anointed Church Service' |url=https://www.charismamag.com/blogs/the-strang-report/38641-kenneth-copeland-on-trump-s-state-dinner-it-was-like-a-really-anointed-church-service |work=Charisma Magazine |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\nCopeland has amassed significant wealth during his career, and has referred to himself as a \"very wealthy man\".<ref name=\"washingtonpost-private-jet\" /> News media have cited different numbers of his net worth, from $300 million<ref name=\"christianpost-very-wealthy-man\">{{cite news |last=Blair |first=Leonardo |date=May 28, 2019 |title=\u2018I'm a very wealthy man,\u2019 says Kenneth Copeland; he couldn\u2019t help but buy jet from Tyler Perry |url=https://www.christianpost.com/news/prosperity-preacher-kenneth-copeland-says-ministry-brought-122-million-people-jesus-christ.html |work=The Christian Post |access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref> to $760 million.<ref>{{cite news |last=Swaak |first=Taylor |date=February 21, 2018 |title=Billy Graham Net Worth: Evangelist Was One of the Richest Pastors in America |url=https://www.newsweek.com/billy-graham-net-worth-814750 |work=Newsweek |access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n==Kenneth Copeland Ministries==\nKenneth Copeland and his wife Gloria Copeland run Kenneth Copeland Ministries (KCM), based in [[Tarrant County]], [[Texas]]. The ministry's motto is \"[[Jesus is Lord]]\" from {{bibleverse-lb||Romans|10:9|KJV}}.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://kcm.org/about-us-0 |title=Kenneth Copeland Ministries - About Us |publisher=Kenneth Copeland Ministries |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606124545/http://kcm.org/about-us-0 |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live |access-date=June 26, 2019}}</ref> He has claimed in an interview that the ministry has \"brought over 122 million people to the Lord Jesus Christ\".<ref name=\"christianpost-very-wealthy-man\" />\n\n===Television and other programming===\nFor decades, Copeland's ministry has held three-to-six-day conventions across the United States. The number of longer set conventions has waned in recent years, although KCM still holds an annual Believer's Convention in his hometown of [[Fort Worth, Texas|Fort Worth]], Texas, during the week of July 4. Kenneth and Gloria Copeland, along with ministry friends including some family members, also preach at other conventions and conferences throughout the world.{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}} These events stream live on Copeland's website, kcm.org, as well as being shown on Christian television stations such as [[God TV]] and the [[Daystar Television Network]]. Portions of recorded conferences are shown Sundays. The Monday through Friday television broadcasts feature a Copeland family member, either alone or with another minister, discussing subjects from the [[Bible]].\nMost of these episodes are available on BVOV.tv.  In July 2015, KCM launched the Believer's Voice of Victory Network on channel 265 of [[Dish TV]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dish.com/business/downloads/dish-general-channel-lineup.pdf |title=dish general channel linup |publisher=dish |accessdate=29 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Facilities===\nKenneth Copeland Ministries is located at 14355 Morris Dido Road, Fort Worth, TX 76192 on 33 acres (13 ha), a property valued at $554,160 in 2008 by Tarrant Appraisal District. The site includes the Eagle Mountain International Church, television and radio production facilities, warehouse and distribution facilities, residences for the Copeland family, and [[Kenneth Copeland Airport]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/religion/2008-07-27-copeland-evangelist-finances_N.htm |title=Analysis: Copeland's religious empire benefits his family |publisher=USA Today |date=July 27, 2008 |accessdate=29 January 2014}}</ref> Approximately 500 people are employed by KCM. John Copeland is the ministry's chief operating officer.\n\nKCM also owns a 1998 [[Cessna Citation II|Cessna 550 Citation Bravo]], which it received from a donor in October 2007 and is used for [[domestic flight]]s, and a 2005 [[Cessna Citation X|Cessna 750 Citation X]], which it uses for [[international flight]]s. It also is [[Maintenance, repair, and operations|restoring]] a 1962 [[Beechcraft Model 18|Beech H-18 Twin]], which the ministry plans to use for [[Disaster response|disaster relief efforts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://flightaware.com/resources/airport/4T2|title=Kenneth Copeland Airport FBOs (Fort Worth, TX) [4T2] \u2708 FlightAware|publisher=|accessdate=April 16, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104010640/http://www.believersstandunited.com/faq/ |url=http://www.believersstandunited.com/faq/ |archivedate=2013-11-04 |title=FAQ: Why does Kenneth Copeland Ministries own private aircraft? What types of aircraft are they? Why don't Kenneth and Gloria fly on commercial airlines? |accessdate=May 14, 2013 |work=Believers Stand United}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2007, Copeland was accused of using his ministry's Citation X for personal vacations and friends.<ref name=\"Jetrecords\">{{cite news |title=Jet flight records spur Copeland ministry questions |url=http://www.wfaa.com/sharedcontent/dws/wfaa/latestnews/stories/wfaa070228_mo_churchjet.87be631.html |publisher=[[WFAA-TV]] |date=February 28, 2007 |accessdate=October 17, 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070907124947/http://www.wfaa.com/sharedcontent/dws/wfaa/latestnews/stories/wfaa070228_mo_churchjet.87be631.html |archivedate=September 7, 2007}}</ref> The Copelands' financial records are not publicly available, and a list of the board of directors is not accessible as these details are protected but known confidentially by the [[Internal Revenue Service]].<ref name=\"Jetrecords\" /> Responding to media questions, Copeland pointed to what he asserted was an accounting firm's declaration that all jet travel complies with federal tax laws.<ref name=\"Jetrecords\" /> In December 2008, KCM's Citation Bravo was denied tax exemption after KCM refused to submit a standardized [[Texas Comptroller of Public Accounts|Texas Comptroller]] form that some county appraisal districts use to make determinations, which would have required making public the salary of all ministry staff.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.star-telegram.com/804/story/1078037.html |title=Televangelist's $3.6 million jet not tax-exempt, county says |publisher=[[Fort Worth Star Telegram]] |date=December 5, 2008 |accessdate=December 17, 2008}} {{Dead link|date=September 2010|bot=H3llBot}} - dead link</ref><ref name=\"CLG 2010-03-11\">{{cite news |title=A Victory for Church Freedom |date=March 11, 2010 |url=http://churchlawgroup.com/blog/uncategorized/a-victory-for-church-freedom/ |work=Church Law Group |accessdate=May 14, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104224501/http://churchlawgroup.com/blog/uncategorized/a-victory-for-church-freedom/ |archive-date=November 4, 2013 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> KCM subsequently [[lawsuit|filed suit]] with the [[Tarrant Appraisal District]] in January 2009 and its petition to have the aircraft's tax-exempt status restored was granted in March 2010.<ref name=\"CLG 2010-03-11\" /><ref>{{cite news |first=Darren |last=Barbee |title=Appraisal district sued over tax exemption for private jet |date=February 25, 2009 |work=Fort Worth Star-Telegram |pages=B07 Metro }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=TAD, Copeland ministry settle suit over tax-exempt jet |date=March 10, 2010 |work=Fort Worth Star-Telegram }}</ref>\n\nKenneth Copeland Ministries has taken advantage of a [[Federal Aviation Administration]] program that keeps flights private from tracking websites, and the ministry owns five such aircraft whose flights are kept private, including the [[Cessna Citation X|Cessna 750 Citation X]] noted above and a [[North American T-28 Trojan]].<ref name=\"usatoday30.usatoday.com\">{{cite web|url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/washington/2010-04-08-blocked-flights-inside_N.htm|title=Televangelist, college boosters, Hooters on stealth fliers list - USATODAY.com|publisher=|accessdate=April 16, 2017}}</ref> [[United States Senator]] [[Chuck Grassley]] has questioned some of the flights taken by these aircraft, including layovers in [[Maui]], [[Fiji]], and [[Honolulu]].<ref name=\"usatoday30.usatoday.com\"/> The ministries say that the stopovers were for preaching or for allowing pilot rest.<ref name=\"usatoday30.usatoday.com\"/>\n\n==Controversies==\n\n===2006 Angel Flight 44 Controversy===\nAccording to ''[[The Christian Post]]'', Kenneth Copeland Ministries was criticized in 2010 for failing to fly disaster relief missions to [[Haiti]] after allegedly promising an aviation relief assistance program called '''Angel Flight 44'''.<ref name=\"christianpost.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.christianpost.com/news/televangelist-kenneth-copeland-blasted-for-unfulfilled-vows-43561/|title=Televangelist Kenneth Copeland Blasted for 'Unfulfilled Promises'|publisher=|accessdate=April 16, 2017}}</ref> The Angel Flight 44 ministry was announced by Kenneth Copeland Ministries in 2006 and the ministry attempted to raise money to fund it.<ref name=\"christianpost.com\"/> Richard Vermillion, co-author of a book on Angel Flight 44 commissioned by Kenneth Copeland Ministries, said that Copeland promised to form the aviation ministry but now believes it was never created.<ref name=\"christianpost.com\"/> A spokesperson for Kenneth Copeland Ministries, Stephen Swisher, told ''The Christian Post'', \"This was not a specific promise with a time line attached\", and said that the money was spent on airplane repairs, and that the airplane was \"not in airworthy condition\" and had \"structural issues\".<ref name=\"christianpost.com\"/>\n\n===2008 Mike Huckabee controversy===\nIn late November 2007, [[Mike Huckabee]], a [[Republican Party (United States) presidential primaries, 2008|2008 Republican presidential primary]] candidate, made six appearances on Copeland's daily television program ''[[Believer's Voice of Victory]]'', discussing \"Integrity of Character\".{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}} Huckabee, an ordained Baptist minister, was appearing on Copeland's daily broadcast to promote his book, ''Character IS the Issue: How People with Integrity Can Revolutionize America''. Through the years, Copeland has invited many church pastors and evangelists to appear on his daily program to discuss their respective books.  Subsequently, in January 2008, the Huckabee campaign paid for use of Kenneth Copeland Ministries' facilities for a fundraiser.<ref name=\"2008-01-29 ADG\">{{cite news |url=http://www2.arkansasonline.com/news/2008/jan/29/plate-passed-huckabee-ministry-site |title=Plate passed for Huckabee at ministry site |publisher=[[Arkansas Democrat-Gazette]] |date=January 29, 2008 |accessdate=2008-12-17}}</ref> The fundraising at the church was criticized by the [[Trinity Foundation (Dallas)|Trinity Foundation]].<ref name=\"2008-01-29 ADG\" />\n\nAs a result of the Huckabee appearances, Kenneth Copeland Ministries was one of six approached by the [[United States Senate inquiry into the tax-exempt status of religious organizations]]. The Copelands responded with a [[financial statement]] and created a website, ''Believers Stand United'', to help explain their perspective.{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}}<ref>The investigation found no evidence of the Copelands making personal profit from financial donations. {{cite web |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/40960871/ns/politics-capitol_hill/t/televangelists-escape-penalty-senate-inquiry/#.URiVeTsiGYV |title=Televangelists escape penalty in Senate inquiry |publisher=www.nbcnews.com |date=2011-07-01 |accessdate=2013-02-11 |author=Zoll, Rachel}}</ref>\n\n===2013 vaccination controversy===\nIn 2013, a [[Measles outbreaks in the 21st century#United States|measles outbreak]] (20 confirmed cases as of August 26) in [[Tarrant County]] was attributed in the press to [[Vaccine controversies|anti-vaccination]] sentiments expressed by members of the Copeland Ministries. The church denied making any such statements and urged members to get vaccinations, even offering free immunizations through the church itself.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.christianpost.com/news/texas-measles-outbreak-linked-to-church-led-by-kenneth-copelands-daughter-infection-spread-to-congregation-staff-day-care-103057/|title=Texas Measles Outbreak Linked to Church Led by Kenneth Copeland's Daughter; Infection Spreads to Congregation, Staff, Day Care|website=www.christianpost.com|access-date=2017-12-22}}</ref> Pastor Terri Copeland Pearsons, who is Kenneth Copeland's daughter, offered free vaccination clinics and advised those who did not attend one of the clinics to [[quarantine]] themselves at home for two weeks. In a statement on the church website, Pearsons said she was not against immunizations, but also raised concerns about them.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2013/09/01/217746942/texas-megachurch-at-center-of-measles-outbreak|title=Texas Megachurch At Center Of Measles Outbreak|work=NPR.org|access-date=2017-12-22}}</ref>\n\n<blockquote>\"Some people think I am against immunizations, but that is not true\", the statement said. \"Vaccinations help cut the mortality rate enormously. I believe it is wrong to be against vaccinations. The [[MMR vaccine controversy|concerns]] we have had are primarily with very young children who have family history of [[autism]] and with bundling too many immunizations at one time. There is no indication of the [[Controversies in autism|autism connection]] with vaccinations in older children. Furthermore, the new [[MMR vaccine|MMR vaccination]] is without [[thimerosal]] (mercury), which has also been [[Thiomersal controversy|a concern]] to many.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Health/texas-church-epicenter-measles-outbreak/story?id=20071644|title=Texas Church at Epicenter of Measles Outbreak|last=News|first=A. B. C.|date=2013-08-27|website=ABC News|access-date=2017-12-22}}</ref></blockquote>\n\n===2015 ''Last Week Tonight'' criticism===\nKenneth Copeland and his wife, Gloria Copeland, were featured in a 2015 episode of ''[[Last Week Tonight with John Oliver]]'' that gained media attention.<ref>{{cite web|title=Last Week Tonight with John Oliver: Televangelists (HBO)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7y1xJAVZxXg|website=YouTube|accessdate=18 August 2015|format=16 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Ohlheiser|first1=Abby|title=Comedian John Oliver takes on the prosperity gospel by becoming a televangelist|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/acts-of-faith/wp/2015/08/17/comedian-john-oliver-takes-on-the-prosperity-gospel-by-becoming-a-televangelist/|website=The Washington Post|accessdate=18 August 2015|date=17 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Locker|first1=Melissa|title=John Oliver Becomes a Televangelist and Finally Starts His Own Church|url=http://time.com/3999933/john-oliver-televangelist-church-alst-week-tonight/|website=Time Magazine|accessdate=18 August 2015|date=17 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Stern|first1=Marlow|title=John Oliver Exposes Shady Televangelists Fleecing Americans For Millions|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2015/08/17/john-oliver-exposes-shady-televangelists-fleecing-americans-for-millions.html|website=The Daily Beast|accessdate=18 August 2015|date=17 August 2015}}</ref> Comedian [[John Oliver (comedian)|John Oliver]] criticized the Copelands for using tax laws to live in a $6.3 million mansion as the [[parsonage]] allowance for their home is not subject to income taxes,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Burnett|first1=John|title=Can A Television Network Be A Church? The IRS Says Yes|url=https://www.npr.org/2014/04/01/282496855/can-a-television-network-be-a-church-the-irs-says-yes|website=NPR|accessdate=18 August 2015|format=1 April 2014}}</ref> for using church donations to buy a $20 million jet that was used for trips to a ski resort and a private game ranch,<ref>{{cite web|title=Senate audit critical of TV preacher Kenneth Copeland|url=http://www.wfaa.com/story/news/local/investigates/2014/08/10/13660222/|website=WFAA|accessdate=18 August 2015|location=Dallas, Texas|date=7 January 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151019235219/http://www.wfaa.com/story/news/local/investigates/2014/08/10/13660222/|archive-date=October 19, 2015|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and for promotion of healing through faith and skepticism of medicine, which Oliver highlighted with a video of Gloria Copeland saying that doctors give patients \"poison that will make you sicker\" and that the church is an alternative to medical treatment: \"Which do you want to do? Do you want to do that\", Copeland asked of the doctor's \"poison\" treatment, \"or do you want to sit here on a Saturday morning, hear the word of God, and let faith come into your heart and be healed?\"\n\n===Private jets===\nIn 2009, Copeland's $3.6 million jet was denied tax-exempt status, opening up a possible investigation into the church's expenses; Copeland failed to disclose the salaries of his directors. In 2008 the ministry stated it owned five airplanes, one of which is valued at $17.5 million.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tax-Exempt Status For Televangelist's Jet Denied|publisher=Americans United|url=https://au.org/church-state/january-2009-church-state/au-bulletin/tax-exempt-status-for-televangelist%E2%80%99s-jet-denied|access-date=December 25, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180120124428/https://au.org/church-state/january-2009-church-state/au-bulletin/tax-exempt-status-for-televangelist%E2%80%99s-jet-denied|archive-date=January 20, 2018|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nCopeland's ministry bought a multi-million [[Gulfstream V]] jet airplane,<ref name=CP-KC>{{cite web|title=Kenneth Copeland Acquires New Gulfstream V Jet, Seeks $19.5M for Upgrades and Maintenance|publisher=Christian Post|url=https://www.christianpost.com/news/kenneth-copeland-acquires-new-gulfstream-v-jet-seeks-19-5m-for-upgrades-and-maintenance-214408/}}</ref> and Copeland thanked his followers and Jesus for buying it when it was delivered at the Fort Worth airstrip, wearing a [[Flight jacket|pilot jacket]] and sunglasses.<ref name=D5286955>{{cite web|title='Jesus bought this': Delighted televangelist Kenneth Copeland giggles with glee as he unveils new $3million private jet paid for by donations from his followers|publisher=Daily Mail|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-5286955/Prosperity-Preacher-Kenneth-Copeland-giggles-GV.html}}</ref> The jet was bought from filmmaker and businessman [[Tyler Perry]].<ref name=D5286955/><ref name=CP-KC/> Now,{{when?|reason=This should be a \"As of\" fact. Saying \"Now\" introduces ambiguity.|date=April 2020}} the church is asking another $17<ref name=D5286955/> or $19.5 million for the building of a hangar, upgrading of the runway, and maintenance.<ref name=CP-KC/>\n\nIn 2015, Kenneth Copeland, in a broadcast alongside fellow televangelist [[Jesse Duplantis]], defended the use of private jets as a necessary part of their ministry, comparing flying in a commercial plane to getting \"in long tube with a bunch of demons\".<ref name=\"washingtonpost-private-jet\">{{cite news |last=Brice-Saddler |first=Michael |date=June 4, 2019 |title=A wealthy televangelist explains his fleet of private jets: \u2018It\u2019s a biblical thing\u2019 |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/religion/2019/06/04/wealthy-televangelist-explains-his-fleet-private-jets-its-biblical-thing/ |work=The Washingot Post |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Bote |first=Joshua |date=December 15, 2019 |title='None of your business': A televangelist defending his private jets goes viral |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2019/06/04/televangelist-kenneth-copeland-defends-private-jets-inside-edition/1337549001/ |work=USA Today |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Calicchio |first=Dom  |title=Televangelist Kenneth Copeland defends use of private jets in TV interview, denies calling people 'demons' |url=https://www.foxnews.com/us/televangelist-kenneth-copeland-defends-use-of-private-jets-in-tv-interview-denies-calling-people-demons |work=Fox News |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Brito |first=Christopher |date=June 4, 2019 |title=Televangelist defends lavish lifestyle and use of private jets, calls it a \"biblical thing\" |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/kenneth-copeland-televangelist-defends-lavish-lifestyle-and-use-of-private-jets-2019-06-04/ |work=CBS News |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\nCopeland's and other televangelists' use of private jets and other lavish houses and vehicles has been criticized.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kenneth Copeland Ministries Ups Being a Scumonaut by Bragging About New G5 Jet|publisher=Pulpit&Pen|url=http://pulpitandpen.org/2018/01/16/kenneth-copeland-ministries-ups-being-a-scumonaut-by-bragging-about-new-g5-jet/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Kenneth Copeland Loves His New $36 Million Jet|publisher=Patheos|url=http://www.patheos.com/blogs/warrenthrockmorton/2018/01/18/kenneth-copeland-36-million-jet/|access-date=December 25, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180324233307/http://www.patheos.com/blogs/warrenthrockmorton/2018/01/18/kenneth-copeland-36-million-jet/|archive-date=March 24, 2018|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Televagelist thanks Jesus for $36M private jet he uses to avoid demons|publisher=The Maven|url=https://www.themaven.net/beingliberal/room/televagelist-thanks-jesus-for-36m-private-jet-he-uses-to-avoid-demons-sldtGWfs-kq7Qisw941q5w}}</ref>\n\n=== COVID-19===\nDuring the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|pandemic of COVID-19]], Copeland repeatedly got attention for his comments and actions in response to the outbreak. On March 11, 2020, Copeland claimed to heal viewers of his TV show of the disease, asking them to touch the television set as he prayed for them.<ref>{{cite news |last=Lemon |first=Jason |date=March 12, 2020 |title=Conservative Pastor Claims He 'Healed' Viewers of Coronavirus Through Their TV Screens |url=https://www.newsweek.com/conservative-pastor-claims-he-healed-viewers-coronavirus-through-their-tv-screens-1492044 |work=Newsweek |access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\nAs many lost their jobs in the [[Coronavirus recession|economic crisis]] that the outbreak caused, Copeland told followers to continue paying tithes even if they lost their jobs.<ref>{{cite news |last=Gagn\u00e9 |first=Andr\u00e9 |date=March 29, 2020 |title=Coronavirus: Trump and religious right rely on faith, not science |url=https://theconversation.com/coronavirus-trump-and-religious-right-rely-on-faith-not-science-134508 |work=The Conversation |access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nIn a broadcast, Copeland called it a weak strain of the flu, and that fear of it was sin and putting faith in the devil. Copeland said that he did not agree with pastors that cancelled their services due to the coronavirus, saying \"I want you in my church. If we have to pass out thermometers. If we find one with a fever, let\u2019s get him healed right there. What if you do get it? Big deal!\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Blair |first=Leonardo |date=March 13, 2020 |title=Kenneth Copeland calls coronavirus \u2018very weak strain of flu,\u2019 says healthy people shouldn\u2019t fear |url=https://www.christianpost.com/news/kenneth-copeland-calls-coronavirus-very-weak-strain-of-flu-healthy-people-shouldnt-fear.html |work=The Christian Post |access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Wilson |first=Jason |date=April 4, 202 |title=The rightwing Christian preachers in deep denial over Covid-19's danger |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/apr/04/america-rightwing-christian-preachers-virus-hoax |work=The Guardian |access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nKenneth Copeland has repeatedly said during the pandemic that it has ended or will soon end.<ref name=\"independent-corona\">{{cite news |last=Woodward |first=Alex |date=April 6, 2020 |title=Coronavirus: Televangelist Kenneth Copeland \u2018blows wind of God\u2019 at Covid-19 to \u2018destroy\u2019 pandemic  |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/kenneth-copeland-blow-coronavirus-pray-sermon-trump-televangelist-a9448561.html |work=The Independent |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> He said at one point that God told him that it would soon be over as Christians' prayers have overwhelmed it, and that the pandemic was brought to America by \"displays of hate\" towards president Donald Trump by critics, which had intereferred with \"divine protection\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Sommer |first=Will |date=March 23, 2020 |title=Trump\u2019s Megachurch Allies Promise COVID-19 Snake Oil and \u2018Miracles\u2019 |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/trump-friendly-megachurch-pastors-push-bogus-coronavirus-cures |work=The Daily Beast |access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> On March 29, 2020, in a televised sermon, Copeland \"executed judgement\" on COVID-19. He claimed that it was \"finished\" and \"over\" and that the US was now \"healed and well again\".<ref name=\"independent-corona\" /> In another sermon shortly thereafter, Copeland claimed to destroy the virus with the \"wind of God\", saying \"I blow the wind of God on you. You are destroyed forever, and you\u2019ll never be back. Thank you, God. Let it happen. Cause it to happen.\"<ref name=\"independent-corona\" />\n\n==Selected KCM publications and recordings==\n*''Load Up Pocket Devotional: 31 Devotions to Revolutionize Your Future'' (Harrison House, July 2004) {{ISBN|1-57794-399-6}} {{ISBN|978-1577943990}}\n*''You Are Healed'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, July 1999) {{ISBN|0-88114-733-8}} {{ISBN|978-0881147339}}\n*''A Ceremony of Marriage'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, December 1996) {{ISBN|0-938458-15-9}} {{ISBN|978-0938458159}}\n*''Prayer: Your Foundation for Success'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, June 1999) {{ISBN|1-57794-155-1}} {{ISBN|978-1577941552}}\n*''Kenneth Copeland Reference Bible \u2013 Leather Bound'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, December 1996) {{ISBN|0-88114-296-4}} {{ISBN|978-0881142969}}\n*''Becoming Subject to the Authority of Jesus'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, 2001) {{ISBN|0-88114-972-1}} {{ISBN|978-0881149722}}\n*''How to Discipline Your Flesh'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, June 1999) {{ISBN|1-57562-116-9}} {{ISBN|978-1575621166}}\n*''From Faith to Faith: A Daily Guide to Victory'' (Harrison House, May 2000) {{ISBN|1-57794-225-6}} {{ISBN|978-1577942252}}\n*''Pursuit of His Presence: Daily Devotional'' (Harrison House, September 1998) {{ISBN|1-57794-137-3}} {{ISBN|978-1577941378}}\n*''The Wake-up Call'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, 2002) {{ISBN|1-57562-792-2}} {{ISBN|978-1575627922}}\n*''Classic Redemption'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, 2001) {{ISBN|0-938458-58-2}} {{ISBN|978-0938458586}}\n*''The Laws of Prosperity'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, December 1995) {{ISBN|0-88114-952-7}} {{ISBN|978-0881149524}}\n*''Prosperity: The Choice Is Yours'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, June 1992) {{ISBN|0-88114-728-1}} {{ISBN|978-0881147285}}\n*''Healing Promises'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, August 1994) {{ISBN|0-88114-949-7}} {{ISBN|978-0881149494}}\n*''Over the Edge: Youth Devotional'' (Harrison House, September 1998) {{ISBN|1-57794-138-1}} {{ISBN|978-1577941385}}\n*''Big Band Gospel'' (KCP Records, 2003)\n*''Racism in the Church. Kill the Root, Destroy the Tree'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, 2016) {{ISBN|978-1604633252}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Trinity Foundation (Dallas)]]\n*[[Neo-charismatic churches]]\n*[[Charismatic movement]]\n*[[Word of Faith]]\n*[[Prosperity Gospel]]\n*[[Tony Palmer (bishop)]]\n*[[Ulf Ekman]]\n\n==Notes and references==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.kcm.org/ Kenneth Copeland Ministries official site]\n*[http://emic.org Eagle Mountain International Church]\n*[http://bvov.tv Believer's Voice of Victory streaming site]\n*[http://believersstandunited.com Believers Stand United for Religious Freedom in America]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Copeland, Kenneth}}\n[[Category:1936 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American Pentecostal pastors]]\n[[Category:American television evangelists]]\n[[Category:American Charismatics]]\n[[Category:Imperial Records artists]]\n[[Category:Oral Roberts University people]]\n[[Category:People from Fort Worth, Texas]]\n[[Category:People from Lubbock, Texas]]\n[[Category:Pentecostal writers]]\n[[Category:Oral Roberts University alumni]]\n[[Category:American faith healers]]\n[[Category:Prosperity theologians]]\n[[Category:Pentecostals from Texas]]\n[[Category:Texas Republicans]]\n", "name_user": "78.133.21.138", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kenneth_Copeland"}
{"title_page": "Dung beetle", "text_new": "{{short description|Informal group of insects}}\n{{other uses}}\n{{Paraphyletic group\n| name = Dung beetle\n| image = Scarabaeus viettei 01.jpg\n| image_alt = Scarabaeus viettei (syn. Madateuchus viettei, Scarabaeidae) in dry spiny forest close to Mangily, western Madagascar\n| image_caption = ''{{ill|Scarabaeus viettei|sv}}'' (syn. ''Madateuchus viettei'', [[Scarabaeidae]]) in [[Madagascar spiny forests|dry spiny forest]] close to [[Mangily]], western [[Madagascar]]\n| auto = yes\n| parent = Scarabaeoidea\n| includes = \n*[[Geotrupidae]]\n*[[Scarabaeinae]]\n*[[Aphodiinae]]\n| excludes = \n*[[Termitoderini]]\n}}\n\n'''Dung beetles''' are [[beetle]]s that [[coprophagia|feed]] on [[feces]] (dung). Beetles in some species of dung beetles can bury dung 250 times their own mass in one night.<ref>{{cite web|title=Some Less Known Fascinating Facts about Dung Beetle|url=http://news.biharprabha.com/2014/04/some-less-known-fascinating-facts-about-dung-beetle/|work=IANS|publisher=news.biharprabha.com|accessdate=21 April 2014}}</ref>\n\nMany dung beetles, known as ''rollers'', roll dung into round balls, which are used as a food source or breeding chambers. Others, known as ''tunnelers'', bury the dung wherever they find it. A third group, the ''dwellers'', neither roll nor burrow: they simply live in manure. They are often attracted by the dung collected by [[burrowing owl]]s. There are dung beetle species of different colours and sizes, and some functional traits such as body mass (or biomass) and leg length can have high levels of variability.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite journal|last=Griffiths|first=Hannah M.|last2=Louzada|first2=Julio|last3=Bardgett|first3=Richard D.|last4=Barlow|first4=Jos|date=2016-03-03|title=Assessing the Importance of Intraspecific Variability in Dung Beetle Functional Traits|journal=PLOS ONE|volume=11|issue=3|pages=e0145598|doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0145598|pmid=26939121|pmc=4777568|issn=1932-6203|bibcode=2016PLoSO..1145598G}}</ref>\n\nAll the [[species]] belong to the superfamily [[Scarabaeoidea]], most of them to the subfamilies [[Scarabaeinae]] and [[Aphodiinae]] of the family [[Scarabaeidae]] (scarab beetles). As most species of Scarabaeinae feed exclusively on feces, that subfamily is often dubbed ''true dung beetles''. There are dung-feeding beetles which belong to other families, such as the [[Geotrupidae]] (the ''earth-boring dung beetle''). The Scarabaeinae alone comprises more than 5,000 species.<ref>Frolov, A.V. [http://www.zin.ru/animalia/coleoptera/eng/afrsc_ru.htm \"Subfamily Scarabaeinae: atlas of representatives of the tribes (Scarabaeidae)\"]. Retrieved on 2007-08-02.</ref>\n\nThe nocturnal African dung beetle ''[[Scarabaeus satyrus]]'' is one of the few known non-vertebrate animals that navigate and orient themselves using the [[Milky Way]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-21150721|author=Jonathan Amos|title=Dung beetles guided by Milky Way|publisher=[[BBC News]]|date=24 January 2013|accessdate=28 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Dacke | first1 = M. | last2 = Baird | first2 = E. | last3 = Byrne | first3 = M. | last4 = Scholtz | first4 = C. H. | last5 = Warrant | first5 = E. J. | title = Dung Beetles Use the Milky Way for Orientation | doi = 10.1016/j.cub.2012.12.034 | journal = Current Biology | volume = 23 | issue = 4 | pages = 298\u2013300 | year = 2013 | pmid =  23352694| pmc = | doi-access = free }}</ref>\n\n==Taxonomy==\nDung beetles are not a single taxonomic group; dung feeding is found in a number of families of beetles, so the behaviour cannot be assumed to have evolved only once.\n* [[Coleoptera]] (order), beetles\n** [[Scarabaeoidea]] (superfamily), scarabs (most families in the group do not use dung)\n*** [[Geotrupidae]] (family), \"earth-boring dung beetles\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Geotrupidae (earth-boring dung beetles)|url=http://www.kerbtier.de/cgi-bin/enFSearch.cgi?Fam=Geotrupidae|publisher=kerbtier.de|accessdate=28 March 2015}}</ref>\n*** [[Scarabaeidae]] (family), \"scarab beetles\" (not all species use dung)\n**** [[Scarabaeinae]] (subfamily), \"true dung beetles\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Scarabaeinae dung beetles|url=http://scarabaeinae.lifedesks.org/|accessdate=28 March 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150319101341/http://scarabaeinae.lifedesks.org/|archive-date=2015-03-19|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n**** [[Aphodiinae]] (subfamily), \"small dung beetles\" (not all species use dung)<ref name=skelley>Skelley, P. E. [http://museum.unl.edu/research/entomology/Guide/Scarabaeoidea/Scarabaeidae/Aphodiinae/Aphodiinae-Overview/AphodiinaeO.html Aphodiinae.] ''Generic Guide to New World Scarab Beetles.'' University of Nebraska State Museum. 2008 Version.</ref>\nSystematic Position:\n  Kingdom                        Animalia \n      Phylum                           Arthropoda \n           Subphylum                          Hexapoda \n                  Class                              Insecta \n                          Order                             Coleoptera \n                                    Suborder                     Polyphaga\n                                            Superfamily                Scarabaeoidea \n                                                       Family                   Scarabaeidae\n                              \u2191                                                        (Latreille, 1802)\n\n==Ecology and behavior==\n[[File:Dung beetle working-001.ogv|thumb|Dung beetle rolling a ball of dung in the [[Addo Elephant National Park]], [[South Africa]]]]\n\nDung beetles live in many [[habitat]]s, including desert, [[grassland]]s and [[savanna]]s,<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Fran\u00e7a|first=Filipe M.|last2=Korasaki|first2=Vanesca|last3=Louzada|first3=Julio|last4=Vaz-de-Mello|first4=Fernando Z.|last5=Fran\u00e7a|first5=Filipe M.|last6=Korasaki|first6=Vanesca|last7=Louzada|first7=Julio|last8=Vaz-de-Mello|first8=Fernando Z.|date=2016|title=First report on dung beetles in intra-Amazonian savannahs in Roraima, Brazil|journal=Biota Neotropica|volume=16|issue=1|doi=10.1590/1676-0611-BN-2015-0034|issn=1676-0603|doi-access=free}}</ref> [[farm]]lands, and native and planted [[forest]]s.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Beiroz|first=Wallace|last2=Slade|first2=Eleanor M.|last3=Barlow|first3=Jos|last4=Silveira|first4=Juliana M.|last5=Louzada|first5=Julio|last6=Sayer|first6=Emma|date=2017-01-01|title=Dung beetle community dynamics in undisturbed tropical forests: implications for ecological evaluations of land-use change|journal=Insect Conservation and Diversity|language=en|volume=10|issue=1|pages=94\u2013106|doi=10.1111/icad.12206|issn=1752-4598|url=http://eprints.lancs.ac.uk/83810/1/BeirozEtAlPreprint.pdf}}</ref> They are highly influenced by the environmental context,<ref name=\":0\" /> and do not prefer extremely cold or dry weather. They are found on all continents except [[Antarctica]]. They eat the dung of [[herbivore]]s and [[omnivore]]s, and prefer that produced by the latter.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dell'Amore|first1=Christine|title=Dung Beetles' Favorite Poop Revealed|url=http://voices.nationalgeographic.com/2012/04/17/weird-wild-dung-beetles-favorite-poop-revealed/|website=National Geographic|publisher=National Geographic Society|accessdate=22 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923045212/http://voices.nationalgeographic.com/2012/04/17/weird-wild-dung-beetles-favorite-poop-revealed/|archive-date=2016-09-23|url-status=dead}}</ref> Many of them also feed on [[mushrooms]] and [[decomposition|decaying]] [[leaf|leaves]] and [[fruit]]s. One type living in Central America, ''[[Deltochilum valgum]]'', is a carnivore preying upon [[millipedes]]. Dung beetles do not necessarily have to eat or drink anything else, because the dung provides all the necessary [[nutrient]]s.{{Citation needed|date=August 2019}}\n\nMost dung beetles search for dung using their sensitive [[olfaction|sense of smell]]. Some smaller species simply attach themselves to the dung-providers to wait for the dung. After capturing the dung, a dung beetle rolls it, following a straight line despite all obstacles. Sometimes, dung beetles try to steal the dung ball from another beetle, so the dung beetles have to move rapidly away from a dung pile once they have rolled their ball to prevent it from being stolen. Dung beetles can roll up to 10 times their weight. Male ''Onthophagus taurus'' beetles can pull 1,141 times their own body weight: the equivalent of an average person pulling six double-decker buses full of people.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2010/mar/24/dung-beetles | location=London | work=The Guardian | first=Homa | last=Khaleeli | title=Just how strong is a dung beetle? | date=24 March 2010}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Scarabaeus laticollis 2.jpg|thumb|left|Two dung beetles fighting over a ball of dung]]\n\nA species of dung beetle (the African ''Scarabaeus zambesianus'') [[animal navigation|navigates]] by [[Polarization (waves)|polarization]] patterns in [[moonlight]],{{Sfn|Tills|2013|p=123}}  the first animal known to do so.<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1038/424033a| pmid = 12840748| title = Animal behaviour: Insect orientation to polarized moonlight| journal = Nature| volume = 424| issue = 6944| page = 33| year = 2003| last1 = Dacke | first1 = M. | last2 = Nilsson | first2 = D. E. | last3 = Scholtz | first3 = C. H. | last4 = Byrne | first4 = M. | last5 = Warrant | first5 = E. J. | bibcode=2003Natur.424...33D}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Milius | first1 = Susan | year = 2003 | title = Moonlighting: Beetles navigate by lunar polarity | url = http://www.sciencenews.org/articles/20030705/fob4.asp | journal = Science News | volume = 164 | issue = 1| pages = 4\u20135 | doi = 10.2307/3981988 | jstor = 3981988 }}</ref><ref>Roach, John (2003). [http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2003/07/0702_030702_dungbeetle.html \"Dung Beetles Navigate by the Moon, Study Says\"], ''National Geographic News''. Retrieved on 2007-08-02.</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.2307/3981988| jstor = 3981988| title = Moonlighting| journal = Science News| volume = 164| issue = 1| pages = 4\u20135| year = 2003| last1 = Milius | first1 = S. }}</ref> Dung beetles can also navigate when only the [[Milky Way]] or clusters of bright stars are visible,<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite journal |doi=10.1016/j.cub.2012.12.034|pmid=23352694|title=Dung Beetles Use the Milky Way for Orientation|journal=Current Biology|volume=23|issue=4|pages=298|year=2013|last1=Dacke|first1=Marie|last2=Baird|first2=Emily|last3=Byrne|first3=Marcus|last4=Scholtz|first4=Clarke H.|last5=Warrant|first5=Eric J.|doi-access=free}}</ref>  making them the only insects known to orient themselves by the Milky Way.<ref name=\"scienceDaily\">{{cite news|last=Wits University |url=https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2013/01/130124123203.htm |title=Dung Beetles Follow the Milky Way: Insects Found to Use Stars for Orientation|work=ScienceDaily|date=24 January 2013 |accessdate=25 January 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\"/> The eyes of dung beetles are superposition [[Compound eye|compound eyes]] typical of many scarabaeid beetles;<ref>{{cite journal|author=Meyer-Rochow, V.B.|title=Retina and dioptric apparatus of the dung beetle ( Euoniticellus africanus ; Scarabaeidae)|journal=Journal of Insect Physiology|date=1978|volume= 24|issue=2|pages= 165\u2013179|doi=10.1016/0022-1910(78)90114-2}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal| author1=Meyer-Rochow, V.B.| author2= Gokan, N.| title=The eye of the dung beetle Onthophagus posticus (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae)| date=1990| journal= New Zealand Journal of Entomology| volume=13| pages=7\u201315| doi= 10.1080/00779962.1990.9722582}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Scarabaeus laticollis.jpg|thumb|upright|An earth-boring dung beetle working]]\n[[File:DungBeetle.jpg|thumb|A dung beetle with two balls of dung]]\n\nCambefort and Hanski (1991) classified dung beetles into three functional types based on their feeding and nesting strategies such as \u2013 Rollers, Tunnelers and Dwellers. The \"rollers\" roll and bury a dung ball either for food storage or for making a brooding ball. In the latter case, two beetles, one male and one female, stay around the dung ball during the rolling process. Usually it is the male that rolls the ball, while the female hitch-hikes or simply follows behind. In some cases, the male and the female roll together. When a spot with soft soil is found, they stop and bury the  ball, then [[mating|mate]] underground. After the mating, one or both of them prepares the brooding ball. When the ball is finished, the female lays eggs inside it, a form of [[mass provisioning]].\n\nSome species do not leave after this stage, but remain to safeguard their offspring. The dung beetle goes through a complete [[metamorphosis (biology)|metamorphosis]]. The larvae live in brood balls made with dung prepared by their parents. During the larval stage, the beetle feeds on the dung surrounding it.\n\nThe behavior of the beetles was poorly understood until the studies of [[Jean Henri Fabre]] in the late 19th century. For example, Fabre corrected the myth that a dung beetle would seek aid from other dung beetles when confronted by obstacles. By observation and experiment, he found the seeming helpers were in fact awaiting an opportunity to steal the roller's food source.<ref>{{cite book |author=Fabre, J. Henri |authorlink = Henri Fabre |date=1949 |title=The Insect World of J. Henri Fabre |url=https://archive.org/details/insectworldofjhe0000fabr |url-access=registration |others=De Mattos, Alexander Teixeira (translator) |publisher=Dodd, Mead & Company |page=[https://archive.org/details/insectworldofjhe0000fabr/page/99 99] |quote=I ask myself in vain what Proudhon introduced into Scarabaean morality the daring paradox that 'property means plunder', or what diplomatist taught the Dung-beetle the savage maxim that 'might is right'.}}</ref>\n\nThey are widely used in ecological research as a good [[bioindicator]] group to examine the impacts of climate disturbances, such as extreme droughts <ref>{{Cite journal |doi = 10.1098/rstb.2019.0116|pmid = 31983328 |title = Climatic and local stressor interactions threaten tropical forests and coral reefs |journal = Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society B|volume = 375|issue = 1794 |pages = 20190116|year = 2020|last1 = Fran\u00e7a |first1 = FM|last2 = Benkwitt |first2 = CE|last3 = Peralta |first3 = G |last4 = Robinson |first4 = JPW|last5 = Graham|first5 =  NAJ |last6 = Tylianakis |first6 = JM|last7 = Berenguer |first7 = E |last8 = Lees |first8 = AC|last9 = Ferreira |first9 = J|last10 = Louzada |first10 = J |last11 = Barlow |first11 = J}}</ref> and associated fires <ref>{{Cite journal|last=Fran\u00e7a|first=Filipe|last2=Ferreira|first2=J| last3=Vaz-de-Mello|first3=FZ| last4=Maia|first4=LF| last5=Berenguer|first5=E| last6=Palmeira|first6=A| last7=Fadini|first7=R| last8=Louzada|first8=J |last9=Braga|first9=R| last10=Oliveira|first10=VH| last11=Barlow|first11=J| date=10 February 2020|title= El Ni\u00f1o impacts on human\u2010modified tropical forests: Consequences for dung beetle diversity and associated ecological processes |journal=Biotropica |volume=52 | issue = 1 |pages=1\u201311|doi=10.1111/btp.12756|doi-access=free}}</ref>, and human activities on tropical biodiversity <ref>{{Cite journal|last=Fran\u00e7a|first=Filipe|last2=Barlow|first2=Jos|last3=Ara\u00fajo|first3=B\u00e1rbara|last4=Louzada|first4=Julio|date=4 November 2016|title=Does selective logging stress tropical forest invertebrates? Using fat stores to examine sublethal responses in dung beetles|journal=Ecology and Evolution|volume=6 | issue = 23 |pages=8526\u20138533|doi=10.1002/ece3.2488|pmid=28031804|pmc=5167030}}</ref> and ecosystem functioning,<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Fran\u00e7a|first=Filipe M.|last2=Fraz\u00e3o|first2=F\u00e1bio S.|last3=Korasaki|first3=Vanesca|last4=Louzada|first4=J\u00falio|last5=Barlow|first5=Jos|date=2017-12-01|title=Identifying thresholds of logging intensity on dung beetle communities to improve the sustainable management of Amazonian tropical forests|journal=Biological Conservation|volume=216|issue=Supplement C|pages=115\u2013122|doi=10.1016/j.biocon.2017.10.014|url=https://eprints.lancs.ac.uk/id/eprint/88405/1/170918_Manuscript.pdf}}</ref> such as seed dispersal, soil bioturbation and nutrient cycling<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Fran\u00e7a|first=Filipe|last2=Ferreira|first2=J| last3=Vaz-de-Mello|first3=FZ| last4=Maia|first4=LF| last5=Berenguer|first5=E| last6=Palmeira|first6=A| last7=Fadini|first7=R| last8=Louzada|first8=J |last9=Braga|first9=R| last10=Oliveira|first10=VH| last11=Barlow|first11=J| date=10 February 2020|title= El Ni\u00f1o impacts on human\u2010modified tropical forests: Consequences for dung beetle diversity and associated ecological processes |journal=Biotropica |volume=52 | issue = 1 |pages=1\u201311|doi=10.1111/btp.12756|doi-access=free}}</ref>.\n\n==Benefits and uses==\n[[File:Caution Dung Beetles, South Africa.jpg|thumb|upright|Caution sign showing the importance of dung beetles in [[South Africa]]]]\n[[File:CSIRO ScienceImage 10743 Onitis aygulus.jpg|thumb|left|''Onitis aygulus'']]\n[[File:CSIRO ScienceImage 10809 Dung beetle Onthophagus nigriventris.jpg|thumb|left|''Onthophagus nigriventris'']]\nDung beetles play a role in [[agriculture]] and [[tropical forest]]s. By burying and consuming dung, they improve nutrient recycling and soil structure.<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1016/j.apsoil.2010.05.010| title = Dung beetles (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae) can improve soil hydrological properties| journal = Applied Soil Ecology| volume = 46| pages = 9\u201316| year = 2010| last1 = Brown | first1 = J. | last2 = Scholtz | first2 = C. H. | last3 = Janeau | first3 = J. L. | last4 = Grellier | first4 = S. | last5 = Podwojewski | first5 = P. | hdl = 2263/14419| url = http://repository.up.ac.za/bitstream/2263/14419/1/Brown_Dung%282010%29.pdf }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Nichols|first=E.|last2=Spector|first2=S.|last3=Louzada|first3=J.|last4=Larsen|first4=T.|last5=Amezquita|first5=S.|last6=Favila|first6=M.E.|title=Ecological functions and ecosystem services provided by Scarabaeinae dung beetles|journal=Biological Conservation|volume=141|issue=6|pages=1461\u20131474|doi=10.1016/j.biocon.2008.04.011|year=2008}}</ref> Dung beetles have been further shown to improve soil conditions and plant growth on rehabilitated coal mines in South Africa.<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1016/j.apsoil.2018.08.011| title = Dung beetle activity improves herbaceous plant growth and soil properties on confinements simulating reclaimed mined land in South Africa| journal = Applied Soil Ecology| volume = 132| pages = 53\u201359| year = 2018| last1 = Badenhorst | first1 = J. | last2 = Dabrowski | first2 = J. | last3 = Scholtz | first3 = C. H. | last4 = Truter | first4 = W. F. | hdl = 2263/67268 | hdl-access = free }}</ref> They are also important for the dispersal of seeds present in animals' dung, influencing seed burial and seedling recruitment in tropical forests.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Griffiths|first=Hannah M.|last2=Bardgett|first2=Richard D.|last3=Louzada|first3=Julio|last4=Barlow|first4=Jos|date=2016-12-14|title=The value of trophic interactions for ecosystem function: dung beetle communities influence seed burial and seedling recruitment in tropical forests|journal=Proc. R. Soc. B|language=en|volume=283|issue=1844|pages=20161634|doi=10.1098/rspb.2016.1634|issn=0962-8452|pmc=5204146|pmid=27928036}}</ref> They can protect livestock, such as [[cattle]], by removing the dung which, if left, could provide habitat for [[pest (animal)|pests]] such as [[fly|flies]]. Therefore, many countries have [[Biological pest control|introduced]] the creatures for the benefit of [[animal husbandry]]. In [[developing countries]], the beetles are especially important as an adjunct for improving standards of hygiene. The [[American Institute of Biological Sciences]] reports that dung beetles save the [[United States of America|United States]] cattle industry an estimated [[United States dollar|US$]]380 million annually through burying above-ground livestock feces.<ref>{{Cite journal| doi = 10.1641/0006-3568(2006)56[311:TEVOES]2.0.CO;2| title = The Economic Value of Ecological Services Provided by Insects| journal = BioScience| volume = 56| issue = 4| pages = 311\u201323| year = 2006| last1 = Losey| first1 = J. E.| last2 = Vaughan| first2 = M.| url = http://www.xerces.org/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/economic_value_insects.pdf| access-date = 2009-01-28| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180619202116/http://www.xerces.org/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/economic_value_insects.pdf| archive-date = 2018-06-19| url-status = dead}}</ref>\n\nIn Australia, the [[Commonwealth Scientific and Industrial Research Organisation]] (CSIRO) commissioned the [[Australian Dung Beetle Project]] (1965\u20131985) which, led by [[George Bornemissza]], sought to introduce species of dung beetles from South Africa and Europe. The successful introduction of 23 species was made, most notably ''[[Digitonthophagus gazella]]'' and ''[[Euoniticellus intermedius]]'', which has resulted in improvement of the quality and fertility of Australian cattle pastures, along with a reduction in the population of pestilent [[Musca vetustissima|bush flies]] by around 90 percent.<ref name=\"adbp\">{{cite journal | last1 = Bornemissza | first1 = G. F. | year = 1976 | title = The Australian dung beetle project 1965\u20131975 | url = | journal = Australian Meat Research Committee Review | volume = 30 | issue = | pages = 1\u201330 }}</ref><!---Missylisa153, August 2009--->\n\nAn application has been made by [[Landcare Research]] to import up to 11 species of dung beetle into [[New Zealand]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ermanz.govt.nz/BertDocs/ERMA200599_Application%20summary%20ERMA200599%20FINAL.pdf |title=Application summary \u2013 ERMA200599 |publisher=ERMA |accessdate=12 December 2010 }}{{dead link|date=September 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> As well as improving pasture soils the Dung Beetle Release Strategy Group say that it would result in a reduction in emissions of [[nitrous oxide]] (a [[greenhouse gas]]) from agriculture.<ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10675713 |title=Let's roll... dung beetle to combat global warming|last=Ihaka|first=James|date=24 September 2010|work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]|accessdate=12 December 2010}}</ref> There is, however, strong opposition from some at the [[University of Auckland]], and a few others, based on the risks of the dung beetles acting as vectors of disease.<ref>{{cite web |author=17 Aug 2014, 01:09 am |url=http://www.fwplus.co.nz/article/experts-dump-on-dung-beetle?p=6 |title=Experts dump on dung beetle |publisher=Fwplus.co.nz |date=2012-05-07 |accessdate=2014-08-16 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130414001314/http://www.fwplus.co.nz/article/experts-dump-on-dung-beetle?p=6 |archivedate=2013-04-14 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/environment/news/article.cfm?c_id=39&objectid=10866149 |title=Grant Guilford: Dung beetle plan a risky gamble |publisher=Nzherald.co.nz |date= 2013-02-18|accessdate=2014-08-16|newspaper=NZ Herald |last1=Guilford |first1=Grant }}</ref> There are public health researchers at the University of Auckland who agree with the current EPA risk assessment <ref>{{Cite journal|author=drj9 |url=http://janinepaynter.wordpress.com/2013/03/17/fickle-thy-name-is-vox-populi-puzzle-over-dung-beetles-and-science-reporting/ |title='Fickle thy name is' vox populi : puzzle over dung beetles and science reporting   |journal =Journal of Outrageous Speculation |date=2013-03-17 |accessdate=2014-04-22}}</ref> and indeed there are several Landcare programmes in Australia that involve schoolchildren collecting dung beetles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dungbeetle.org.nz/release-programme/ |title=Release Programme &#124; Dung Beetles in New Zealand |publisher=Dungbeetle.org.nz |date=2013-09-26 |accessdate=2014-04-22}}</ref>\n\nThe African dung beetle, ''D. gazella'', was introduced in several locations in North and [[South America]] and has been spreading its distribution to other regions by natural dispersal and accidental transportation, and is now probably naturalized in most countries between [[M\u00e9xico]] and [[Argentina]]. The exotic species might be useful for controlling diseases of [[livestock]] in commercial areas, and might displace native species in modified landscapes, however data is not conclusive about its effect on native species in natural environments and further monitoring is required.<ref name=DgazellaVenezuela>{{cite journal|last1=Ferrer-Paris|first1=Jos\u00e9 R.|title=El escarabajo estercolero africano, ''Digitonthophagus gazella'', (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae) en la regi\u00f3n Neotropical, \u00bfbeneficioso o perjudicial?|journal=Bolet\u00edn de la Red Latinoamericana Para el Estudio de Especies Invasoras|date=2014|volume=4|issue=1|pages=41\u201348|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/268510737}}</ref>\n\nLike many other insects, the (dried) dung beetle, called ''qianglang'' (\u8723\u870b) in Chinese, is used in [[Chinese materia medica|Chinese herbal medicine]]. It is recorded in the \"Insect section\" (\u87f2\u90e8) of the ''[[Bencao Gangmu|Compendium of Materia Medica]]'', where it is recommended for the cure of 10 diseases.{{cn|date=December 2019}}\n\nIn [[Isan]], Northeastern Thailand, the local people famously eat many different kinds of insects including the dung beetle. There is an Isan song \u0e01\u0e38\u0e14\u0e08\u0e35\u0e48\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e22\u0e44\u0e1b\u0e43\u0e2b\u0e19 \"Where did the Dung Beetle go\", which relates the replacement of [[water buffalo]] with the \"metal\" buffalo, which does not provide the dung needed for the dung beetle and has led to the increasing rarity of the dung beetle in the agricultural region.\n\nMediterranean dung beetles (''Bubas bison'') have been used in conjunction with [[Biochar#Stock_fodder|biochar stock fodder]] to reduce emissions of [[Nitrous_oxide#Greenhouse_effect|nitrous oxide]] and [[Carbon_dioxide#In_Earth's_atmosphere|carbon dioxide]], which are both greenhouse gases. The beetles work the biochar-enriched dung into the soil without the use of machines.<ref name=\"abc.net.au-2019-10-18-beetles-charcoal\">{{cite web\n | url =https://www.abc.net.au/news/rural/2019-10-18/wa-farmer-uses-beetles-and-charcoal-to-combat-climate-change/11613846\n | title =Poo-eating beetles and charcoal used by WA farmer to combat climate change\n | last =Daly\n | first =Jon\n | date =18 October 2019\n | website =ABC.net.au\n | publisher =Australian Broadcasting Corporation\n | access-date =18 October 2019\n | quote =Mr Pow said his innovative farming system could help livestock producers become more profitable while helping to address the impact of climate change. }}</ref>\n\n==Scarab in ancient Egypt==\n{{Main|Scarab (artifact)}}\n[[File:Karnak temple scarab beetle A.jpg|thumb|right|A scarab statue at the [[Karnak]] temple complex]]\n\nSeveral species of the dung beetle, most notably the species ''[[Scarabaeus sacer]]'' (often referred to as ''the sacred scarab''), enjoyed a sacred status among the [[ancient Egypt]]ians.\n{{hiero|\u1e2bpr|<hiero>xpr</hiero>|align=right|era=egypt}}Egyptian hieroglyphic script uses the image of the beetle to represent a [[Egyptian language|triliteral phonetic]] that Egyptologists transliterate as ''xpr'' or ''\u1e2bpr'' and translate as \"to come into being\", \"to become\" or \"to transform\". The derivative term ''xprw'' or ''\u1e2bpr(w)'' is variously translated as \"form\", \"transformation\", \"happening\", \"mode of being\" or \"what has come into being\", depending on the context. It may have existential, fictional, or ontologic significance.\n\nThe scarab was linked to [[Khepri]] (\"he who has come into being\"), the god of the rising [[sun]]. The ancients believed that the dung beetle was only male in gender, and reproduced by depositing [[semen]] into a dung ball. The supposed self-creation of the beetle resembles that of Khepri, who creates himself out of nothing. Moreover, the dung ball rolled by a dung beetle resembles the sun. [[Plutarch]] wrote: {{quote|The race of beetles has no female, but all the males eject their sperm into a round pellet of material which they roll up by pushing it from the opposite side, just as the sun seems to turn the heavens in the direction opposite to its own course, which is from west to east.<ref>[http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Isis_and_Osiris*/E.html#ref373 \"Isis and Osiris\"], ''Moralia'', in volume V of the [[Loeb Classical Library]] edition, 1936, now in the public domain. Retrieved on 2007-08-02.</ref>}}\n\nThe ancient Egyptians believed that Khepri renewed the sun every day before rolling it above the horizon, then carried it through the other world after sunset, only to renew it, again, the next day. Some [[New Kingdom]] royal tombs exhibit a threefold image of the sun god, with the beetle as symbol of the morning sun. The astronomical ceiling in the tomb of [[Ramses VI]] portrays the nightly \"death\" and \"rebirth\" of the sun as being swallowed by [[Nut (goddess)|Nut]], goddess of the sky, and re-emerging from her womb as Khepri.\n\nThe image of the scarab, conveying ideas of transformation, renewal, and resurrection, is ubiquitous in ancient Egyptian religious and [[funerary art]].\n\nExcavations of ancient Egyptian sites have yielded images of the scarab in bone, [[ivory]], stone, [[Egyptian faience]], and precious metals, dating from the Sixth Dynasty and up to the period of Roman rule. They are generally small, bored to allow stringing on a necklace, and the base bears a brief inscription or [[cartouche]]. Some have been used as [[Impression seal|seals]]. [[Pharaoh]]s sometimes commissioned the manufacture of larger images with lengthy inscriptions, such as the [[The lion hunts of Amenhotep III during the first ten years of his reign|commemorative scarab]] of Queen [[Tiye]]. Massive sculptures of scarabs can be seen at [[Luxor Temple]], at the Serapeum in Alexandria (see [[Serapis]]) and elsewhere in Egypt.\n\n[[File:Egypt.KV6.04.jpg|thumb|left|A scarab, depicted on the walls of [[KV6|Tomb KV6]] in the [[Valley of the Kings]]]]\n\nThe scarab was of prime significance in the funerary cult of ancient Egypt. Scarabs, generally, though not always, were cut from green stone, and placed on the chest of the deceased. Perhaps the most famous example of such \"heart scarabs\" is the yellow-green [[pectoral (Ancient Egypt)|pectoral]] scarab found among the entombed provisions of [[Tutankhamen]]. It was carved from a large piece of [[Libyan desert glass]]. The purpose of the \"heart scarab\" was to ensure that the heart would not bear witness against the deceased at judgement in the Afterlife. Other possibilities are suggested by the \"transformation spells\" of the ''Coffin Texts'', which affirm that the soul of the deceased may transform (''xpr'') into a human being, a god, or a bird and reappear in the world of the living.\n\nOne scholar comments on other traits of the scarab connected with the theme of death and rebirth:\n{{quote|It may not have gone unnoticed that the pupa, whose wings and legs are encased at this stage of development, is very mummy-like. It has even been pointed out that the egg-bearing ball of dung is created in an underground chamber which is reached by a vertical shaft and horizontal passage curiously reminiscent of Old Kingdom mastaba tombs.\"<ref>Andrews, Carol (1994). ''Amulets of Ancient Egypt''. Texas: University of Texas Press. {{ISBN|0-292-70464-X}}. p. 51.</ref>}}\n\nIn contrast to funerary contexts, some of ancient Egypt's neighbors adopted the scarab motif for [[scaraboid seal|seals]] of varying types. The best-known of these being Judean [[LMLK seal]]s (8 of 21 designs contained scarab beetles), which were used exclusively to stamp impressions on storage jars during the reign of [[Hezekiah]].\n\nThe scarab remains an item of popular interest thanks to modern fascination with the art and beliefs of ancient Egypt. Scarab beads in semiprecious stones or glazed ceramics can be purchased at most bead shops, while at Luxor Temple a massive ancient scarab has been roped off to discourage visitors from rubbing the base of the statue \"for luck\".\n\n==In culture==\nSome dung beetles are used as food in South East Asia and a variety of dung beetle species have been used [[therapeutically]] (and are still being used in traditionally living societies) in potions and folk medicines to treat a number of illnesses and disorders.<ref>{{cite journal |last=Meyer-Rochow | first=V.B. |title=Therapeutic arthropods and other, largely terrestrial, folk-medicinally important invertebrates: a comparative survey and review. |journal=Journal of Ethnobiology and Ethnomedicine| date=January 2017| volume=13 |issue=9 |pages=9| doi=10.1186/s13002-017-0136-0| pmid=28173820 | pmc=5296966 }}</ref>\n\n===In literature===\nIn [[Aesop's fable]] \"[[The Eagle and the Beetle]]\", the eagle kills a hare that has asked for sanctuary with a beetle. The beetle then takes revenge by twice destroying the eagle's eggs. The eagle, in despair, flies up to [[Mount Olympus|Olympus]] and places her latest eggs in [[Zeus]]'s lap, beseeching the god to protect them. When the beetle finds out what the eagle has done, it stuffs itself with dung, goes straight up to Zeus and flies right into his face. Zeus is startled at the sight of the unpleasant creature, jumping to his feet so that the eggs are broken. Learning of the origin of their feud, Zeus attempts to mediate and, when his efforts to mediate fail, he changes the breeding season of the eagle to a time when the beetles are not above ground.\n\n[[Aristophanes]] alluded to Aesop's fable several times in his plays. In ''[[Peace (play)|Peace]]'', the hero rides up to Olympus to free the goddess Peace from her prison. His steed is an enormous dung beetle which has been fed so much dung that it has grown to monstrous size.\n\n[[Hans Christian Andersen]]'s \"The Dung Beetle\" tells the story of a dung beetle who lives in the stable of the king's horses in an imaginary kingdom. When he demands golden shoes like those the king's horse wears and is refused, he flies away and has a series of adventures, which are often precipitated by his [[Superiority complex|feeling of superiority]] to other animals. He finally returns to the stable having decided (against all logic) that it is for him that the king's horse wears golden shoes.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Andersen|first1=Hans Christian|last2=James|first2=M. R. (trans.)|work=Hans Andersen Forty-Two Stories | title=The Beetle |date=1930 |publisher=Faber and Faber |url=https://fadedpage.com/showbook.php?pid=20100119}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Franz Kafka]]'s ''[[The Metamorphosis]]'', the transformed character of Gregor Samsa is called an \"old dung beetle\" (''alter Mistk\u00e4fer'') by a [[charwoman]] (Samsa is, in fact, a [[cockroach]]).\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|Insects}}\n* ''[[Catharsius]]'', an important dung beetle genus in African and Asian environments\n* [[Addo Elephant National Park]], site of the largest remaining population of the endangered flightless dung beetle (''Circellium bacchus'').\n* [[List of dung beetle and chafer (Scarabaeoidea) species recorded in Britain]]\n* [[Rotating locomotion in living systems]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n== Book sources ==\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{citation|title=Sciene Year|first=Tony |last=Tills|publisher=World Book,Inc.|year=2013|isbn=9780716605676}}\n\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikispecies|Scarabaeinae}}\n{{wikispecies|Aphodiinae}}\n{{Commons category|Dung beetles}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20121105033930/http://www.cosmosmagazine.com/features/online/5803/on-a-roll Feature: 'What to do with too much poo'] \u2013 The success story behind the introduction of dung beetles in Australia at cosmosmagazine.com\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20161018110844/http://www.insects.org/ced1/beetles_rel_sym.html Beetles as religious symbols] at insects.org\n* [http://www.scarabnet.org/ Scarabaeinae Research Network]\n* [http://www.amonline.net.au/factsheets/dung-beetles.htm Dung beetles] at the Australia Museum\n* [http://www.catharsius.fr/ Catharsius], an international group working on taxonomy and ecology of Western African dung beetles\n* Tomas Libich, [http://www.goliathus.com/en/en-dung-beetle.html Congo dung beetle sp1] and [http://www.goliathus.com/en/en-dung-beetle-2.html Congo dung beetle sp2] photos\n* [https://archive.is/20130416051320/http://www.wild.org/video/i-brake-for-dung-beetles/ Dung Beetles in action (video)] by The WILD Foundation/Boyd Norton\n* [http://www.dungbeetle.org.nz/ Dung Beetles in New Zealand] (proposed release of dung beetles, with background research)\n* [http://www.ted.com/talks/marcus_byrne_the_dance_of_the_dung_beetle.html Marcus Byrne The dance of the dung beetle] Ted conference about dung beetle behavior.\n* [http://www.dungbeetles.com.au Dung Beetle Ecosystem Engineers] Dung Beetle Ecosystem Engineers \u2013 expanding the range of dung beetles in Australia and analysing their performance for livestock producers.\n* [http://www.coolmathgames.com] Coolmathgames\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Coprophagous insects]]\n<!-- [[Category:Scarabaeinae]] -->\n[[Category:Scarabaeidae]]<!-- for Aphodiinae (have no own category yet) -->\n[[Category:Egyptian artefact types]]\n[[Category:Egyptian hieroglyphs]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n[[Category:Polyphyletic groups]]\n[[Category:Insect common names]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Informal group of insects}}\n{{other uses}}\n{{Paraphyletic group\n| name = Dung beetle\n| image = Scarabaeus viettei 01.jpg\n| image_alt = Scarabaeus viettei (syn. Madateuchus viettei, Scarabaeidae) in dry spiny forest close to Mangily, western Madagascar\n| image_caption = ''{{ill|Scarabaeus viettei|sv}}'' (syn. ''Madateuchus viettei'', [[Scarabaeidae]]) in [[Madagascar spiny forests|dry spiny forest]] close to [[Mangily]], western [[Madagascar]]\n| auto = yes\n| parent = Scarabaeoidea\n| includes = \n*[[Geotrupidae]]\n*[[Scarabaeinae]]\n*[[Aphodiinae]]\n| excludes = \n*[[Termitoderini]]\n}}\n\n'''Dung beetles''' are [[beetle]]s that [[coprophagia|feed]] on [[feces]] (dung). Beetles in some species of dung beetles can bury dung 250 times their own mass in one night.<ref>{{cite web|title=Some Less Known Fascinating Facts about Dung Beetle|url=http://news.biharprabha.com/2014/04/some-less-known-fascinating-facts-about-dung-beetle/|work=IANS|publisher=news.biharprabha.com|accessdate=21 April 2014}}</ref>\n\nMany dung beetles, known as ''rollers'', roll dung into round balls, which are used as a food source or breeding chambers. Others, known as ''tunnelers'', bury the dung wherever they find it. A third group, the ''dwellers'', neither roll nor burrow: they simply live in manure. They are often attracted by the dung collected by [[burrowing owl]]s. There are dung beetle species of different colours and sizes, and some functional traits such as body mass (or biomass) and leg length can have high levels of variability.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite journal|last=Griffiths|first=Hannah M.|last2=Louzada|first2=Julio|last3=Bardgett|first3=Richard D.|last4=Barlow|first4=Jos|date=2016-03-03|title=Assessing the Importance of Intraspecific Variability in Dung Beetle Functional Traits|journal=PLOS ONE|volume=11|issue=3|pages=e0145598|doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0145598|pmid=26939121|pmc=4777568|issn=1932-6203|bibcode=2016PLoSO..1145598G}}</ref>\n\nAll the [[species]] belong to the superfamily [[Scarabaeoidea]], most of them to the subfamilies [[Scarabaeinae]] and [[Aphodiinae]] of the family [[Scarabaeidae]] (scarab beetles). As most species of Scarabaeinae feed exclusively on feces, that subfamily is often dubbed ''true dung beetles''. There are dung-feeding beetles which belong to other families, such as the [[Geotrupidae]] (the ''earth-boring dung beetle''). The Scarabaeinae alone comprises more than 5,000 species.<ref>Frolov, A.V. [http://www.zin.ru/animalia/coleoptera/eng/afrsc_ru.htm \"Subfamily Scarabaeinae: atlas of representatives of the tribes (Scarabaeidae)\"]. Retrieved on 2007-08-02.</ref>\n\nThe nocturnal African dung beetle ''[[Scarabaeus satyrus]]'' is one of the few known non-vertebrate animals that navigate and orient themselves using the [[Milky Way]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-21150721|author=Jonathan Amos|title=Dung beetles guided by Milky Way|publisher=[[BBC News]]|date=24 January 2013|accessdate=28 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Dacke | first1 = M. | last2 = Baird | first2 = E. | last3 = Byrne | first3 = M. | last4 = Scholtz | first4 = C. H. | last5 = Warrant | first5 = E. J. | title = Dung Beetles Use the Milky Way for Orientation | doi = 10.1016/j.cub.2012.12.034 | journal = Current Biology | volume = 23 | issue = 4 | pages = 298\u2013300 | year = 2013 | pmid =  23352694| pmc = | doi-access = free }}</ref>\n\n==Taxonomy==\nDung beetles are not a single taxonomic group; dung feeding is found in a number of families of beetles, so the behaviour cannot be assumed to have evolved only once.\n* [[Coleoptera]] (order), beetles\n** [[Scarabaeoidea]] (superfamily), scarabs (most families in the group do not use dung)\n*** [[Geotrupidae]] (family), \"earth-boring dung beetles\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Geotrupidae (earth-boring dung beetles)|url=http://www.kerbtier.de/cgi-bin/enFSearch.cgi?Fam=Geotrupidae|publisher=kerbtier.de|accessdate=28 March 2015}}</ref>\n*** [[Scarabaeidae]] (family), \"scarab beetles\" (not all species use dung)\n**** [[Scarabaeinae]] (subfamily), \"true dung beetles\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Scarabaeinae dung beetles|url=http://scarabaeinae.lifedesks.org/|accessdate=28 March 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150319101341/http://scarabaeinae.lifedesks.org/|archive-date=2015-03-19|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n**** [[Aphodiinae]] (subfamily), \"small dung beetles\" (not all species use dung)<ref name=skelley>Skelley, P. E. [http://museum.unl.edu/research/entomology/Guide/Scarabaeoidea/Scarabaeidae/Aphodiinae/Aphodiinae-Overview/AphodiinaeO.html Aphodiinae.] ''Generic Guide to New World Scarab Beetles.'' University of Nebraska State Museum. 2008 Version.</ref>\nSystematic Position:\n  Kingdom                        Animalia \n      Phylum                           Arthropoda \n           Subphylum                          Hexapoda \n                  Class                              Insecta \n                          Order                             Coleoptera \n                                    Suborder                     Polyphaga\n                                            Superfamily                Scarabaeoidea \n                                                       Family                   Scarabaeidae\n                              \u2191                                                        (Latreille, 1802)\n\n==Ecology and behavior==\n[[File:Dung beetle working-001.ogv|thumb|Dung beetle rolling a ball of dung in the [[Addo Elephant National Park]], [[South Africa]]]]\n\nDung beetles live in many [[habitat]]s, including desert, [[grassland]]s and [[savanna]]s,<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Fran\u00e7a|first=Filipe M.|last2=Korasaki|first2=Vanesca|last3=Louzada|first3=Julio|last4=Vaz-de-Mello|first4=Fernando Z.|last5=Fran\u00e7a|first5=Filipe M.|last6=Korasaki|first6=Vanesca|last7=Louzada|first7=Julio|last8=Vaz-de-Mello|first8=Fernando Z.|date=2016|title=First report on dung beetles in intra-Amazonian savannahs in Roraima, Brazil|journal=Biota Neotropica|volume=16|issue=1|doi=10.1590/1676-0611-BN-2015-0034|issn=1676-0603|doi-access=free}}</ref> [[farm]]lands, and native and planted [[forest]]s.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Beiroz|first=Wallace|last2=Slade|first2=Eleanor M.|last3=Barlow|first3=Jos|last4=Silveira|first4=Juliana M.|last5=Louzada|first5=Julio|last6=Sayer|first6=Emma|date=2017-01-01|title=Dung beetle community dynamics in undisturbed tropical forests: implications for ecological evaluations of land-use change|journal=Insect Conservation and Diversity|language=en|volume=10|issue=1|pages=94\u2013106|doi=10.1111/icad.12206|issn=1752-4598|url=http://eprints.lancs.ac.uk/83810/1/BeirozEtAlPreprint.pdf}}</ref> They are highly influenced by the environmental context,<ref name=\":0\" /> and do not prefer extremely cold or dry weather. They are found on all continents except [[Antarctica]]. They eat the dung of [[herbivore]]s and [[omnivore]]s, and prefer that produced by the latter.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dell'Amore|first1=Christine|title=Dung Beetles' Favorite Poop Revealed|url=http://voices.nationalgeographic.com/2012/04/17/weird-wild-dung-beetles-favorite-poop-revealed/|website=National Geographic|publisher=National Geographic Society|accessdate=22 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923045212/http://voices.nationalgeographic.com/2012/04/17/weird-wild-dung-beetles-favorite-poop-revealed/|archive-date=2016-09-23|url-status=dead}}</ref> Many of them also feed on [[mushrooms]] and [[decomposition|decaying]] [[leaf|leaves]] and [[fruit]]s. One type living in Central America, ''[[Deltochilum valgum]]'', is a carnivore preying upon [[millipedes]]. Dung beetles do not necessarily have to eat or drink anything else, because the dung provides all the necessary [[nutrient]]s.{{Citation needed|date=August 2019}}\n\nMost dung beetles search for dung using their sensitive [[olfaction|sense of smell]]. Some smaller species simply attach themselves to the dung-providers to wait for the dung. After capturing the dung, a dung beetle rolls it, following a straight line despite all obstacles. Sometimes, dung beetles try to steal the dung ball from another beetle, so the dung beetles have to move rapidly away from a dung pile once they have rolled their ball to prevent it from being stolen. Dung beetles can roll up to 10 times their weight. Male ''Onthophagus taurus'' beetles can pull 1,141 times their own body weight: the equivalent of an average person pulling six double-decker buses full of people.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2010/mar/24/dung-beetles | location=London | work=The Guardian | first=Homa | last=Khaleeli | title=Just how strong is a dung beetle? | date=24 March 2010}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Scarabaeus laticollis 2.jpg|thumb|left|Two dung beetles fighting over a ball of dung]]\n\nA species of dung beetle (the African ''Scarabaeus zambesianus'') [[animal navigation|navigates]] by [[Polarization (waves)|polarization]] patterns in [[moonlight]],{{Sfn|Tills|2013|p=123}}  the first animal known to do so.<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1038/424033a| pmid = 12840748| title = Animal behaviour: Insect orientation to polarized moonlight| journal = Nature| volume = 424| issue = 6944| page = 33| year = 2003| last1 = Dacke | first1 = M. | last2 = Nilsson | first2 = D. E. | last3 = Scholtz | first3 = C. H. | last4 = Byrne | first4 = M. | last5 = Warrant | first5 = E. J. | bibcode=2003Natur.424...33D}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Milius | first1 = Susan | year = 2003 | title = Moonlighting: Beetles navigate by lunar polarity | url = http://www.sciencenews.org/articles/20030705/fob4.asp | journal = Science News | volume = 164 | issue = 1| pages = 4\u20135 | doi = 10.2307/3981988 | jstor = 3981988 }}</ref><ref>Roach, John (2003). [http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2003/07/0702_030702_dungbeetle.html \"Dung Beetles Navigate by the Moon, Study Says\"], ''National Geographic News''. Retrieved on 2007-08-02.</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.2307/3981988| jstor = 3981988| title = Moonlighting| journal = Science News| volume = 164| issue = 1| pages = 4\u20135| year = 2003| last1 = Milius | first1 = S. }}</ref> Dung beetles can also navigate when only the [[Milky Way]] or clusters of bright stars are visible,<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite journal |doi=10.1016/j.cub.2012.12.034|pmid=23352694|title=Dung Beetles Use the Milky Way for Orientation|journal=Current Biology|volume=23|issue=4|pages=298|year=2013|last1=Dacke|first1=Marie|last2=Baird|first2=Emily|last3=Byrne|first3=Marcus|last4=Scholtz|first4=Clarke H.|last5=Warrant|first5=Eric J.|doi-access=free}}</ref>  making them the only insects known to orient themselves by the Milky Way.<ref name=\"scienceDaily\">{{cite news|last=Wits University |url=https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2013/01/130124123203.htm |title=Dung Beetles Follow the Milky Way: Insects Found to Use Stars for Orientation|work=ScienceDaily|date=24 January 2013 |accessdate=25 January 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\"/> The eyes of dung beetles are superposition [[Compound eye|compound eyes]] typical of many scarabaeid beetles;<ref>{{cite journal|author=Meyer-Rochow, V.B.|title=Retina and dioptric apparatus of the dung beetle ( Euoniticellus africanus ; Scarabaeidae)|journal=Journal of Insect Physiology|date=1978|volume= 24|issue=2|pages= 165\u2013179|doi=10.1016/0022-1910(78)90114-2}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal| author1=Meyer-Rochow, V.B.| author2= Gokan, N.| title=The eye of the dung beetle Onthophagus posticus (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae)| date=1990| journal= New Zealand Journal of Entomology| volume=13| pages=7\u201315| doi= 10.1080/00779962.1990.9722582}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Scarabaeus laticollis.jpg|thumb|upright|An earth-boring dung beetle working]]\n[[File:DungBeetle.jpg|thumb|A dung beetle with two balls of dung]]\n\nCambefort and Hanski (1991) classified dung beetles into three functional types based on their feeding and nesting strategies such as \u2013 Rollers, Tunnelers and Dwellers. The \"rollers\" roll and bury a dung ball either for food storage or for making a brooding ball. In the latter case, two beetles, one male and one female, stay around the dung ball during the rolling process. Usually it is the male that rolls the ball, while the female hitch-hikes or simply follows behind. In some cases, the male and the female roll together. When a spot with soft soil is found, they stop and bury the  ball, then [[mating|mate]] underground. After the mating, one or both of them prepares the brooding ball. When the ball is finished, the female lays eggs inside it, a form of [[mass provisioning]].\n\nSome species do not leave after this stage, but remain to safeguard their offspring. The dung beetle goes through a complete [[metamorphosis (biology)|metamorphosis]]. The larvae live in brood balls made with dung prepared by their parents. During the larval stage, the beetle feeds on the dung surrounding it.\n\nThe behavior of the beetles was poorly understood until the studies of [[Jean Henri Fabre]] in the late 19th century. For example, Fabre corrected the myth that a dung beetle would seek aid from other dung beetles when confronted by obstacles. By observation and experiment, he found the seeming helpers were in fact awaiting an opportunity to steal the roller's food source.<ref>{{cite book |author=Fabre, J. Henri |authorlink = Henri Fabre |date=1949 |title=The Insect World of J. Henri Fabre |url=https://archive.org/details/insectworldofjhe0000fabr |url-access=registration |others=De Mattos, Alexander Teixeira (translator) |publisher=Dodd, Mead & Company |page=[https://archive.org/details/insectworldofjhe0000fabr/page/99 99] |quote=I ask myself in vain what Proudhon introduced into Scarabaean morality the daring paradox that 'property means plunder', or what diplomatist taught the Dung-beetle the savage maxim that 'might is right'.}}</ref>\n\nThey are widely used in ecological research as a good [[bioindicator]] group to examine the impacts of climate disturbances, such as extreme droughts <ref>{{Cite journal |doi = 10.1098/rstb.2019.0116|pmid = 31983328 |title = Climatic and local stressor interactions threaten tropical forests and coral reefs |journal = Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society B|volume = 375|issue = 1794 |pages = 20190116|year = 2020|last1 = Fran\u00e7a |first1 = FM|last2 = Benkwitt |first2 = CE|last3 = Peralta |first3 = G |last4 = Robinson |first4 = JPW|last5 = Graham|first5 =  NAJ |last6 = Tylianakis |first6 = JM|last7 = Berenguer |first7 = E |last8 = Lees |first8 = AC|last9 = Ferreira |first9 = J|last10 = Louzada |first10 = J |last11 = Barlow |first11 = J}}</ref> and associated fires <ref>{{Cite journal|last=Fran\u00e7a|first=Filipe|last2=Ferreira|first2=J| last3=Vaz-de-Mello|first3=FZ| last4=Maia|first4=LF| last5=Berenguer|first5=E| last6=Palmeira|first6=A| last7=Fadini|first7=R| last8=Louzada|first8=J |last9=Braga|first9=R| last10=Oliveira|first10=VH| last11=Barlow|first11=J| date=10 February 2020|title= El Ni\u00f1o impacts on human\u2010modified tropical forests: Consequences for dung beetle diversity and associated ecological processes |journal=Biotropica |volume=52 | issue = 1 |pages=1\u201311|doi=10.1111/btp.12756|doi-access=free}}</ref>, and human activities on tropical biodiversity <ref>{{Cite journal|last=Fran\u00e7a|first=Filipe|last2=Barlow|first2=Jos|last3=Ara\u00fajo|first3=B\u00e1rbara|last4=Louzada|first4=Julio|date=4 November 2016|title=Does selective logging stress tropical forest invertebrates? Using fat stores to examine sublethal responses in dung beetles|journal=Ecology and Evolution|volume=6 | issue = 23 |pages=8526\u20138533|doi=10.1002/ece3.2488|pmid=28031804|pmc=5167030}}</ref> and ecosystem functioning,<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Fran\u00e7a|first=Filipe M.|last2=Fraz\u00e3o|first2=F\u00e1bio S.|last3=Korasaki|first3=Vanesca|last4=Louzada|first4=J\u00falio|last5=Barlow|first5=Jos|date=2017-12-01|title=Identifying thresholds of logging intensity on dung beetle communities to improve the sustainable management of Amazonian tropical forests|journal=Biological Conservation|volume=216|issue=Supplement C|pages=115\u2013122|doi=10.1016/j.biocon.2017.10.014|url=https://eprints.lancs.ac.uk/id/eprint/88405/1/170918_Manuscript.pdf}}</ref> such as seed dispersal, soil bioturbation and nutrient cycling<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Fran\u00e7a|first=Filipe|last2=Ferreira|first2=J| last3=Vaz-de-Mello|first3=FZ| last4=Maia|first4=LF| last5=Berenguer|first5=E| last6=Palmeira|first6=A| last7=Fadini|first7=R| last8=Louzada|first8=J |last9=Braga|first9=R| last10=Oliveira|first10=VH| last11=Barlow|first11=J| date=10 February 2020|title= El Ni\u00f1o impacts on human\u2010modified tropical forests: Consequences for dung beetle diversity and associated ecological processes |journal=Biotropica |volume=52 | issue = 1 |pages=1\u201311|doi=10.1111/btp.12756|doi-access=free}}</ref>.\n\n==Benefits and uses==\n[[File:Caution Dung Beetles, South Africa.jpg|thumb|upright|Caution sign showing the importance of dung beetles in [[South Africa]]]]\n[[File:CSIRO ScienceImage 10743 Onitis aygulus.jpg|thumb|left|''Onitis aygulus'']]\n[[File:CSIRO ScienceImage 10809 Dung beetle Onthophagus nigriventris.jpg|thumb|left|''Onthophagus nigriventris'']]\nDung beetles play a role in [[agriculture]] and [[tropical forest]]s. By burying and consuming dung, they improve nutrient recycling and soil structure.<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1016/j.apsoil.2010.05.010| title = Dung beetles (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae) can improve soil hydrological properties| journal = Applied Soil Ecology| volume = 46| pages = 9\u201316| year = 2010| last1 = Brown | first1 = J. | last2 = Scholtz | first2 = C. H. | last3 = Janeau | first3 = J. L. | last4 = Grellier | first4 = S. | last5 = Podwojewski | first5 = P. | hdl = 2263/14419| url = http://repository.up.ac.za/bitstream/2263/14419/1/Brown_Dung%282010%29.pdf }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Nichols|first=E.|last2=Spector|first2=S.|last3=Louzada|first3=J.|last4=Larsen|first4=T.|last5=Amezquita|first5=S.|last6=Favila|first6=M.E.|title=Ecological functions and ecosystem services provided by Scarabaeinae dung beetles|journal=Biological Conservation|volume=141|issue=6|pages=1461\u20131474|doi=10.1016/j.biocon.2008.04.011|year=2008}}</ref> Dung beetles have been further shown to improve soil conditions and plant growth on rehabilitated coal mines in South Africa.<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1016/j.apsoil.2018.08.011| title = Dung beetle activity improves herbaceous plant growth and soil properties on confinements simulating reclaimed mined land in South Africa| journal = Applied Soil Ecology| volume = 132| pages = 53\u201359| year = 2018| last1 = Badenhorst | first1 = J. | last2 = Dabrowski | first2 = J. | last3 = Scholtz | first3 = C. H. | last4 = Truter | first4 = W. F. | hdl = 2263/67268 | hdl-access = free }}</ref> They are also important for the dispersal of seeds present in animals' dung, influencing seed burial and seedling recruitment in tropical forests.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Griffiths|first=Hannah M.|last2=Bardgett|first2=Richard D.|last3=Louzada|first3=Julio|last4=Barlow|first4=Jos|date=2016-12-14|title=The value of trophic interactions for ecosystem function: dung beetle communities influence seed burial and seedling recruitment in tropical forests|journal=Proc. R. Soc. B|language=en|volume=283|issue=1844|pages=20161634|doi=10.1098/rspb.2016.1634|issn=0962-8452|pmc=5204146|pmid=27928036}}</ref> They can protect livestock, such as [[cattle]], by removing the dung which, if left, could provide habitat for [[pest (animal)|pests]] such as [[fly|flies]]. Therefore, many countries have [[Biological pest control|introduced]] the creatures for the benefit of [[animal husbandry]]. In [[developing countries]], the beetles are especially important as an adjunct for improving standards of hygiene. The [[American Institute of Biological Sciences]] reports that dung beetles save the [[United States of America|United States]] cattle industry an estimated [[United States dollar|US$]]380 million annually through burying above-ground livestock feces.<ref>{{Cite journal| doi = 10.1641/0006-3568(2006)56[311:TEVOES]2.0.CO;2| title = The Economic Value of Ecological Services Provided by Insects| journal = BioScience| volume = 56| issue = 4| pages = 311\u201323| year = 2006| last1 = Losey| first1 = J. E.| last2 = Vaughan| first2 = M.| url = http://www.xerces.org/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/economic_value_insects.pdf| access-date = 2009-01-28| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180619202116/http://www.xerces.org/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/economic_value_insects.pdf| archive-date = 2018-06-19| url-status = dead}}</ref>\n\nIn Australia, the [[Commonwealth Scientific and Industrial Research Organisation]] (CSIRO) commissioned the [[Australian Dung Beetle Project]] (1965\u20131985) which, led by [[George Bornemissza]], sought to introduce species of dung beetles from South Africa and Europe. The successful introduction of 23 species was made, most notably ''[[Digitonthophagus gazella]]'' and ''[[Euoniticellus intermedius]]'', which has resulted in improvement of the quality and fertility of Australian cattle pastures, along with a reduction in the population of pestilent [[Musca vetustissima|bush flies]] by around 90 percent.<ref name=\"adbp\">{{cite journal | last1 = Bornemissza | first1 = G. F. | year = 1976 | title = The Australian dung beetle project 1965\u20131975 | url = | journal = Australian Meat Research Committee Review | volume = 30 | issue = | pages = 1\u201330 }}</ref><!---Missylisa153, August 2009--->\n\nAn application has been made by [[Landcare Research]] to import up to 11 species of dung beetle into [[New Zealand]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ermanz.govt.nz/BertDocs/ERMA200599_Application%20summary%20ERMA200599%20FINAL.pdf |title=Application summary \u2013 ERMA200599 |publisher=ERMA |accessdate=12 December 2010 }}{{dead link|date=September 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> As well as improving pasture soils the Dung Beetle Release Strategy Group say that it would result in a reduction in emissions of [[nitrous oxide]] (a [[greenhouse gas]]) from agriculture.<ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10675713 |title=Let's roll... dung beetle to combat global warming|last=Ihaka|first=James|date=24 September 2010|work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]|accessdate=12 December 2010}}</ref> There is, however, strong opposition from some at the [[University of Auckland]], and a few others, based on the risks of the dung beetles acting as vectors of disease.<ref>{{cite web |author=17 Aug 2014, 01:09 am |url=http://www.fwplus.co.nz/article/experts-dump-on-dung-beetle?p=6 |title=Experts dump on dung beetle |publisher=Fwplus.co.nz |date=2012-05-07 |accessdate=2014-08-16 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130414001314/http://www.fwplus.co.nz/article/experts-dump-on-dung-beetle?p=6 |archivedate=2013-04-14 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/environment/news/article.cfm?c_id=39&objectid=10866149 |title=Grant Guilford: Dung beetle plan a risky gamble |publisher=Nzherald.co.nz |date= 2013-02-18|accessdate=2014-08-16|newspaper=NZ Herald |last1=Guilford |first1=Grant }}</ref> There are public health researchers at the University of Auckland who agree with the current EPA risk assessment <ref>{{Cite journal|author=drj9 |url=http://janinepaynter.wordpress.com/2013/03/17/fickle-thy-name-is-vox-populi-puzzle-over-dung-beetles-and-science-reporting/ |title='Fickle thy name is' vox populi : puzzle over dung beetles and science reporting   |journal =Journal of Outrageous Speculation |date=2013-03-17 |accessdate=2014-04-22}}</ref> and indeed there are several Landcare programmes in Australia that involve schoolchildren collecting dung beetles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dungbeetle.org.nz/release-programme/ |title=Release Programme &#124; Dung Beetles in New Zealand |publisher=Dungbeetle.org.nz |date=2013-09-26 |accessdate=2014-04-22}}</ref>\n\nThe African dung beetle, ''D. gazella'', was introduced in several locations in North and [[South America]] and has been spreading its distribution to other regions by natural dispersal and accidental transportation, and is now probably naturalized in most countries between [[M\u00e9xico]] and [[Argentina]]. The exotic species might be useful for controlling diseases of [[livestock]] in commercial areas, and might displace native species in modified landscapes, however data is not conclusive about its effect on native species in natural environments and further monitoring is required.<ref name=DgazellaVenezuela>{{cite journal|last1=Ferrer-Paris|first1=Jos\u00e9 R.|title=El escarabajo estercolero africano, ''Digitonthophagus gazella'', (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae) en la regi\u00f3n Neotropical, \u00bfbeneficioso o perjudicial?|journal=Bolet\u00edn de la Red Latinoamericana Para el Estudio de Especies Invasoras|date=2014|volume=4|issue=1|pages=41\u201348|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/268510737}}</ref>\n\nLike many other insects, the (dried) dung beetle, called ''qianglang'' (\u8723\u870b) in Chinese, is used in [[Chinese materia medica|Chinese herbal medicine]]. It is recorded in the \"Insect section\" (\u87f2\u90e8) of the ''[[Bencao Gangmu|Compendium of Materia Medica]]'', where it is recommended for the cure of 10 diseases.{{cn|date=December 2019}}\n\nIn [[Isan]], Northeastern Thailand, the local people famously eat many different kinds of insects including the dung beetle. There is an Isan song \u0e01\u0e38\u0e14\u0e08\u0e35\u0e48\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e22\u0e44\u0e1b\u0e43\u0e2b\u0e19 \"Where did the Dung Beetle go\", which relates the replacement of [[water buffalo]] with the \"metal\" buffalo, which does not provide the dung needed for the dung beetle and has led to the increasing rarity of the dung beetle in the agricultural region.\n\nMediterranean dung beetles (''Bubas bison'') have been used in conjunction with [[Biochar#Stock_fodder|biochar stock fodder]] to reduce emissions of [[Nitrous_oxide#Greenhouse_effect|nitrous oxide]] and [[Carbon_dioxide#In_Earth's_atmosphere|carbon dioxide]], which are both greenhouse gases. The beetles work the biochar-enriched dung into the soil without the use of machines.<ref name=\"abc.net.au-2019-10-18-beetles-charcoal\">{{cite web\n | url =https://www.abc.net.au/news/rural/2019-10-18/wa-farmer-uses-beetles-and-charcoal-to-combat-climate-change/11613846\n | title =Poo-eating beetles and charcoal used by WA farmer to combat climate change\n | last =Daly\n | first =Jon\n | date =18 October 2019\n | website =ABC.net.au\n | publisher =Australian Broadcasting Corporation\n | access-date =18 October 2019\n | quote =Mr Pow said his innovative farming system could help livestock producers become more profitable while helping to address the impact of climate change. }}</ref>\n\n==Scarab in ancient Egypt==\n{{Main|Scarab (artifact)}}\n[[File:Karnak temple scarab beetle A.jpg|thumb|right|A scarab statue at the [[Karnak]] temple complex]]\n\nSeveral species of the dung beetle, most notably the species ''[[Scarabaeus sacer]]'' (often referred to as ''the sacred scarab''), enjoyed a sacred status among the [[ancient Egypt]]ians.\n{{hiero|\u1e2bpr|<hiero>xpr</hiero>|align=right|era=egypt}}Egyptian hieroglyphic script uses the image of the beetle to represent a [[Egyptian language|triliteral phonetic]] that Egyptologists transliterate as ''xpr'' or ''\u1e2bpr'' and translate as \"to come into being\", \"to become\" or \"to transform\". The derivative term ''xprw'' or ''\u1e2bpr(w)'' is variously translated as \"form\", \"transformation\", \"happening\", \"mode of being\" or \"what has come into being\", depending on the context. It may have existential, fictional, or ontologic significance.\n\nThe scarab was linked to [[Khepri]] (\"he who has come into being\"), the god of the rising [[sun]]. The ancients believed that the dung beetle was only male in gender, and reproduced by depositing [[semen]] into a dung ball. The supposed self-creation of the beetle resembles that of Khepri, who creates himself out of nothing. Moreover, the dung ball rolled by a dung beetle resembles the sun. [[Plutarch]] wrote: {{quote|The race of beetles has no female, but all the males eject their sperm into a round pellet of material which they roll up by pushing it from the opposite side, just as the sun seems to turn the heavens in the direction opposite to its own course, which is from west to east.<ref>[http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Isis_and_Osiris*/E.html#ref373 \"Isis and Osiris\"], ''Moralia'', in volume V of the [[Loeb Classical Library]] edition, 1936, now in the public domain. Retrieved on 2007-08-02.</ref>}}\n\nThe ancient Egyptians believed that Khepri renewed the sun every day before rolling it above the horizon, then carried it through the other world after sunset, only to renew it, again, the next day. Some [[New Kingdom]] royal tombs exhibit a threefold image of the sun god, with the beetle as symbol of the morning sun. The astronomical ceiling in the tomb of [[Ramses VI]] portrays the nightly \"death\" and \"rebirth\" of the sun as being swallowed by [[Nut (goddess)|Nut]], goddess of the sky, and re-emerging from her womb as Khepri.\n\nThe image of the scarab, conveying ideas of transformation, renewal, and resurrection, is ubiquitous in ancient Egyptian religious and [[funerary art]].\n\nExcavations of ancient Egyptian sites have yielded images of the scarab in bone, [[ivory]], stone, [[Egyptian faience]], and precious metals, dating from the Sixth Dynasty and up to the period of Roman rule. They are generally small, bored to allow stringing on a necklace, and the base bears a brief inscription or [[cartouche]]. Some have been used as [[Impression seal|seals]]. [[Pharaoh]]s sometimes commissioned the manufacture of larger images with lengthy inscriptions, such as the [[The lion hunts of Amenhotep III during the first ten years of his reign|commemorative scarab]] of Queen [[Tiye]]. Massive sculptures of scarabs can be seen at [[Luxor Temple]], at the Serapeum in Alexandria (see [[Serapis]]) and elsewhere in Egypt.\n\n[[File:Egypt.KV6.04.jpg|thumb|left|A scarab, depicted on the walls of [[KV6|Tomb KV6]] in the [[Valley of the Kings]]]]\n\nThe scarab was of prime significance in the funerary cult of ancient Egypt. Scarabs, generally, though not always, were cut from green stone, and placed on the chest of the deceased. Perhaps the most famous example of such \"heart scarabs\" is the yellow-green [[pectoral (Ancient Egypt)|pectoral]] scarab found among the entombed provisions of [[Tutankhamen]]. It was carved from a large piece of [[Libyan desert glass]]. The purpose of the \"heart scarab\" was to ensure that the heart would not bear witness against the deceased at judgement in the Afterlife. Other possibilities are suggested by the \"transformation spells\" of the ''Coffin Texts'', which affirm that the soul of the deceased may transform (''xpr'') into a human being, a god, or a bird and reappear in the world of the living.\n\nOne scholar comments on other traits of the scarab connected with the theme of death and rebirth:\n{{quote|It may not have gone unnoticed that the pupa, whose wings and legs are encased at this stage of development, is very mummy-like. It has even been pointed out that the egg-bearing ball of dung is created in an underground chamber which is reached by a vertical shaft and horizontal passage curiously reminiscent of Old Kingdom mastaba tombs.\"<ref>Andrews, Carol (1994). ''Amulets of Ancient Egypt''. Texas: University of Texas Press. {{ISBN|0-292-70464-X}}. p. 51.</ref>}}\n\nIn contrast to funerary contexts, some of ancient Egypt's neighbors adopted the scarab motif for [[scaraboid seal|seals]] of varying types. The best-known of these being Judean [[LMLK seal]]s (8 of 21 designs contained scarab beetles), which were used exclusively to stamp impressions on storage jars during the reign of [[Hezekiah]].\n\nThe scarab remains an item of popular interest thanks to modern fascination with the art and beliefs of ancient Egypt. Scarab beads in semiprecious stones or glazed ceramics can be purchased at most bead shops, while at Luxor Temple a massive ancient scarab has been roped off to discourage visitors from rubbing the base of the statue \"for luck\".\n\n==In culture==\nSome dung beetles are used as food in South East Asia and a variety of dung beetle species have been used [[therapeutically]] (and are still being used in traditionally living societies) in potions and folk medicines to treat a number of illnesses and disorders.<ref>{{cite journal |last=Meyer-Rochow | first=V.B. |title=Therapeutic arthropods and other, largely terrestrial, folk-medicinally important invertebrates: a comparative survey and review. |journal=Journal of Ethnobiology and Ethnomedicine| date=January 2017| volume=13 |issue=9 |pages=9| doi=10.1186/s13002-017-0136-0| pmid=28173820 | pmc=5296966 }}</ref>\n\n===In literature===\nIn [[Aesop's fable]] \"[[The Eagle and the Beetle]]\", the eagle kills a hare that has asked for sanctuary with a beetle. The beetle then takes revenge by twice destroying the eagle's eggs. The eagle, in despair, flies up to [[Mount Olympus|Olympus]] and places her latest eggs in [[Zeus]]'s lap, beseeching the god to protect them. When the beetle finds out what the eagle has done, it stuffs itself with dung, goes straight up to Zeus and flies right into his face. Zeus is startled at the sight of the unpleasant creature, jumping to his feet so that the eggs are broken. Learning of the origin of their feud, Zeus attempts to mediate and, when his efforts to mediate fail, he changes the breeding season of the eagle to a time when the beetles are not above ground.\n\n[[Aristophanes]] alluded to Aesop's fable several times in his plays. In ''[[Peace (play)|Peace]]'', the hero rides up to Olympus to free the goddess Peace from her prison. His steed is an enormous dung beetle which has been fed so much dung that it has grown to monstrous size.\n\n[[Hans Christian Andersen]]'s \"The Dung Beetle\" tells the story of a dung beetle who lives in the stable of the king's horses in an imaginary kingdom. When he demands golden shoes like those the king's horse wears and is refused, he flies away and has a series of adventures, which are often precipitated by his [[Superiority complex|feeling of superiority]] to other animals. He finally returns to the stable having decided (against all logic) that it is for him that the king's horse wears golden shoes.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Andersen|first1=Hans Christian|last2=James|first2=M. R. (trans.)|work=Hans Andersen Forty-Two Stories | title=The Beetle |date=1930 |publisher=Faber and Faber |url=https://fadedpage.com/showbook.php?pid=20100119}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Franz Kafka]]'s ''[[The Metamorphosis]]'', the transformed character of Gregor Samsa is called an \"old dung beetle\" (''alter Mistk\u00e4fer'') by a [[charwoman]] (Samsa is, in fact, a [[cockroach]]).\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|Insects}}\n* ''[[Catharsius]]'', an important dung beetle genus in African and Asian environments\n* [[Addo Elephant National Park]], site of the largest remaining population of the endangered flightless dung beetle (''Circellium bacchus'').\n* [[List of dung beetle and chafer (Scarabaeoidea) species recorded in Britain]]\n* [[Rotating locomotion in living systems]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n== Book sources ==\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{citation|title=Sciene Year|first=Tony |last=Tills|publisher=World Book,Inc.|year=2013|isbn=9780716605676}}\n\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikispecies|Scarabaeinae}}\n{{wikispecies|Aphodiinae}}\n{{Commons category|Dung beetles}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20121105033930/http://www.cosmosmagazine.com/features/online/5803/on-a-roll Feature: 'What to do with too much poo'] \u2013 The success story behind the introduction of dung beetles in Australia at cosmosmagazine.com\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20161018110844/http://www.insects.org/ced1/beetles_rel_sym.html Beetles as religious symbols] at insects.org\n* [http://www.scarabnet.org/ Scarabaeinae Research Network]\n* [http://www.amonline.net.au/factsheets/dung-beetles.htm Dung beetles] at the Australia Museum\n* [http://www.catharsius.fr/ Catharsius], an international group working on taxonomy and ecology of Western African dung beetles\n* Tomas Libich, [http://www.goliathus.com/en/en-dung-beetle.html Congo dung beetle sp1] and [http://www.goliathus.com/en/en-dung-beetle-2.html Congo dung beetle sp2] photos\n* [https://archive.is/20130416051320/http://www.wild.org/video/i-brake-for-dung-beetles/ Dung Beetles in action (video)] by The WILD Foundation/Boyd Norton\n* [http://www.dungbeetle.org.nz/ Dung Beetles in New Zealand] (proposed release of dung beetles, with background research)\n* [http://www.ted.com/talks/marcus_byrne_the_dance_of_the_dung_beetle.html Marcus Byrne The dance of the dung beetle] Ted conference about dung beetle behavior.\n* [http://www.dungbeetles.com.au Dung Beetle Ecosystem Engineers] Dung Beetle Ecosystem Engineers \u2013 expanding the range of dung beetles in Australia and analysing their performance for livestock producers.\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Coprophagous insects]]\n<!-- [[Category:Scarabaeinae]] -->\n[[Category:Scarabaeidae]]<!-- for Aphodiinae (have no own category yet) -->\n[[Category:Egyptian artefact types]]\n[[Category:Egyptian hieroglyphs]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n[[Category:Polyphyletic groups]]\n[[Category:Insect common names]]\n", "name_user": "72.217.57.6", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dung_beetle"}
{"title_page": "Nemanja Nikoli\u0107 (footballer, born 1987)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{distinguish|Nemanja Nikoli\u0107 (footballer, born 1988)}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Nemanja Nikoli\u0107\n| image          = CINvCHI 2017-06-28 - Nemanja Nikoli\u0107 (39393300370) (cropped).jpg\n| image_size     = 200\n| caption        = Nikoli\u0107 with the [[Chicago Fire Soccer Club|Chicago Fire]] in 2017\n| fullname       = Nemanja Nikoli\u0107\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1987|12|31|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Senta]], [[SFR Yugoslavia]]\n| height         = 1.80 m<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vidi.hu/jatekosok/nikolics-nemanja.html|title=Nikolics Nemanja - vidi.hu|website=Vidi.hu|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n| currentclub    = [[Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r FC|Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r]]\n| clubnumber     = 71\n| position       = [[Forward (association football)#Striker|Striker]]\n| youthyears1 = 1996\u20132006\n| youthclubs1 = [[FK Senta|Senta]]\n| years1 = 2006\u20132007\n| clubs1 = [[Barcsi SC|Barcs]]\n| caps1 = 19\n| goals1 = 3\n| years2 = 2007\u20132008\n| clubs2 = [[Kaposv\u00f6lgye VSC|Kaposv\u00f6lgye]]\n| caps2 = 14\n| goals2 = 11\n| years3 = 2008\u20132010\n| clubs3 = [[Kaposv\u00e1ri R\u00e1k\u00f3czi FC|Kaposv\u00e1r]]\n| caps3 = 49\n| goals3 = 30\n| years4 = 2010\u20132015\n| clubs4 = [[Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r FC|Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r]]\n| caps4 = 149\n| goals4 = 87\n| years5 = 2015\u20132016\n| clubs5 = [[Legia Warsaw]]\n| caps5 = 56\n| goals5 = 40\n| years6 = 2016\u20132019\n| clubs6 = [[Chicago Fire Soccer Club|Chicago Fire]]\n| caps6 = 96\n| goals6 = 51\n| years7 = 2020\u2013\n| clubs7 = [[Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r FC|Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r]]\n| caps7 = 6\n| goals7= 2\n| club-update = 14 March 2020\n| nationalyears1 = 2013\u20132018\n| nationalteam1 = [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 27\n| nationalgoals1 = 5\n| nationalteam-update = {{date|2018-3-27}}\n}}\n\n'''Nemanja Nikoli\u0107''' ({{lang-sr-Cyrl|\u041d\u0435\u043c\u0430\u045a\u0430 \u041d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0438\u045b}} {{IPA-sh|n\u011bma\u0272a n\u01d0kolit\u0255|}}; {{lang-hu|Nikolics Nemanja}}; born 31 December 1987) is a Yugoslav-born Hungarian footballer who last played as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]] for [[Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I]] club [[Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r FC|Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r]]. Born in [[Socialist Republic of Serbia|Serbia]], but never selected for the [[Serbia national football team|Serbian national team]], he chose to represent the [[Hungary national football team|Hungarian national team]] instead.<ref>{{cite news|script-title=sr:\u0415\u043a\u0441\u043a\u043b\u0443\u0437\u0438\u0432\u043d\u043e, \u041d\u0435\u043c\u0430\u045a\u0430 \u041d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0438\u045b, \u0440\u0435\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0446 \u041c\u0430\u0452\u0430\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0435: \u041d\u0438\u043a\u043e \u043c\u0435 \u0438\u0437 \u0424\u0421\u0421 \u043d\u0438\u0458\u0435 \u0433\u043b\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043e!|url=http://www.zurnal.rs/fudbal/evropsko-prvenstvo/35736/ekskluzivno-nemanja-nikolic-reprezentativac-madjarske-niko-me-iz-fss-nije-gledao|accessdate=20 June 2016|work=zurnal.rs|date=20 June 2016|language=Serbian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Jovanovi\u0107|first1=Jovan|title=Pri\u010da dana Ma\u0111arski reprezentativac Nemanja Nikoli\u0107 otvorio du\u0161u za \"Sport\"|url=http://www.sport.org.rs/940-madarski-reprezentativac-nemanja-nikolic-otvorio-dusu-za-sport/|accessdate=20 June 2016|work=sport.rs|agency=Dnevni list Sport|language=Serbian|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160916204157/http://www.sport.org.rs/940-madarski-reprezentativac-nemanja-nikolic-otvorio-dusu-za-sport/|archivedate=16 September 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nNikoli\u0107 was born in [[Senta]], [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|Yugoslavia]] to a [[Serbs|Serbian]] father and a [[Hungarians|Hungarian]] mother. He began his career with his brother at [[FK Senta]].\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Kaposv\u00e1r===\n[[File:Nemanja Nikoli\u0107.JPG|thumb|150px|right|Nikoli\u0107 with [[Videoton FC|Videoton]] in 2010]]\nOn 7 February 2008, Nikoli\u0107 was signed by [[Kaposv\u00e1ri R\u00e1k\u00f3czi FC|Kaposv\u00e1r]]. He played his first match against [[Videoton FC|Videoton]]. He managed to score thirty goals in just 49 matches therefore many top Hungarian sides wanted to sign him such as [[\u00dajpest FC|\u00dajpest]], [[Ferencv\u00e1rosi TC|Ferencv\u00e1ros]] and [[Videoton FC|Videoton]].\n\n===Videoton===\nIn 2010 [[Videoton FC|Videoton]] signed Nikoli\u0107. He became top scorer in the [[2009\u201310 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2009\u201310]] season of the [[Hungarian League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/association=hun/news/newsid=1485621.html|title=Nikoli\u0107 thriving in Videoton spotlight|date=6 May 2010|publisher=UEFA}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/association=hun/news/newsid=1503384.html|title=Season review: Hungary|date=9 July 2010|publisher=UEFA}}</ref>\n\nNikoli\u0107 won the [[2010\u201311 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2010\u201311]] season of the Hungarian League with [[Videoton FC|Videoton]]. With the arrival of the Portuguese coach [[Paulo Sousa]] he was often left out from the first squad in the early matches of the [[2011\u201312 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2011\u201312]] season of the [[Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|Hungarian League]]. However, as a substitute he managed to score against [[Paksi SE|Paks]], [[Si\u00f3fok KC|Si\u00f3fok]] (twice), [[\u00dajpest FC|\u00dajpest]] (twice) and [[Lombard-P\u00e1pa TFC|P\u00e1pa]] in a row in the Hungarian League.\n\nOn 2 August 2012, Nikoli\u0107 scored the only goal of the first leg of the third round of the [[Europa league 2012\u201313]] season, when Videoton beat the Belgian [[K.A.A. Gent]] 1\u20130 at the S\u00f3st\u00f3i Stadion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2013/matches/round=2000354/match=2009771/index.html|title=UEFA Europa League 2012\u201313: Videoton 1\u20130 KAA Gent|date=2 August 2012|publisher=UEFA}}</ref> He also scored in the second leg of the tie which was won by 3\u20130 by Videoton at the [[Jules Ottenstadion]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2013/matches/round=2000354/match=2009800/index.html|title=UEFA Europa League 2012\u201313: KAA Gent 0\u20133 Videoton|date=9 August 2012|publisher=UEFA}}</ref> On 4 September 2012, he scored a goal in the [[Europa league 2012\u201313]] season when [[Videoton FC|Videoton]] beat Portugal's [[Sporting Clube de Portugal|Sporting CP]] 3\u20130 at [[Stadion Sostoi|Stadion S\u00f3st\u00f3i]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2013/matches/round=2000356/match=2009928/postmatch/report/index.html#videoton+stun+sporting|title=UEFA Europa League 2012\u201313: Paulo Sousa's Videoton stun Sporting|date=4 October 2012|publisher=UEFA}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/19839286|title=Europa League round-up: Lazio and Inter win, but Napoli defeated|date=4 October 2012|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 October 2014, Nikoli\u0107 set a new record scoring in 12 consecutive league matches in the 2014\u201315 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/labdarugo_nb_i/nikolics-europa-rekorder-a-dvtk-es-az-otthon-kapott-harmasok-2372573|title=Nikolics Eur\u00f3pa-rekorder! A DVTK \u00e9s az otthon kapott h\u00e1rmasok|date=27 October 2014|publisher=[[Nemzeti Sport]]}}</ref>\n\n===Legia Warsaw===\nOn 8 June 2015, Nikoli\u0107 joined [[Ekstraklasa]] club, [[Legia Warsaw]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Nemanja Nikoli\u0107 pi\u0142karzem Legii [Nemanja Nikoli\u0107 is a Legia player]|url=http://legia.com/aktualnosci/nemanja-nikolic-pilkarzem-legii-47054|accessdate=8 June 2015|language=Polish|date=8 June 2015}}</ref> On 19 July 2015, Nikoli\u0107 debuted in the [[2015\u201316 Ekstraklasa|2015\u201316]] season of the [[Ekstraklasa]] by scoring two goals against [[\u015al\u0105sk Wroc\u0142aw]] at the [[Stadion Miejski (Wroc\u0142aw)|Stadion Miejski]], [[Wroc\u0142aw]].<ref>{{cite web|title=\u015al\u0105sk Wroc\u0142aw 1-4 Legia Warsaw|url=http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/association=pol/domesticleague/season=2016/matches/match=200155204/live/index.html|publisher=[[UEFA.com]]|date=19 July 2015}}</ref> On 16 March 2016 Nikolic scored a [[hat-trick]] against [[Zawisza Bydgoszcz]] at the Pepsi Arena, [[Warsaw]]. The match ended with a 4\u20130 win for Legia Warsaw.<ref>{{cite web|title=Legia Warsaw 4-0 Zawisza Bydgoszcz|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2016/03/16/poland/cup/kp-legia-warsaw/sp-zawisza-bydgoszcz/2178120/|publisher=[[UEFA.com]]|date=16 March 2016}}</ref> On 15 May 2016 Legia became champions of the [[2015\u201316 Ekstraklasa]] season by beating [[Pogo\u0144 Szczecin]] 3\u20130 at home. He was the top scorer of the [[2015\u201316 Ekstraklasa]] season, scoring 28 goals in 37 matches.<ref name=\"sw\">{{cite web|title=N. Nikolics|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/nemanja-nikolic/33875/|website=Soccerway.com|date=16 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Chicago Fire===\n\nNikoli\u0107 joined the [[Chicago Fire Soccer Club|Chicago Fire]] as a [[Designated Player Rule|Designated Player]] for a reported transfer fee of $3 million from [[Legia Warsaw]] on 20 December 2016 on a three-year deal worth reportedly $1.9 million per year, per MLS Players Union documents.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/us/features/nemanja-nikolic-best-forward-mls-right-now-analysis-video|title=Baller on a budget: Nemanja Nikolic is the best forward in MLS right now|date=19 May 2017|website=Fourfourtwo.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Nikoli\u0107 odchodzi z Legii - Legia Warszawa|url=http://legia.com/aktualnosci/nikolic-odchodzi-z-legii-54352|website=Legia.com}}</ref>\n\nSpeaking on the transfer, in a press release by the club, Fire GM Nelson Rodriguez stated \"Through this transfer, we have secured a champion in his prime, and one of the most prolific goal scorers in Europe over the last few years\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chicago-fire.com/post/2016/12/20/chicago-fire-sign-nemanja-nikolic-designated-player|title=Chicago Fire Sign Nemanja Nikolic as Designated Player|date=20 December 2016|website=Chicago-fire.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nFire coach [[Veljko Paunovi\u0107]] noted his awareness of Nikoli\u0107 from an early age from his time in Serbia. In an article published by the Fire Paunovi\u0107 praised Nikoli\u0107's skillset:\n\n<blockquote>\u201cHis quality is scoring goals and assisting, but then he\u2019s a man that can participate in both phases of team play,\u201d Paunovic said. \u201cHe\u2019s very good in all phases of the game. Defensively, he helps the team to recover the ball as soon as possible in order that we can control the game and create opportunities for our team to win. Sometimes he will benefit from team play and he will be just the executor, but sometimes he\u2019s capable of creating his own situations in the game, the opportunities 1v1, and scoring his own goals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chicago-fire.com/post/2016/12/20/paunovic-nikolic-brings-class-and-highest-expectations-chicago-fire|title=Paunovic: Nikolic brings class and \"highest expectations\" to Chicago Fire|date=20 December 2016|website=Chicago-firec.om|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\u201d</blockquote>\n\n====2017 season====\nNikoli\u0107's high career strike-rate continued with the Fire, where he became an instant success - leading the league in scoring and acquiring numerous accolades through the first half of the season, and ultimately winning the [[MLS Golden Boot|2017 MLS Golden Boot]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/05/18/fires-nemanja-nikolic-leading-mls-goals-and-taking-league-storm|title=Fire's Nemanja Nikolic leading MLS in goals, and taking the league by storm|date=18 May 2017|website=Mlssoccer.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref><ref>https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/10/22/chicago-fire-striker-nemanja-nikolic-wins-2017-mls-golden-boot</ref> His first goal for the club came in the Fire's 2017 home opener against [[Real Salt Lake]], in which he scored an unassisted effort in the 11th minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chicago-fire.com/post/2017/03/11/chicago-fire-victorious-home-opener-2-0-against-real-salt-lake|title=Chicago Fire Victorious in Home Opener 2-0 Against Real Salt Lake|date=11 March 2017|website=Chicago-fire.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nNikoli\u0107 was named to the MLS Team of the Week in week 7 alongside fellow Fire forward [[Luis Solignac]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/04/17/2017-team-week-wk-7-sporting-kc-recognized-after-another-big-win|title=2017 Team of the Week (Wk 7): Sporting KC recognized after another big win|date=17 April 2017|website=Mlssoccer.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref> He was additionally selected as MLS player of the week in week 7.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/04/18/chicago-fires-nemanja-nikolic-voted-alcatel-mls-player-week|title=Chicago Fire's Nemanja Nikolic voted Alcatel MLS Player of the Week|date=18 April 2017|website=Mlssoccer.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nHe was once again chosen for team of the week in week 11 for his brace in Chicago's 4\u20131 win against the reigning [[MLS Cup]] champion [[Seattle Sounders FC|Seattle Sounders]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/05/15/2017-team-week-wk-11-fire-union-feature-after-statement-wins|title=2017 Team of the Week (Wk 11): Fire, Union feature after statement wins|date=15 May 2017|website=Mlssoccer.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nWith 10 goals through the first 11 games of the season, Nikoli\u0107 led the league in scoring. With his brace against the [[Colorado Rapids]] on 16 May, he became the first Fire player to score in four straight games since Mike Magee in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/05/17/chicago-fire-3-colorado-rapids-0-2017-mls-match-recap|title=Chicago Fire 3, Colorado Rapids 0 - 2017 MLS Match Recap|date=17 May 2017|website=Mlssoccer.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref> This brace once again earned him MLS Team of the Week honors.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/05/22/2017-team-week-wk-12-superstars-and-men-red-shine|title=2017 Team of the Week (Wk 12): Superstars, and Men in Red, shine|date=22 May 2017|website=Mlssoccer.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nAfter week 15 Nikoli\u0107 continued to lead the league in scoring, with 12 goals in 15 games. He was named to the week 15 Team of the Week for his goal against Atlanta United in Chicago's 2\u20130 home win alongside Fire players [[Bastian Schweinsteiger]], [[David Accam]], and [[Jo\u00e3o Meira]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/06/12/2017-team-week-wk-15-portland-timbers-impress-shutout-win|title=2017 Team of the Week (Wk 15): Portland Timbers impress in shutout win|date=12 June 2017|website=Mlssoccer.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nHe was named [[MLS Player of the Month]] for May for his six goals and one assist during the Fire's undefeated run during the stretch.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/06/05/chicago-fw-nemanja-nikolic-voted-alcatel-mls-player-month-may|title=Chicago FW Nemanja Nikolic voted Alcatel MLS Player of the Month for May|date=5 June 2017|website=Mlssoccer.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nA week after Fire teammate David Accam was named player of the week for week 17 for his [[hat-trick]] against [[Orlando City SC]], Nikoli\u0107 earned the same honor on 3 July for his brace against the [[Vancouver Whitecaps FC|Vancouver Whitecaps]]. It was the second time he won the award (the first time in week 7 as noted above). After week 18 Nikoli\u0107 continued to lead the [[MLS Golden Boot]] race with 16 goals in 18 matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/07/03/chicago-fires-nemanja-nikolic-wins-week-18-alcatel-mls-player-week|title=Chicago Fire's Nemanja Nikolic wins Week 18 Alcatel MLS Player of the Week|date=3 July 2017|website=Mlssoccer.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nAlongside [[Bastian Schweinsteiger]] Nikoli\u0107 was named to the \"2017 MLS All-Star Fan XI\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chicago-fire.com/post/2017/07/07/nikolic-schweinsteiger-named-2017-mls-all-star-fan-xi-presented-target|title=Nikolic, Schweinsteiger Named to 2017 MLS All-Star Fan XI Presented by Target|date=7 July 2017|website=Chicago-fire.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref> Nikolic finished the 2017 season as the Golden Boot winner with 24 goals and 4 assists.\n\n====2018 season====\nNikoli\u0107 finished the [[2018 MLS season|2018 season]] as the Fire's top scorer, finishing seventh in scoring league-wide, with 15 goals and 2 assists.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/stats/season?year=2018&group=goals|title=By Season|website=www.mlssoccer.com|accessdate = 11 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nOn 11 October 2013, Nikoli\u0107 debuted in the [[Hungary national football team]] against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] in an 8\u20131 defeat at the [[Amsterdam Arena]] in the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification - UEFA Group D|2014 FIFA World Cup qualification]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/europe/matches/round=258374/match=300183556/index.html|title=FIFA 2014 World Cup Qualification: Netherlands 8-1 Hungary|date=11 October 2013|website=Fifa.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/news/newsid=2194168/index.html|title=Eight-goal Oranje dent Hungary hopes|date=11 October 2013|website=Fifa.com}}</ref> On 14 October 2013 Nikoli\u0107 scored his first goal in the national team against [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]] in the 51st minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/europe/matches/round=258374/match=300183566/index.html?intcmp=livecoverage_header_fwcq_en|title=FIFA 2014 World Cup Qualification: Hungary 2-0 Andorra|date=15 October 2013|website=Fifa.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/news/newsid=2196261/index.html|title=Hungarian victory to no avail|date=15 October 2013|website=Fifa.com}}</ref> His second goal was recorded as an own goal by [[Ildefons Lima|Lima]].\n\nOn 18 November 2014, Nikoli\u0107 scored against [[Russia national football team|Russia]] in a 2\u20131 defeat in a [[friendly match]] at the [[Groupama Arena]], [[Budapest]], [[Hungary]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/football/international-friendlies/hungary-russia-22312/|title=Hungary 1-2 Russia|date=18 November 2014|publisher=[[Eurosport]]}}</ref>\n\nNikoli\u0107 was called up to Hungary's squad for [[UEFA Euro 2016]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/news/newsid=2370006.html|title=Hungary on the offensive with EURO squad|date=31 May 2016|publisher=[[UEFA]].com}}</ref> On 18 June 2016 he played in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]] at the [[Stade V\u00e9lodrome]], [[Marseille]] in which his run and far post drive was re-directed in by Iceland for the last minute equalizer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2016/matches/round=2000448/match=2017962/index.html|title=UEFA Euro 2016: Iceland 1\u20131 Hungary|publisher=[[UEFA.com]]}}</ref>\n\nOn 3 May 2018, Nikoli\u0107 announced his retirement from the national team.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/magyar_valogatott/valogatott-nikolics-nemanja-nem-jatszik-tobbet-a-nemzeti-csapatban-2633411|title=V\u00e1logatott: Nikolics Nemanja nem j\u00e1tszik t\u00f6bbet a nemzeti csapatban!|language=Hungarian|date=3 May 2018|publisher=[[Nemzeti Sport]].com}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|14 March 2020}}<ref name=\"sw\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hlsz.hu/1987-12-31/nikolics-nemanja.html|title=HLSZ|website=Hlsz.hu|access-date=25 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[UEFA|Europe]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Barcsi SC|Barcs]]\n|[[Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g II|2006\u201307]]\n|19||3||0||0||0||0||0||0||19||3\n|-\n!Total\n!19!!3!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!19!!3\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Kaposv\u00f6lgye VSC|Kaposv\u00f6lgye]]\n|[[Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g II|2007\u201308]]\n|14||11||0||0||0||0||0||0||14||11\n|-\n!Total\n!14!!11!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!14!!11\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Kaposv\u00e1ri R\u00e1k\u00f3czi FC|Kaposv\u00e1r]]\n|[[2007\u201308 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2007\u201308]]\n|12||4||5||2||4||2||0||0||21||8\n|-\n|[[2008\u201309 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2008\u201309]]\n|22||16||3||1||5||7||0||0||30||24\n|-\n|[[2009\u201310 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2009\u201310]]\n|15||10||3||1||0||0||0||0||18||11\n|-\n!Total\n!49!!30!!11!!4!!9!!9!!0!!0!!69!!43\n|-\n|rowspan=\"8\"|[[Videoton FC|Videoton]]\n|[[2009\u201310 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2009\u201310]]\n|15||8||1||1||3||1||0||0||19||10\n|-\n|[[2010\u201311 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2010\u201311]]\n|24||8||7||5||2||0||2||0||35||13\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2011\u201312]]\n|30||19||6||4||10||7||1||0||47||30\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2012\u201313]]\n|27||13||5||5||7||5||12||4||51||27\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2013\u201314]]\n|28||18||1||0||3||1||2||0||34||19\n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2014\u201315]]\n|25||21||4||3||0||0||0||0||29||24\n|-\n|[[2019\u201320 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2019\u201320]]\n|6||2||3||1||\u2013||\u2013||0||0||9||3\n|-\n!Tota