 goals)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.90minut.pl/strzelcy.php?id=8073 |title=Strzelcy |language=Polish}}</ref>\n* [[Ekstraklasa]] Player of the Month: August 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.przegladsportowy.pl/nemanja-nikolic-odebral-statuetke-dla-najlepszego-pilkarza-sierpnia,artykul,603064,1,12684.html|title = Nikoli\u0107 pi\u0142karzem miesi\u0105ca sierpnia Ekstraklasy 2015|language = Polish|access-date = 10 November 2015|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304042203/http://www.przegladsportowy.pl/nemanja-nikolic-odebral-statuetke-dla-najlepszego-pilkarza-sierpnia,artykul,603064,1,12684.html|archive-date = 4 March 2016|url-status = dead}}</ref> September 2015,<ref>{{cite web|title = PI\u0141KARZ MIESI\u0104CA: NEMANJA NIKOLI\u0106!|url = http://www.ekstraklasa.org/pilkarz-miesiaca-nemanja-nikolic|language=Polish}}</ref> October 2015<ref>{{cite web|title = Hat-trick Nikolicia!|url = http://www.ekstraklasa.org/hat-trick-nikolicia|language=Polish}}</ref>\n* [[Ekstraklasa]] Best Forward: [[2015\u201316 Ekstraklasa|2015\u201316]]<ref name=\"nemzetisport.hu\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/legiosok/legiosok-nikolics-harom-egyeni-dijat-is-besoport-2501699|title=L\u00e9gi\u00f3sok: Nikolics h\u00e1rom egy\u00e9ni d\u00edjat is bes\u00f6p\u00f6rt - NSO|last=nemzetisport.hu|date=16 May 2016|language=hu-HU|access-date=25 June 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Ekstraklasa]] Best Player: [[2015\u201316 Ekstraklasa|2015\u201316]]<ref name=\"nemzetisport.hu\"/>\n* [[Ekstraklasa]] [[Canal+ Poland|Canal +]] Spectator Prize: [[2015\u201316 Ekstraklasa|2015\u201316]]<ref name=\"nemzetisport.hu\"/>\n* [[MLS Golden Boot]]: [[2017 Major League Soccer season#Goals|2017]] (24 goals)<ref name=\"2017 MLS Best XI\"/>\n* [[MLS Best XI]]: [[2017 Major League Soccer season#MLS Best XI|2017]]<ref name=\"2017 MLS Best XI\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/11/29/2017-mls-best-xi|title=2017 MLS Best XI revealed: Who was the best in 2017?|publisher=MLS Soccer|date=30 November 2017}}</ref>\n* 2017 Hungarian Player of the Year (M4 Sport G\u00e1la)<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.chicago-fire.com/post/2018/01/11/nikolic-named-best-hungarian-footballer-2018-m4-sport-gala}}</ref>\n* [[2018 ESPY Awards]] Best MLS Player\n\n==Personal life==\nOn 28 January 2011, Nikoli\u0107 obtained [[Hungarian citizenship]]. Andr\u00e1s Cser-Palkovics, mayor of [[Sz\u00e9kesfeh\u00e9rv\u00e1r]] said that \"We know about him that he knows the country, speaks the language since he has big plans with [[Videoton FC|Videoton]] this year\". Nikoli\u0107 said that \"I knew that it is not easy to obtain [[Hungarian citizenship]] but I hoped that due to the fact that my mother is Hungarian it would be easier but it turned out to be a bit more difficult.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/labdarugo_nb_i/nikolics-nemanja-letette-az-allampolgarsagi-eskut-2062043|title=Nikolics Nemanja letette az \u00e1llampolg\u00e1rs\u00e1gi esk\u00fct|date=28 January 2011|publisher=[[Nemzeti Sport]]}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons}}\n* [http://www.magyarfutball.hu/hu/szemelyek/adatlap/7833/nikolics_nemanja Nemanja Nikoli\u0107] profile at magyarfutball.hu\n* [http://www.hlsz.hu/index.php?WG_NODE=WebHlszJatekos&WG_OID=hPLf_89719b5 Profile] {{in lang|hu}}\n* {{90minut|23824}}\n* {{MLS|nemanja-nikolic}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title= Awards\n|bg= gold\n|fg= navy\n|list1=\n{{2017 MLS Best XI}}\n{{Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I top scorers}}\n{{Ekstraklasa top scorers}}\n{{Major League Soccer top scorers}}\n{{Hungarian Footballer of the Year}}\n{{Hungarian Golden Ball}}\n{{ESPY Best MLS Player}}\n}}\n{{Hungary squad UEFA Euro 2016}}\n{{MOL Vidi FC squad}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nikolic, Nemanja}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Senta]]\n[[Category:Hungarian footballers]]\n[[Category:Hungary international footballers]]\n[[Category:Hungarian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Hungarian expatriate sportspeople in the United States]]\n[[Category:Serbian footballers]]\n[[Category:Hungarian people of Serbian descent]]\n[[Category:Serbian people of Hungarian descent]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:FK Senta players]]\n[[Category:Barcsi SC footballers]]\n[[Category:Kaposv\u00f6lgye VSC footballers]]\n[[Category:Kaposv\u00e1ri R\u00e1k\u00f3czi FC players]]\n[[Category:Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r FC players]]\n[[Category:Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I players]]\n[[Category:Ekstraklasa players]]\n[[Category:Legia Warsaw players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Poland]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2016 players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in the United States]]\n[[Category:Chicago Fire FC players]]\n[[Category:Designated Players (MLS)]]\n[[Category:Major League Soccer players]]\n[[Category:Major League Soccer All-Stars]]\n[[Category:Naturalized citizens of Hungary]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|Nemanja Nikoli\u0107 (footballer, born 1988)}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Nemanja Nikoli\u0107\n| image          = CINvCHI 2017-06-28 - Nemanja Nikoli\u0107 (39393300370) (cropped).jpg\n| image_size     = 200\n| caption        = Nikoli\u0107 with the [[Chicago Fire Soccer Club|Chicago Fire]] in 2017\n| fullname       = Nemanja Nikoli\u0107\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1987|12|31|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Senta]], [[SFR Yugoslavia]]\n| height         = {{height|m=1.80}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vidi.hu/jatekosok/nikolics-nemanja.html|title=Nikolics Nemanja - vidi.hu|website=Vidi.hu|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n| currentclub    = [[Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r FC|Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r]]\n| clubnumber     = 71\n| position       = [[Forward (association football)#Striker|Striker]]\n| youthyears1 = 1996\u20132006\n| youthclubs1 = [[FK Senta|Senta]]\n| years1 = 2006\u20132007\n| clubs1 = [[Barcsi SC|Barcs]]\n| caps1 = 19\n| goals1 = 3\n| years2 = 2007\u20132008\n| clubs2 = [[Kaposv\u00f6lgye VSC|Kaposv\u00f6lgye]]\n| caps2 = 14\n| goals2 = 11\n| years3 = 2008\u20132010\n| clubs3 = [[Kaposv\u00e1ri R\u00e1k\u00f3czi FC|Kaposv\u00e1r]]\n| caps3 = 49\n| goals3 = 30\n| years4 = 2010\u20132015\n| clubs4 = [[Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r FC|Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r]]\n| caps4 = 149\n| goals4 = 87\n| years5 = 2015\u20132016\n| clubs5 = [[Legia Warsaw]]\n| caps5 = 56\n| goals5 = 40\n| years6 = 2016\u20132019\n| clubs6 = [[Chicago Fire Soccer Club|Chicago Fire]]\n| caps6 = 96\n| goals6 = 51\n| years7 = 2020\u2013\n| clubs7 = [[Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r FC|Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r]]\n| caps7 = 6\n| goals7= 2\n| club-update = 14 March 2020\n| nationalyears1 = 2013\u20132018\n| nationalteam1 = [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 27\n| nationalgoals1 = 5\n| nationalteam-update = {{date|2018-3-27}}\n}}\n\n'''Nemanja Nikoli\u0107''' ({{lang-sr-Cyrl|\u041d\u0435\u043c\u0430\u045a\u0430 \u041d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0438\u045b}} {{IPA-sh|n\u011bma\u0272a n\u01d0kolit\u0255|}}; {{lang-hu|Nikolics Nemanja}}; born 31 December 1987) is a Yugoslav-born Hungarian footballer who last played as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]] for [[Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I]] club [[Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r FC|Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r]]. Born in [[Socialist Republic of Serbia|Serbia]], but never selected for the [[Serbia national football team|Serbian national team]], he chose to represent the [[Hungary national football team|Hungarian national team]] instead.<ref>{{cite news|script-title=sr:\u0415\u043a\u0441\u043a\u043b\u0443\u0437\u0438\u0432\u043d\u043e, \u041d\u0435\u043c\u0430\u045a\u0430 \u041d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0438\u045b, \u0440\u0435\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0446 \u041c\u0430\u0452\u0430\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0435: \u041d\u0438\u043a\u043e \u043c\u0435 \u0438\u0437 \u0424\u0421\u0421 \u043d\u0438\u0458\u0435 \u0433\u043b\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043e!|url=http://www.zurnal.rs/fudbal/evropsko-prvenstvo/35736/ekskluzivno-nemanja-nikolic-reprezentativac-madjarske-niko-me-iz-fss-nije-gledao|accessdate=20 June 2016|work=zurnal.rs|date=20 June 2016|language=Serbian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Jovanovi\u0107|first1=Jovan|title=Pri\u010da dana Ma\u0111arski reprezentativac Nemanja Nikoli\u0107 otvorio du\u0161u za \"Sport\"|url=http://www.sport.org.rs/940-madarski-reprezentativac-nemanja-nikolic-otvorio-dusu-za-sport/|accessdate=20 June 2016|work=sport.rs|agency=Dnevni list Sport|language=Serbian|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160916204157/http://www.sport.org.rs/940-madarski-reprezentativac-nemanja-nikolic-otvorio-dusu-za-sport/|archivedate=16 September 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nNikoli\u0107 was born in [[Senta]], [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|Yugoslavia]] to a [[Serbs|Serbian]] father and a [[Hungarians|Hungarian]] mother. He began his career with his brother at [[FK Senta]].\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Kaposv\u00e1r===\n[[File:Nemanja Nikoli\u0107.JPG|thumb|150px|right|Nikoli\u0107 with [[Videoton FC|Videoton]] in 2010]]\nOn 7 February 2008 Nikoli\u0107 was signed by [[Kaposv\u00e1ri R\u00e1k\u00f3czi FC|Kaposv\u00e1r]]. He played his first match against [[Videoton FC|Videoton]]. He managed to score thirty goals in just 49 matches therefore many top Hungarian sides wanted to sign him such as [[\u00dajpest FC|\u00dajpest]], [[Ferencv\u00e1rosi TC|Ferencv\u00e1ros]] and [[Videoton FC|Videoton]].\n\n===Videoton===\nIn 2010 [[Videoton FC|Videoton]] signed Nikoli\u0107. He became top scorer in the [[2009-10 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2009-10]] season of the [[Hungarian League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/association=hun/news/newsid=1485621.html|title=Nikoli\u0107 thriving in Videoton spotlight|date=6 May 2010|publisher=UEFA}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/association=hun/news/newsid=1503384.html|title=Season review: Hungary|date=9 July 2010|publisher=UEFA}}</ref>\n\nNikoli\u0107 won the [[2010-11 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2010-11]] season of the Hungarian League with [[Videoton FC|Videoton]]. With the arrival of the Portuguese coach [[Paulo Sousa]] he was often left out from the first squad in the early matches of the [[2011-12 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2011-12]] season of the [[Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|Hungarian League]]. However, as a substitute he managed to score against [[Paksi SE|Paks]], [[Si\u00f3fok KC|Si\u00f3fok]] (twice), [[\u00dajpest FC|\u00dajpest]] (twice) and [[Lombard-P\u00e1pa TFC|P\u00e1pa]] in a row in the Hungarian League.\n\nOn 2 August 2012, Nikoli\u0107 scored the only goal of the first leg of the third round of the [[Europa league 2012-13]] season, when Videoton beat the [[Belgian people|Belgian]] [[KAA Gent]] 1\u20130 at the S\u00f3st\u00f3i Stadion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2013/matches/round=2000354/match=2009771/index.html|title=UEFA Europa League 2012\u201313: Videoton 1\u20130 KAA Gent|date=2 August 2012|publisher=UEFA}}</ref> He also scored in the second leg of the tie which was won by 3\u20130 by Videoton at the [[Jules Ottenstadion]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2013/matches/round=2000354/match=2009800/index.html|title=UEFA Europa League 2012\u201313: KAA Gent 0\u20133 Videoton|date=9 August 2012|publisher=UEFA}}</ref> On 4 September 2012, he scored a goal in the [[Europa league 2012-13]] season when [[Videoton FC|Videoton]] beat Portugal's [[Sporting Clube de Portugal|Sporting CP]] 3-0 at [[Stadion Sostoi|Stadion S\u00f3st\u00f3i]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2013/matches/round=2000356/match=2009928/postmatch/report/index.html#videoton+stun+sporting|title=UEFA Europa League 2012\u201313: Paulo Sousa's Videoton stun Sporting|date=4 October 2012|publisher=UEFA}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/19839286|title=Europa League round-up: Lazio and Inter win, but Napoli defeated|date=4 October 2012|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 October 2014, Nikoli\u0107 set a new record scoring in 12 consecutive league matches in the 2014\u201315 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/labdarugo_nb_i/nikolics-europa-rekorder-a-dvtk-es-az-otthon-kapott-harmasok-2372573|title=Nikolics Eur\u00f3pa-rekorder! A DVTK \u00e9s az otthon kapott h\u00e1rmasok|date=27 October 2014|publisher=[[Nemzeti Sport]]}}</ref>\n\n===Legia Warsaw===\nOn 8 June 2015, Nikoli\u0107 joined [[Ekstraklasa]] club, [[Legia Warsaw]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Nemanja Nikoli\u0107 pi\u0142karzem Legii [Nemanja Nikoli\u0107 is a Legia player]|url=http://legia.com/aktualnosci/nemanja-nikolic-pilkarzem-legii-47054|accessdate=8 June 2015|language=Polish|date=8 June 2015}}</ref> On 19 July 2015, Nikoli\u0107 debuted in the [[2015\u201316 Ekstraklasa|2015-16]] season of the [[Ekstraklasa]] by scoring two goals against [[\u015al\u0105sk Wroc\u0142aw]] at the [[Stadion Miejski (Wroc\u0142aw)|Stadion Miejski]], [[Wroc\u0142aw]].<ref>{{cite web|title=\u015al\u0105sk Wroc\u0142aw 1-4 Legia Warsaw|url=http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/association=pol/domesticleague/season=2016/matches/match=200155204/live/index.html|publisher=[[UEFA.com]]|date=19 July 2015}}</ref> On 16 March 2016 Nikolic scored a [[hat-trick]] against [[Zawisza Bydgoszcz]] at the Pepsi Arena, [[Warsaw]]. The match ended with a 4\u20130 win for Legia Warsaw.<ref>{{cite web|title=Legia Warsaw 4-0 Zawisza Bydgoszcz|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2016/03/16/poland/cup/kp-legia-warsaw/sp-zawisza-bydgoszcz/2178120/|publisher=[[UEFA.com]]|date=16 March 2016}}</ref> On 15 May 2016 Legia became champions of the [[2015\u201316 Ekstraklasa]] season by beating [[Pogo\u0144 Szczecin]] 3\u20130 at home. He was the top scorer of the [[2015\u201316 Ekstraklasa]] season, scoring 28 goals in 37 matches.<ref name=\"sw\">{{cite web|title=N. Nikolics|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/nemanja-nikolic/33875/|website=Soccerway.com|date=16 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Chicago Fire===\n\nNikoli\u0107 joined the [[Chicago Fire Soccer Club|Chicago Fire]] as a [[Designated Player Rule|Designated Player]] for a reported transfer fee of $3 million from [[Legia Warsaw]] on 20 December 2016 on a three-year deal worth reportedly $1.9 million per year, per MLS Players Union documents.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/us/features/nemanja-nikolic-best-forward-mls-right-now-analysis-video|title=Baller on a budget: Nemanja Nikolic is the best forward in MLS right now|date=19 May 2017|website=Fourfourtwo.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Nikoli\u0107 odchodzi z Legii - Legia Warszawa|url=http://legia.com/aktualnosci/nikolic-odchodzi-z-legii-54352|website=Legia.com}}</ref>\n\nSpeaking on the transfer, in a press release by the club, Fire GM Nelson Rodriguez stated \"Through this transfer, we have secured a champion in his prime, and one of the most prolific goal scorers in Europe over the last few years\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chicago-fire.com/post/2016/12/20/chicago-fire-sign-nemanja-nikolic-designated-player|title=Chicago Fire Sign Nemanja Nikolic as Designated Player|date=20 December 2016|website=Chicago-fire.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nFire coach [[Veljko Paunovi\u0107]] noted his awareness of Nikoli\u0107 from an early age from his time in Serbia. In an article published by the Fire Paunovi\u0107 praised Nikoli\u0107's skillset:\n\n<blockquote>\u201cHis quality is scoring goals and assisting, but then he\u2019s a man that can participate in both phases of team play,\u201d Paunovic said. \u201cHe\u2019s very good in all phases of the game. Defensively, he helps the team to recover the ball as soon as possible in order that we can control the game and create opportunities for our team to win. Sometimes he will benefit from team play and he will be just the executor, but sometimes he\u2019s capable of creating his own situations in the game, the opportunities 1v1, and scoring his own goals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chicago-fire.com/post/2016/12/20/paunovic-nikolic-brings-class-and-highest-expectations-chicago-fire|title=Paunovic: Nikolic brings class and \"highest expectations\" to Chicago Fire|date=20 December 2016|website=Chicago-firec.om|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\u201d</blockquote>\n\n====2017 Season====\n\nNikoli\u0107's high career strike-rate continued with the Fire, where he became an instant success - leading the league in scoring and acquiring numerous accolades through the first half of the season, and ultimately winning the [[MLS Golden Boot|2017 MLS Golden Boot]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/05/18/fires-nemanja-nikolic-leading-mls-goals-and-taking-league-storm|title=Fire's Nemanja Nikolic leading MLS in goals, and taking the league by storm|date=18 May 2017|website=Mlssoccer.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref><ref>https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/10/22/chicago-fire-striker-nemanja-nikolic-wins-2017-mls-golden-boot</ref> His first goal for the club came in the Fire's 2017 home opener against [[Real Salt Lake]], in which he scored an unassisted effort in the 11th minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chicago-fire.com/post/2017/03/11/chicago-fire-victorious-home-opener-2-0-against-real-salt-lake|title=Chicago Fire Victorious in Home Opener 2-0 Against Real Salt Lake|date=11 March 2017|website=Chicago-fire.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nNikoli\u0107 was named to the MLS Team of the Week in week 7 alongside fellow Fire forward [[Luis Solignac]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/04/17/2017-team-week-wk-7-sporting-kc-recognized-after-another-big-win|title=2017 Team of the Week (Wk 7): Sporting KC recognized after another big win|date=17 April 2017|website=Mlssoccer.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref> He was additionally selected as MLS player of the week in week 7.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/04/18/chicago-fires-nemanja-nikolic-voted-alcatel-mls-player-week|title=Chicago Fire's Nemanja Nikolic voted Alcatel MLS Player of the Week|date=18 April 2017|website=Mlssoccer.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nHe was once again chosen for team of the week in week 11 for his brace in Chicago's 4\u20131 win against the reigning [[MLS Cup]] champion [[Seattle Sounders FC|Seattle Sounders]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/05/15/2017-team-week-wk-11-fire-union-feature-after-statement-wins|title=2017 Team of the Week (Wk 11): Fire, Union feature after statement wins|date=15 May 2017|website=Mlssoccer.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nWith 10 goals through the first 11 games of the season, Nikoli\u0107 led the league in scoring. With his brace against the [[Colorado Rapids]] on 16 May, he became the first Fire player to score in four straight games since Mike Magee in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/05/17/chicago-fire-3-colorado-rapids-0-2017-mls-match-recap|title=Chicago Fire 3, Colorado Rapids 0 - 2017 MLS Match Recap|date=17 May 2017|website=Mlssoccer.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref> This brace once again earned him MLS Team of the Week honors.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/05/22/2017-team-week-wk-12-superstars-and-men-red-shine|title=2017 Team of the Week (Wk 12): Superstars, and Men in Red, shine|date=22 May 2017|website=Mlssoccer.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nAfter week 15 Nikoli\u0107 continued to lead the league in scoring, with 12 goals in 15 games. He was named to the week 15 Team of the Week for his goal against Atlanta United in Chicago's 2\u20130 home win alongside Fire players [[Bastian Schweinsteiger]], [[David Accam]], and [[Jo\u00e3o Meira]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/06/12/2017-team-week-wk-15-portland-timbers-impress-shutout-win|title=2017 Team of the Week (Wk 15): Portland Timbers impress in shutout win|date=12 June 2017|website=Mlssoccer.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nHe was named [[MLS Player of the Month]] for May for his six goals and one assist during the Fire's undefeated run during the stretch.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/06/05/chicago-fw-nemanja-nikolic-voted-alcatel-mls-player-month-may|title=Chicago FW Nemanja Nikolic voted Alcatel MLS Player of the Month for May|date=5 June 2017|website=Mlssoccer.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nA week after Fire teammate David Accam was named player of the week for week 17 for his [[hat-trick]] against [[Orlando City SC]], Nikoli\u0107 earned the same honor on 3 July for his brace against the [[Vancouver Whitecaps FC|Vancouver Whitecaps]]. It was the second time he won the award (the first time in week 7 as noted above). After week 18 Nikoli\u0107 continued to lead the [[MLS Golden Boot]] race with 16 goals in 18 matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2017/07/03/chicago-fires-nemanja-nikolic-wins-week-18-alcatel-mls-player-week|title=Chicago Fire's Nemanja Nikolic wins Week 18 Alcatel MLS Player of the Week|date=3 July 2017|website=Mlssoccer.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nAlongside [[Bastian Schweinsteiger]] Nikoli\u0107 was named to the \"2017 MLS All-Star Fan XI\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chicago-fire.com/post/2017/07/07/nikolic-schweinsteiger-named-2017-mls-all-star-fan-xi-presented-target|title=Nikolic, Schweinsteiger Named to 2017 MLS All-Star Fan XI Presented by Target|date=7 July 2017|website=Chicago-fire.com|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref> Nikolic finished the 2017 season as the Golden Boot winner with 24 goals and 4 assists.\n\n====2018 Season====\n\nNikoli\u0107 finished the [[2018 MLS season|2018 season]] as the Fire's top scorer, finishing seventh in scoring league-wide, with 15 goals and 2 assists.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/stats/season?year=2018&group=goals|title=By Season|website=www.mlssoccer.com|accessdate = January 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nOn 11 October 2013, Nikoli\u0107 debuted in the [[Hungary national football team]] against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] in an 8\u20131 defeat at the [[Amsterdam Arena]] in the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification - UEFA Group D|2014 FIFA World Cup qualification]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/europe/matches/round=258374/match=300183556/index.html|title=FIFA 2014 World Cup Qualification: Netherlands 8-1 Hungary|date=11 October 2013|website=Fifa.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/news/newsid=2194168/index.html|title=Eight-goal Oranje dent Hungary hopes|date=11 October 2013|website=Fifa.com}}</ref> On 14 October 2013 Nikoli\u0107 scored his first goal in the national team against [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]] in the 51st minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/europe/matches/round=258374/match=300183566/index.html?intcmp=livecoverage_header_fwcq_en|title=FIFA 2014 World Cup Qualification: Hungary 2-0 Andorra|date=15 October 2013|website=Fifa.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/news/newsid=2196261/index.html|title=Hungarian victory to no avail|date=15 October 2013|website=Fifa.com}}</ref> His second goal was recorded as an own goal by [[Ildefons Lima|Lima]].\n\nOn 18 November 2014, Nikoli\u0107 scored against [[Russia national football team|Russia]] in a 2\u20131 defeat in a [[friendly match]] at the [[Groupama Arena]], [[Budapest]], [[Hungary]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/football/international-friendlies/hungary-russia-22312/|title=Hungary 1-2 Russia|date=18 November 2014|publisher=[[Eurosport]]}}</ref>\n\nNikoli\u0107 was called up to Hungary's squad for [[UEFA Euro 2016]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/news/newsid=2370006.html|title=Hungary on the offensive with EURO squad|date=31 May 2016|publisher=[[UEFA]].com}}</ref> On 18 June 2016 he played in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]] at the [[Stade V\u00e9lodrome]], [[Marseille]] in which his run and far post drive was re-directed in by Iceland for the last minute equalizer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2016/matches/round=2000448/match=2017962/index.html|title=UEFA Euro 2016: Iceland 1\u20131 Hungary|publisher=[[UEFA.com]]}}</ref>\n\nOn 3 May 2018, Nikoli\u0107 announced his retirement from the national team.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/magyar_valogatott/valogatott-nikolics-nemanja-nem-jatszik-tobbet-a-nemzeti-csapatban-2633411|title=V\u00e1logatott: Nikolics Nemanja nem j\u00e1tszik t\u00f6bbet a nemzeti csapatban!|language=Hungarian|date=3 May 2018|publisher=[[Nemzeti Sport]].com}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|14 March 2020}}<ref name=\"sw\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hlsz.hu/1987-12-31/nikolics-nemanja.html|title=HLSZ|website=Hlsz.hu|access-date=2016-06-25}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[UEFA|Europe]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Barcsi SC|Barcs]]\n|[[Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g II|2006\u201307]]\n|19||3||0||0||0||0||0||0||19||3\n|-\n!Total\n!19!!3!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!19!!3\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Kaposv\u00f6lgye VSC|Kaposv\u00f6lgye]]\n|[[Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g II|2007\u201308]]\n|14||11||0||0||0||0||0||0||14||11\n|-\n!Total\n!14!!11!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!14!!11\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Kaposv\u00e1ri R\u00e1k\u00f3czi FC|Kaposv\u00e1r]]\n|[[2007\u201308 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2007\u201308]]\n|12||4||5||2||4||2||0||0||21||8\n|-\n|[[2008\u201309 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2008\u201309]]\n|22||16||3||1||5||7||0||0||30||24\n|-\n|[[2009\u201310 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I|2009\u201310]]\n|15|