agyarfutball.hu\n* [http://www.hlsz.hu/index.php?WG_NODE=WebHlszJatekos&WG_OID=hPLf_89719b5 Profile] {{in lang|hu}}\n* {{90minut|23824}}\n* {{MLS|nemanja-nikolic}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title= Awards\n|bg= gold\n|fg= navy\n|list1=\n{{2017 MLS Best XI}}\n{{Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I top scorers}}\n{{Ekstraklasa top scorers}}\n{{Major League Soccer top scorers}}\n{{Hungarian Footballer of the Year}}\n{{Hungarian Golden Ball}}\n{{ESPY Best MLS Player}}\n}}\n{{Hungary squad UEFA Euro 2016}}\n{{MOL Vidi FC squad}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nikolic, Nemanja}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Senta]]\n[[Category:Hungarian footballers]]\n[[Category:Hungary international footballers]]\n[[Category:Hungarian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Hungarian expatriate sportspeople in the United States]]\n[[Category:Serbian footballers]]\n[[Category:Hungarian people of Serbian descent]]\n[[Category:Serbian people of Hungarian descent]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:FK Senta players]]\n[[Category:Barcsi SC footballers]]\n[[Category:Kaposv\u00f6lgye VSC footballers]]\n[[Category:Kaposv\u00e1ri R\u00e1k\u00f3czi FC players]]\n[[Category:Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r FC players]]\n[[Category:Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I players]]\n[[Category:Ekstraklasa players]]\n[[Category:Legia Warsaw players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Poland]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2016 players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in the United States]]\n[[Category:Chicago Fire FC players]]\n[[Category:Designated Players (MLS)]]\n[[Category:Major League Soccer players]]\n[[Category:Major League Soccer All-Stars]]\n[[Category:Naturalized citizens of Hungary]]\n", "name_user": "Robby.is.on", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fix dashes.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nemanja_Nikoli%C4%87_(footballer,_born_1987)"}
{"title_page": "Godwin Emefiele", "text_new": "{{short description|Nigerian economist|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name               = Godwin Emefiele \n| honorific-suffix   =  \n| image              =  \n| imagesize          = \n| alt                = \n| caption            =  \n| order              = \n| office             = [[Central Bank of Nigeria#Governors|Governor of the Central Bank of Nigeria]]\n| term_start         = 3 June 2014\n| term_end           =  \n| predecessor        = [[Sarah Alade]] (Acting)<ref>https://www.cbn.gov.ng/aboutcbn/TheBoard.asp?Name=Dr.+Sarah+Alade+(OON)&Biodata=alade</ref> \n| successor          =  \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1961|8|4|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = Lagos, Nigeria.\n| birthname          = \n| nationality        = [[Nigeria]]n\n| party              = \n| spouse             = \n| relations          =  \n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| residence          = \n| alma_mater         = [[University of Nigeria, Nsukka]] \n| profession         = [[Banker]]\n| religion           =  [[Christian]]\n| website            = \n| footnotes          = \n| blank1             = Awards\n| data1              =  \n}}\n\n'''Godwin Emefiele''' is a Nigerian economist who has been serving as the Governor of the [[Central Bank of Nigeria]] since June 4, 2014. .<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=20 February 2014 |title=Profile of Godwin Emefiele, new CBN GOV |url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2014/02/profile-godwin-emefiele-new-cbn-gov/ |newspaper= |location= |publisher=[[Vanguard (Nigeria)]] |accessdate=20 February 2014 }}</ref> \n\n==Education==\nEmefiele holds a [[B.Sc.]] degree in Finance<ref>CNN.com</ref> in 1984 and an MBA Degree in Finance in 1986, both from the University of Nigeria, Nsukka. He is also an alumnus of Executive Education at [[Stanford University]], [[Harvard University]] (2004) and [[Wharton School of Business]] (2005). The Central Bank Governor, Mr Godwin Emefiele was conferred with a Honorary Doctorate Degree in Business Administration by the University of Nigeria, Nsukka (UNN)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://leadership.ng/2019/05/17/unn-confers-honorary-degree-on-emefiele/|title=UNN Confers Honorary Degree On Emefiele|last=Reporter|first=Our|date=2019-05-17|website=Leadership Newspaper|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-07}}</ref>.\n\n==Career in the private sector==\nEarly in his career, Emefiele lectured Finance and Insurance at the [[University of Nigeria Nsukka]], and [[University of Port Harcourt]], respectively. \n\nBefore moving to the Central Bank, Emefiele gained over eighteen years of banking experience. He served as Chief Executive officer and Group Managing Director of [[Zenith Bank]] Plc. Emefiele served as Deputy Managing Director of Zenith Bank Plc. from 2001. He served as Executive Director in charge of Corporate Banking, Treasury, Financial Control and Strategic Planning of Zenith Bank Plc and served on the management team from its inception. Emefiele served as director at Zenith Bank Plc and Zenith Bank ([[Gambia]]) Limited. Emefiele serves as Director of ACCION Microfinance Bank Limited. \n\n==Governor of the Central Bank==\nEmefiele has been Governor of the Central Bank of Nigeria since 2014. During his first term, he oversaw an interventionist currency policy at the behest of the presidency, propping up the [[Nigerian naira]] by pumping billions of dollars into the foreign exchange market. He also introduced a multiple [[exchange rate regime]] to try to mask pressure on the naira and avoid a series of devaluations.<ref>Camillus Eboh and Chijioke Ohuocha (May 9, 2019), [https://www.reuters.com/article/ozabs-us-nigeria-cenbank-idAFKCN1SF2CH-OZABS Nigeria central bank head nominated for second term] ''[[Reuters]]''.</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Nigeria's Senate approved a second five-year term for Emefiele.<ref>{{cite news |title=BREAKING: Senate confirms Emefiele\u2019s re-appointment a day after screening |url=https://oak.tv/newstrack/breaking-senate-confirms-emefiele/ |accessdate=17 May 2019 |work=Oak TV Newstrack |date=16 May 2019}}</ref><ref>Camillus Eboh (May 16, 2019), [https://www.reuters.com/article/nigeria-cenbank/nigerias-senate-confirms-second-term-for-cbank-governor-emefiele-idUSL5N22S44S Nigeria's Senate confirms second term for cbank governor Emefiele] ''[[Reuters]]''.</ref> This is the first time that anyone will serve for a second term since Nigeria's return to democracy in 1999.<ref>Camillus Eboh and Chijioke Ohuocha (May 9, 2019), [https://www.reuters.com/article/ozabs-us-nigeria-cenbank-idAFKCN1SF2CH-OZABS Nigeria central bank head nominated for second term] ''[[Reuters]]''.</ref> Senator Bukola Saraki read Buhari's letter on Thursday, May 9, 2019<ref>{{cite news |title=BREAKING: Again, Buhari nominates Godwin Emefiele for second term |url=https://oak.tv/newstrack/buhari-nominates-godwin-emefiele/ |accessdate=17 May 2019 |work=Oak TV Newstrack |date=9 May 2019}}</ref>. He was screened on Wednesday<ref>{{cite news |title=CBN Governor: Senate committee begins Emefiele\u2019s tenure extension screening |url=https://oak.tv/newstrack/cbn-governor-senate-committee-emefiele/ |accessdate=17 May 2019 |work=Oak TV Newstrack |date=15 May 2019}}</ref> and his confirmation came on Thursday, May 16, 2019.\n\n==Other activities==\n* [[International Monetary Fund]] (IMF), Ex-Officio Member of the Board of Governors (since 2018)<ref>[http://www.imf.org/external/np/sec/memdir/members.aspx Members] [[International Monetary Fund]] (IMF).</ref>\n* International Islamic Liquidity Management Corporation (IILM), Memver of the Governing Board (since 2018)<ref>[http://www.iilm.com/governing-board/ Governing Board] International Islamic Liquidity Management Corporation (IILM).</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Economy of Nigeria]]\n*[[Central Bank of Nigeria]]\n*[[Aishah Ahmad]]\n*[[Edward Lametek Adamu]]\n*[[List of banks in Nigeria]]\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Governors of the Central Bank of Nigeria}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Emefiele, Godwin}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Governors of the Central Bank of Nigeria]]\n[[Category:Nigerian bankers]]\n[[Category:University of Nigeria, Nsukka alumni]]\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:People from Lagos]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Nigerian economist|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name               = Godwin Emefiele \n| honorific-suffix   =  \n| image              =  \n| imagesize          = \n| alt                = \n| caption            =  \n| order              = \n| office             = [[Central Bank of Nigeria#Governors|Governor of the Central Bank of Nigeria]]\n| term_start         = 3 June 2014\n| term_end           =  \n| predecessor        = [[Sarah Alade]] (Acting)<ref>https://www.cbn.gov.ng/aboutcbn/TheBoard.asp?Name=Dr.+Sarah+Alade+(OON)&Biodata=alade</ref> \n| successor          =  \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1961|8|4|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = Lagos, Nigeria.\n| birthname          = \n| nationality        = [[Nigeria]]n\n| party              = \n| spouse             = \n| relations          =  \n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| residence          = \n| alma_mater         = [[University of Nigeria, Nsukka]] \n| profession         = [[Banker]]\n| religion           =  [[Christian]]\n| website            = \n| footnotes          = \n| blank1             = Awards\n| data1              =  \n}}\n\n'''Godwin Emefiele''' is a Nigerian economist who has been serving as the Governor of the [[Central Bank of Nigeria]] since June 4, 2014. .<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=20 February 2014 |title=Profile of Godwin Emefiele, new CBN GOV |url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2014/02/profile-godwin-emefiele-new-cbn-gov/ |newspaper= |location= |publisher=[[Vanguard (Nigeria)]] |accessdate=20 February 2014 }}</ref> \n\n==Education==\nEmefiele holds a [[B.Sc.]] degree in Finance<ref>CNN.com</ref> in 1984 and an MBA Degree in Finance in 1986, both from the University of Nigeria, Nsukka. He is also an alumnus of Executive Education at [[Stanford University]], [[Harvard University]] (2004) and [[Wharton School of Business]] (2005). The Central Bank Governor, Mr Godwin Emefiele was conferred with a Honorary Doctorate Degree in Business Administration by the University of Nigeria, Nsukka (UNN)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://leadership.ng/2019/05/17/unn-confers-honorary-degree-on-emefiele/|title=UNN Confers Honorary Degree On Emefiele|last=Reporter|first=Our|date=2019-05-17|website=Leadership Newspaper|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-07}}</ref>.\n\n==Career in the private sector==\nEarly in his career, Emefiele lectured Finance and Insurance at the [[University of Nigeria Nsukka]], and [[University of Port Harcourt]], respectively. \n\nBefore moving to the Central Bank, Emefiele gained over eighteen years of banking experience. He served as Chief Executive officer and Group Managing Director of [[Zenith Bank]] Plc. Emefiele served as Deputy Managing Director of Zenith Bank Plc. from 2001. He served as Executive Director in charge of Corporate Banking, Treasury, Financial Control and Strategic Planning of Zenith Bank Plc and served on the management team from its inception. Emefiele served as director at Zenith Bank Plc and Zenith Bank ([[Gambia]]) Limited. Emefiele serves as Director of ACCION Microfinance Bank Limited. \n\n==Governor of the Central Bank==\nEmefiele has been Governor of the Central Bank of Nigeria since 2014. During his first term, he oversaw an interventionist currency policy at the behest of the presidency, propping up the [[Nigerian naira]] by pumping billions of dollars into the foreign exchange market. He also introduced a multiple [[exchange rate regime]] to try to mask pressure on the naira and avoid a series of devaluations.<ref>Camillus Eboh and Chijioke Ohuocha (May 9, 2019), [https://www.reuters.com/article/ozabs-us-nigeria-cenbank-idAFKCN1SF2CH-OZABS Nigeria central bank head nominated for second term] ''[[Reuters]]''.</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Nigeria's Senate approved a second five-year term for Emefiele.<ref>{{cite news |title=BREAKING: Senate confirms Emefiele\u2019s re-appointment a day after screening |url=https://oak.tv/newstrack/breaking-senate-confirms-emefiele/ |accessdate=17 May 2019 |work=Oak TV Newstrack |date=16 May 2019}}</ref><ref>Camillus Eboh (May 16, 2019), [https://www.reuters.com/article/nigeria-cenbank/nigerias-senate-confirms-second-term-for-cbank-governor-emefiele-idUSL5N22S44S Nigeria's Senate confirms second term for cbank governor Emefiele] ''[[Reuters]]''.</ref> This is the first time that anyone will serve for a second term since Nigeria's return to democracy in 1999.<ref>Camillus Eboh and Chijioke Ohuocha (May 9, 2019), [https://www.reuters.com/article/ozabs-us-nigeria-cenbank-idAFKCN1SF2CH-OZABS Nigeria central bank head nominated for second term] ''[[Reuters]]''.</ref> Senator Bukola Saraki read Buhari's letter on Thursday, May 9, 2019<ref>{{cite news |title=BREAKING: Again, Buhari nominates Godwin Emefiele for second term |url=https://oak.tv/newstrack/buhari-nominates-godwin-emefiele/ |accessdate=17 May 2019 |work=Oak TV Newstrack |date=9 May 2019}}</ref>. He was screened on Wednesday<ref>{{cite news |title=CBN Governor: Senate committee begins Emefiele\u2019s tenure extension screening |url=https://oak.tv/newstrack/cbn-governor-senate-committee-emefiele/ |accessdate=17 May 2019 |work=Oak TV Newstrack |date=15 May 2019}}</ref> and his confirmation came on Thursday, May 16, 2019.\n\n==Other activities==\n* [[International Monetary Fund]] (IMF), Ex-Officio Member of the Board of Governors (since 2018)<ref>[http://www.imf.org/external/np/sec/memdir/members.aspx Members] [[International Monetary Fund]] (IMF).</ref>\n* International Islamic Liquidity Management Corporation (IILM), Memver of the Governing Board (since 2018)<ref>[http://www.iilm.com/governing-board/ Governing Board] International Islamic Liquidity Management Corporation (IILM).</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Economy of Nigeria]]\n*[[Central Bank of Nigeria]]\n*[[Aishah Ahmad]]\n*[[Edward Lametek Adamu]]\n*[[List of banks in Nigeria]]\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Governors of the Central Bank of Nigeria}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Emefiele, Godwin}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Governors of the Central Bank of Nigeria]]\n[[Category:Nigerian bankers]]\n[[Category:University of Nigeria, Nsukka alumni]]\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n", "name_user": "Inter&anthro", "label": "safe", "comment": "says it in the article", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Godwin_Emefiele"}
{"title_page": "Athletics at the 1976 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's javelin throw", "text_new": "{{Infobox Olympic event\n|event = Men's javelin throw\n|games = 1976 Summer\n|venue = [[Olympic Stadium (Montreal)|Olympic Stadium]]\n|date = 24\u201325 July\n|competitors = 23\n|nations = 15\n|win_label = Winning distance\n|win_value = 94.58 {{WR|athletics}}\n|longnames = yes\n|gold = [[Mikl\u00f3s N\u00e9meth (athlete)|Mikl\u00f3s N\u00e9meth]]\n|goldNOC = HUN\n|silver = [[Hannu Siitonen]]\n|silverNOC = FIN\n|bronze = [[Gheorghe Megelea]]\n|bronzeNOC = ROM\n|prev = [[Athletics at the 1972 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's javelin throw|1972]]\n|next = [[Athletics at the 1980 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's javelin throw|1980]]\n}}\n{{AthleticsAt1976SummerOlympics}}\nThe '''[[Javelin throw|Men's Javelin Throw]]''' event at the '''[[Athletics at the 1976 Summer Olympics|1976 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Montreal|Montreal, Quebec]], [[Canada]], had an entry list of 23 competitors, with two qualifying groups (23 throwers) before the final (15) took place on Saturday Monday 26, 1976. The top twelve and ties, and all those reaching 79.00 metres advanced to the final. The qualification round was held on Sunday 25, 1976.<ref name=\"SR\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/1976/ATH/mens-javelin-throw.html |title=Athletics at the 1976 Montreal Summer Games: Men's Javelin Throw |accessdate=18 January 2018 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref>\n\n==Medalists==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\" width=\"35%\"\n|- \n|{{OlympicGoldMedalist|[[Mikl\u00f3s N\u00e9meth (athlete)|Mikl\u00f3s N\u00e9meth]]|HUN|1976 Summer}}\n|-\n|{{OlympicSilverMedalist|[[Hannu Siitonen]]|FIN|1976 Summer}}\n|-\n|{{OlympicBronzeMedalist|[[Gheorghe Megelea]]|ROM|1976 Summer}}\n|}\n\n==Abbreviations==\n*''All results shown are in metres''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\" width=\"35%\"\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"ccffcc\"| '''Q''' || aut